description: When homeless, young Nikita is framed for the killing of a policeman, she is given a choice -- join Section One or rot in prison. Section One is a secret government organization comprised of some of the smartest, most dangerous and ruthless people in the world. When Nikita chooses to join Section One, she is trained to be an elite assassin in the supposed fight against international terrorism ... at least that's what Section One tells her. Nikita's trainer is emotionless, coldly efficient Michael, with whom Nikita eventually becomes romantically involved.

name: Dark Angel
title: 2000 ‧ Sci-fi ‧ 2 seasons
description: A genetically enhanced superhuman prototype, Max, who, as a child, escaped from a covert government military facility along with 11 others who were all being raised and trained to be super-soldiers. Now an adult, Max joins forces with idealistic cyber journalist Logan to battle corruption in post-apocalypse America as he constantly tries to elude capture by government agents. While all that is going on, Max also searches for her genetically enhanced brothers and sisters, all of whom were scattered in the aftermath of their escape.

name: Snoops
title: 1999 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Three sexy private eyes team up with a surveillance expert to crack cases. There's plenty of catty repartee, cleavage and voyeurism - plus a suitcase full of high-tech toys.

name: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
title: 2013 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 8 seasons
description: Ray Holt, an eccentric commanding officer, and his diverse and quirky team of odd detectives solve crimes in Brooklyn, New York City.

name: Monk
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 8 seasons
description: After a detective is unable to solve his wife's murder case, he suffers from obsessive compulsive disorder. Despite getting sacked from his job, he continues to solve cases with his former boss.

name: The Inside
title: 2005 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A young female agent joins the FBI's Violent Crime Unit in Los Angeles - but unknown to her, her boss recruits her more because of a trauma in her past than for her experience or skills as a profiler.

name: The District
title: 2000 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Newark Police Chief Jack Mannion takes over as Commissioner of the Washington DC police force in a bid to reduce the crime rate in the city and deal with internal politics.

name: Shots Fired
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Officers investigating the killing of a white boy by an African-American police deputy face public anger as a small town in Tennessee is rocked by multiple racially-charged murders.

name: Flashpoint
title: 2008 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: A special tactical team of police in Canada takes on extreme situations that include rescuing hostages, arresting dangerous criminals and defusing bombs.

name: Reef Break
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Cat Chambers' less-than-perfect past as a thief gives her an instinctive gift for understanding crime and criminals, which comes in handy in her new role as fixer for the governor of a Pacific Island paradise. As she becomes enmeshed in fast-paced, high octane adventures and island intrigue, Cat's reappearance also makes waves for old friends, enemies and lovers -- including an FBI agent ex-husband, her imprisoned crime boss and a police detective lover who is in over his head -- and the lines between work and play become increasingly blurry.

name: Crossing Jordan
title: 2001 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: Follows coroner Dr. Jordan Cavanaugh, whose unorthodox methods and forensic skills help the Boston police department bring murderers to justice and closure to victims' families.

name: Cold Case
title: 2003 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: Detective Lilly Rush, a lone female homicide detective at the Philadelphia Police Department, finds her calling investigating older unsolved cases.

name: Without a Trace
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: Detectives associated with a Missing Persons Unit of the FBI in NYC employ advanced psychological profiling to divulge varied facets of the victims' lives and solve complex cases.

name: Thieves
title: 2001 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Johnny and Rita are high-class thieves who are caught red-handed by the FBI. Then the Bureau offers them a get out of jail (not so) free card: recover missing government property to avoid the pen.

name: Warehouse 13
title: 2009 ‧ Sci-fi ‧ 5 seasons
description: Two US Secret Service agents are transferred to a classified supernatural warehouse in South Dakota to investigate reports of psychic activity there and to retrieve lost paranormal artefacts.

name: Hustle
title: 2004 ‧ Drama ‧ 8 seasons
description: Mickey Stone leads a group of highly-skilled, professional fraudsters, who overcome obstacles in order to pull off a series of complicated scams.

name: The Closer
title: 2005 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: The story revolves around Deputy Police Chief Brenda Johnson's innate ability to read people and obtain confessions and how it helps her and her team solve the city's toughest, most sensitive cases.

name: Eureka
title: 2006 ‧ Sci-fi ‧ 5 seasons
description: Eureka, a town, is inhabited by brilliant scientists who work for Global Dynamics, an advanced research facility. When their tests go disastrously awry, Sheriff Jack Carter steps in to help them.

name: NCIS
title: 2003 ‧ Drama ‧ 22 seasons
description: Special Agent Leroy Jethro Gibbs, associated with the Naval Criminal Investigative Service, captains his team to get to the bottom of criminal cases connected to Navy and Marine Corps personnel.

name: Take Two
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: When Sam, a former star of a successful television show, returns from rehab, her career is in ruins. However, she teams up with private investigator Eddie to prepare for her potential comeback role.

name: Rizzoli & Isles
title: 2010 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: Jane Rizzoli, a police detective, and Maura Isles, a blunt medical examiner, share a strong friendship and help each other in order to solve crimes.

name: Chuck
title: 2007 ‧ Action ‧ 5 seasons
description: Chuck's life turns upside down after he downloads a few government secrets into his brain. He is then employed by the CIA and the NSA for their secret missions.

name: Lie to Me
title: 2009 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Through applied psychology, Dr. Cal Lightman and his colleagues accept assignments from local and federal law enforcement agencies, and assist in investigations to reach out to the truth.

name: Elementary
title: 2012 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: Sherlock, a recovering drug addict, and Joan Watson, a former surgeon hired to aid Sherlock in his rehabilitation, help the New York Police Department solve difficult crimes.

name: Faith's Song
title: 2017 ‧ Drama/Music ‧ 1h 43m
description: A girl's faith is tested after her parents are killed in a car crash and she is forced to move in with relatives who are non-believers. She wants to worship God through her singing, but faces ridicule and challenges to her piety at home and school.

name: A Question of Faith
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 44m
description: When three families find themselves in the middle of a crisis, they begin to question their beliefs. However, a series of events bring them together.

name: The Forge
title: 2024 ‧ Drama ‧ 2h 5m
description: A year out of high school with no plans for his future, a boy is challenged by his single mom and a successful businessman to start charting a better course for his life. Through the prayers of his mother and biblical discipleship from his new mentor, he begins discovering God's purpose for his life is so much more than he could hope for or imagine.

name: Like Arrows: The Art of Parenting
title: 2018 ‧ Drama
description: Charlie and Alice try to change their parenting strategy when conflict, rebellion and resentment overwhelm their family. To their surprise, they soon find that effective, lifelong solutions were closer than they had ever imagined.

name: The Perfect Host
title: 2010 ‧ Thriller/Comedy ‧ 1h 33m
description: John, a criminal, makes his way to a dinner party hosted by Warwick Wilson in order to find a place to hide after committing a bank robbery.

name: Her Boyfriend's Secret
title: 2018 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 25m
description: Melissa believes she has found the man of her dreams in John, a client of her business. However, a chance meeting with John's ex-girlfriend leads her to believe that he is hiding a dark secret.

name: Two Against Time
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 40m
description: When a single mother and her teenage daughter are both diagnosed with cancer, the discovery forces both mother and daughter to reassess their relationship and helps both sufferers to overcome the long-time antagonistic relationship that has developed between them.

name: Hostile Advances
title: 1996 ‧ Thriller/Drama
description: The true story about a young IRS agent who is stalked by a colleague. Her complaint of harassment is dismissed by the courts, but her campaign for justice leads eventually to a change in American law.

name: Fatal Honeymoon
title: 2012 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 30m
description: Tina Watson drowns in an unfortunate accident while scuba diving with her husband Gabe on their honeymoon. Gabe is accused of murder and an investigation ensues to discover the truth behind her death.

name: Murder on Pleasant Drive
title: 2006 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 30m
description: When Fran Smith goes missing without a trace, her daughter and sister dig deeper to learn of her whereabouts. Her husband John is a worthy suspect but her body is nowhere to be found.

name: Love's Everlasting Courage
title: 2011 ‧ Western/Romance ‧ 1h 28m
description: After Clark's hardworking wife dies an untimely death due to fever, he, along with his young daughter Missie, decides to turn to his parents for care and support.

name: Love Begins
title: 2011 ‧ Romance/Western ‧ 1h 28m
description: Clark, a cowboy with dreams of travelling the world, falls in love with Ellen while working at a farm. Soon he becomes conflicted about staying back with Ellen or continuing with his journey.

name: New Life
title: 2016 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 28m
description: Childhood sweethearts, Ben and Ava, who have known each other since they were seven, come to terms with a tragedy that changes their lives forever.

name: Hoovey
title: 2015 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 1h 31m
description: While practising, when Eric 'Hoovey' Elliot collapses on the floor, he learns that he has a tumour in his brain. After a dangerous and risky surgery, he begins to relearn everything.

name: A Lobster Tale
title: 2006 ‧ Family/Drama ‧ 1h 35m
description: Fisherman Cody is facing hardships on the work front and at home. While his wife feels neglected, his son gets bullied at school. It all changes when he finds a strange green moss with magical powers.

name: The Short History Of The Long Road
title: 2019 ‧ Adventure/Drama ‧ 1h 37m
description: A teenager has to confront the reality of life on the road after tragedy strikes.

name: Driveways
title: 2019 ‧ Drama/Comedy ‧ 1h 25m
description: A young boy and his mother head over to a late relative's home to clean out her belongings. There, the child forms a special bond with an old man who lives next door.

name: Mountain Top
title: 2017 ‧ Mystery/Drama ‧ 1h 42m
description: A lawyer-turned-preacher must embrace his former profession as he chooses to represent an eccentric man in a court to solve a case that is linked to his sober life in a small town.

name: The Untold Story 2
title: 1998 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 31m
description: Chung and Kuen, a couple in a loveless marriage, welcome the latter's relative into their home. However, strange things begin to occur in their household when she arrives.

name: The Way Back Home
title: 2006 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 33m
description: New York attorney Spencer Krane pays a visit to his grandmother, after she suffers from a heart attack. But what starts as a simple visit becomes more about learning the importance of faith.

name: Wish Man
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 47m
description: Arizona motorcycle cop Frank Shankwitz meets a terminally ill boy named Michael and is inspired to change his life, leading to the creation of the Make-A-Wish foundation.

name: A Killer in the Family
title: 1983 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 30m
description: Three brothers help their father escape from jail, but their love is betrayed when he leads them on a murder spree.

name: Blur Circle
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 32m
description: A single mother (Cora Vander Broek), still grieving the loss of her young son who disappeared two years earlier, meets a man (Matthew Brumlow) with a shrouded past while following up on a lead.

name: Arthur Hailey's Detective
title: 2005 ‧ Mystery/Thriller ‧ 2h 51m
description: Malcolm Ainslie, a priest-turned-detective, agrees to meet a serial killer before he is convicted to find out the reason behind the crimes he committed.

name: The Meanest Man in Texas
title: 2017 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 45m
description: After being sentenced to death for murder, Clyde Thompson is miraculously granted parole. Soon, he finds redemption and love with Julia Perryman.

name: Mockingbird Don't Sing
title: 2001 ‧ Drama/Indie film ‧ 1h 38m
description: In 1970, 13-year-old Katie Standon (Tarra Steele) gains national media attention for having suffered through one of the most extreme cases of child abuse ever discovered. After being locked in a closet for 12 years, Katie is unable to speak or function properly in the outside world. With the attention Katie now receives, researchers and social workers from all over offer to help her -- but not all of them have entirely pure intentions, as some only seek to garner fame from her spotlight.

name: A Matter of Justice
title: 1993 ‧ Thriller/Drama
description: In this adaptation of a true story, young marine Chris Brown (Jason London) returns home to his parents, Mary (Patty Duke) and Jack (Martin Sheen), with his new wife, a manipulative older woman named Dusty (Alexandra Powers). Mary does not support the marriage and urges Chris to divorce Dusty, but Chris ignores her pleas and claims that they are in love. When Chris is found dead, Mary suspects Dusty of killing him, and vows to avenge his murder and gain custody of her granddaughter.

name: Trial by Fire
title: 1996 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 34m
description: Her husband and a lawyer (Keith Carradine) stand by a high-school teacher (Gail O'Grady) charged with sexual assault after a student's (Michael Bowen) suicide.

name: Bless You, Prison
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 30m
description: Nicole Valery-Grossu (Maria Ploae) is an intellectual political activist living in communist Romania. She is arrested for her anti-government views and sent to prison without a trial. She is then subjected to solitary confinement and rigorous interrogation. After months of abuse, Nicole has a religious awakening. Through her newfound faith, she finds the strength to endure the hardships imposed by her captors and inspires her fellow inmates by continuing her outspoken resistance.

name: Fight for Justice: The Nancy Conn Story
title: 1995 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 29m
description: When a woman is stalked by an escaped psychopath who had previously kidnapped and killed her cousin, she launches a dangerous crusade to put the man back behind bars.

name: The Unspoken Truth
title: 1995 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 45m
description: A woman tries to take the fall for another of her husband's violent outbreaks, which results in a man's death, but her actions may spell danger for her young daughter.

name: Shattered Innocence
title: 1988 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 33m
description: A Kansas cheerleader (Jonna Lee) turns 18, moves to Los Angeles and becomes a porno star hooked on cocaine.

name: Escape from Terror: The Teresa Stamper Story
title: 1995 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 30m
description: Teresa's blissful marriage crumbles after her husband starts battering her and consuming drugs. However, he continues to stalk her, shoots her boyfriend and abducts her and their daughter.

name: The Execution of Wanda Jean
title: 2002 ‧ Documentary/Crime ‧ 1h 28m
description: "The Execution of Wanda Jean" chronicles the life-and-death battle of Wanda Jean Allen. By telling one woman's story, the film becomes an unforgettable exploration into one of America's most controversial moral and political dilemmas: the death penalty. "The Execution of Wanda Jean" is an unflinching investigation of the role that poverty, mental health, race, and sexuality play within the criminal justice system.

name: Lies in Plain Sight
title: 2010 ‧ Mystery/Drama ‧ 1h 30m
description: Sofia, a sightless girl, is guided through her adolescence by her cousin Eva. When Eva commits suicide, a shocked Sofia starts investigating and uncovers unpleasant secrets related to their childhood.

name: The Cheating Pact
title: 2013 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 25m
description: Three high school teenagers coerce Meredith, a shy but smart student, to take the College Entrance Test on their behalf. When Meredith winds up dead, all the three girls become the prime suspects.

name: Sworn to Vengeance
title: 1993 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 37m
description: Sergeant Stewart sets off to investigate the murder of three innocent kids with the help of a woman, the only witness in the case.

name: A Murder of Crows
title: 1998 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 42m
description: A disbarred lawyer forgoes the writing of his own book and takes credit for a late friend's book. The book is a murder mystery and becomes a huge success.

name: Outrage!
title: 1986 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 2 hours
description: Dennis Riordan (Robert Preston) is enraged after the man who raped and murdered his daughter is relieved of punishment because of a legal loophole. Riordan then assumes the role of judge and jury and kills the man himself. He subsequently refuses to plea insanity, leaving his defense attorney, Brad Gordon (Beau Bridges), in a tough spot. Gordon then resorts to desperate measures and calls the judge who released Riordan's victim to the stand for a tense debate of legal ethics.

name: Murder in Texas
title: 1981 ‧ Drama ‧ 3h 20m
description: John Hill (Sam Elliott) is a plastic surgeon who may not be what he seems. His first wife, Joan Robinson (Farrah Fawcett), is a socialite who falls ill and dies under suspicious circumstances. Hill proceeds to marry his mistress, divorcée Ann Kurth (Katharine Ross), with whom he conducted an affair while still married to Joan. Ash Robinson (Andy Griffith), Joan's father, is convinced that Hill murdered his daughter. And he is intent on bringing the doctor to justice.

name: Texas Justice
title: 1995 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 55m
description: Millionaire Cullen Davis marries the not-so-rich Priscilla. Their relationship turns sour and Cullen kills Priscilla's daughter and lover. He hires a famous attorney, but things do not go as planned.

name: The Girl Who Played with Fire
title: 2009 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 9m
description: Computer hacker Lisbeth tries to investigate and bust a sex trafficking network jointly with the journalist Mikael. But when she is accused of killing three people, she is on the run from the police.

name: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
title: 2011 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 38m
description: Mikael Blomkvist, a journalist, hires Lisbeth Salander, a computer hacker, to solve the mystery of a woman who has been missing for forty years. The two soon discover more than they bargained for.

name: Warlock
title: 1989 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 43m
description: Horror tale of a 17th century warlock who is transported into contemporary Los Angeles. He tries to reunite portions of a Devil's Book that can destroy mankind, and a witch hunter is out to stop him.

name: Jacob's Ladder
title: 1990 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 53m
description: A postal worker is haunted by flashbacks from his earlier marriage, his torturous days of duty during the Vietnam War and his now-dead son.

name: Night of the Creeps
title: 1986 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 30m
description: An alien experiment containing slug-like organisms crashes Earth and infects a fraternity member. Mayhem ensues when a couple of college boys discover the cryogenically frozen corpse.

name: Brain Damage
title: 1988 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 26m
description: A young man discovers a disgusting parasite has attached itself to his brain stem. He becomes addicted to the psychedelic euphoria it produces, but in return he must feed it human victims.

name: The Exorcist III
title: 1990 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 50m
description: Lieutenant Kinderman sets out to investigate a series of brutal murders with the trademark of a serial killer, The Gemini. However, he uncovers disturbing facts which leave him troubled.

name: Society
title: 1989 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 39m
description: A California teen's worst nightmares about his parents come true when he returns home to find a grotesque party in full swing.

name: Hellraiser
title: 1987 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 52m
description: A couple moves to an old house to find the man's brother and the wife's former lover who has turned into an ugly beast. He now bids the woman to bring him human sacrifices to help him be whole again.

name: The People Under the Stairs
title: 1991 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 42m
description: Three burglars attempt to rob a house and get trapped inside. They are haunted by children who stay under the staircase of the house.

name: From Beyond
title: 1986 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 29m
description: Obsessive scientist Dr. Pretorius (Ted Sorel) successfully discovers a way to access a parallel universe of pleasure by tapping into the brain's pineal gland. When he is seemingly killed by forces from this other dimension, his assistant, Dr. Crawford Tillinghast (Jeffrey Combs), is accused of the murder. After psychiatrist Katherine McMichaels (Barbara Crampton) and detective Bubba Brownlee (Ken Foree) take the case, the trio risks a return to the other world in order to solve the mystery.

name: Night of the Demons
title: 1988 ‧ Horror/Comedy horror ‧ 1h 30m
description: A group of teens decides to have a Halloween party up at the deserted funeral parlor where they accidentally awaken some evil force and find themselves trapped, with no way out.

name: Prince of Darkness
title: 1987 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 42m
description: While cleaning the basement in his church, Father Loomis comes across a canister filled with a volatile green substance. With help from Professor Birack, he realises that the liquid is Satan's spirit.

name: Near Dark
title: 1987 ‧ Horror/Western ‧ 1h 34m
description: Cowboy Caleb Colton (Adrian Pasdar) meets gorgeous Mae (Jenny Wright) at a bar, and the two have an immediate attraction. But when Mae turns out to be a vampire and bites Caleb on the neck, their relationship gets complicated. Wracked with a craving for human blood, Caleb is forced to leave his family and ride with Mae and her gang of vampires, including the evil Severen. Along the way Caleb must decide between his new love of Mae and the love of his family.

name: Pumpkinhead
title: 1988 ‧ Horror/Indie film ‧ 1h 26m
description: After a group of motorists kill his son, Ed Harley consults a witch to summon Pumpkinhead, a vicious creature, to hunt the murderers. He immediately regrets his decision when things take a dark turn.

name: Come and See
title: 1985 ‧ War/Horror ‧ 2h 26m
description: Florya joins the Soviet Army against his family's wishes. After being subjected to unfair treatment in the army, he returns home and finds his family massacred by the German forces.

name: Hacksaw Ridge
title: 2016 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 19m
description: After Desmond Doss nearly kills his younger brother, he refuses to handle weapons or engage in war. However, post the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbour, he joins the American army as a combat medic.

name: They Shall Not Grow Old
title: 2018 ‧ Documentary/War ‧ 1h 39m
description: Using state-of-the-art technology and materials from the BBC and Imperial War Museum, filmmaker Peter Jackson allows the story of World War I to be told by the men who were there. Life on the front is explored through the voices of the soldiers, who discuss their feelings about the conflict, the food they ate, the friends they made and their dreams of the future.

name: Fury
title: 2014 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 14m
description: Wardaddy, along with his crew of five members, embarks on a mission that puts many lives in danger. The crew members realise that the odds are against them, but still decide to attack the Nazi army.

name: Dead Poets Society
title: 1989 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 8m
description: A group of students in a highly conservative boarding school learn to rebel against the status quo and find deeper meaning in life with the help of their new poetry teacher.

name: A Higher Law
title: 2021 ‧ Thriller/Thriller ‧ 2h 3m
description: Ecaterina, high school religion teacher and wife of the town priest, gets involved with a 16-year-old student who has a troubled past. She tries to keep him under control, but loses her own sense of control in the process.

name: Dogs Don't Wear Pants
title: 2019 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 45m
description: The story follows Juha who develops an unexpected but powerful connection with a dominatrix named Mona, following a tragic event in his life that has left him emotionally paralysed. His dangerous addiction to suffocation is reciprocated by Mona leading them both down a wild and crazy path towards emotional enlightenment.

name: Quills
title: 2000 ‧ Drama ‧ 2h 4m
description: Marquis De Sade, a writer, caused political turmoil quite often with his writing. So, the state emperor takes away his ink and quills. Sade, then seeks the help of Madeline, a laundry girl.

name: The Piano
title: 1993 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 1m
description: A mute woman and her daughter suffer exile in New Zealand and bring with them a piano. She is then set to marry a rich landlord but a peasant begins to fall in love with her.

name: Notes on a Scandal
title: 2006 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 38m
description: When a disgruntled veteran high school teacher realizes that her friend, a young and married art teacher, is having an affair with a fifteen year old student, she makes sexual advances of her own.

name: The Violin Player
title: 1994 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 35m
description: The Violin Player is a 1994 French-Belgian drama film directed by Charles Van Damme. It was entered into the 1994 Cannes Film Festival.

name: Taste of Cherry
title: 1997 ‧ Drama/Comedy ‧ 1h 35m
description: A desperate middle-aged man, who wants to commit suicide, searches for an assistant who will bury him in the grave which he has already dug for himself.

name: Children of Heaven
title: 1997 ‧ Family/Sport ‧ 1h 29m
description: Siblings Ali and Zahra make an intricate arrangement to conceal the loss of Zahra's pair of shoes. However, when it becomes difficult to do so, Ali decides to participate in a race to win new shoes.

name: It's a Wonderful Life
title: 1946 ‧ Family/Fantasy ‧ 2h 10m
description: When a frustrated businessman, George Bailey, becomes suicidal, an angel from heaven, Clarence, is sent to him. To his change of heart, she shows him what life would have been without his existence.

name: The Monster
title: 1994 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 52m
description: Authorities use a policewoman to trap an innocent misfit who was mistaken for a notorious sex criminal and killer.

name: My Best Friend Anne Frank
title: 2021 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 1h 43m
description: Based on the real-life relationship between Anne Frank and Hannah Goslar, from Nazi-occupied Amsterdam to their harrowing reunion in a concentration camp.

name: A Beautiful Life
title: 2023 ‧ Romance/Musical ‧ 1h 39m
description: Elliott, a young fisherman with an extraordinary voice, gets the opportunity of a lifetime when he is discovered by the successful and well-known music manager Suzanne. Suzanne soon pairs Elliott with her divorced daughter and music producer, Lilly. On his way to stardom, the struggles of his past threaten not only his big break, but also his budding love for Lilly.

name: Train of Life (Zug des Lebens)
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy/War ‧ 1h 43m
description: The inhabitants of a small Jewish village in Central Europe organize a deportation train so that they can escape the atrocities of the Nazis and flee to Palestine.

name: Cinema Paradiso
title: 1988 ‧ Drama/Melodrama ‧ 2h 35m
description: Salvatore, a famous film director, returns to his hometown for the funeral of the local theatre's film projectionist, Alfredo. He reminisces about his life as a young boy falling in love with cinema.

name: A Bag of Marbles
title: 2017 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 1h 50m
description: Two Jewish brothers, aged 10 and 12, flee from Paris in the year 1941 to escape the Nazi invasion and reunite with their family.

name: The Boy in the Striped Pajamas
title: 2008 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
description: Bruno, the son of a Nazi commander, meets Shmuel, a Jewish boy living in a concentration camp. Later, both the children become friends while being oblivious to the reality of the situation.

name: Jojo Rabbit
title: 2019 ‧ Comedy/War ‧ 1h 48m
description: Hitler Youth cadet Jojo Betzler firmly believes in the ideals of Nazism manifested by his imaginary friend, Adolf Hitler. However, his foundations are shaken when he finds a Jewish girl in his house.

name: 12 Angry Men
title: 1957 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 36m
description: An eighteen-year-old Latino is accused of having stabbed his father to death. He is presented in a courtroom before a twelve-man jury. Eleven out of the twelve men vote guilty, except for Mr. Davis.

name: The Zookeeper’s Wife
title: 2017 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 7m
description: When the Nazi forces invade Poland, Antonina and her husband Jan, the director of the Warsaw Zoo, risk their lives to help countless Jews and animals get to safety.

name: The English Patient
title: 1996 ‧ Romance/War ‧ 2h 42m
description: Hana, a nurse, tends to a plane crash victim who cannot remember anything. With time he gets flashbacks and is finally able to remember his past, but things do not end well for him.

name: Schindler: The Documentary
title: 1983 ‧ Documentary
description: As the Nazis increase their stranglehold in Europe and enter World War II, millions of Jews are senselessly killed. The least likely ally during this time would be a German businessman, especially one who joined the Nazi Party to maintain the status quo. But as this documentary demonstrates, by employing Jews in his factory, Oskar Schindler becomes a hero, saving the lives of hundreds of Jews in Poland and Czechoslovakia from the horrors of ethnic cleansing.

name: Life Is Beautiful
title: 1997 ‧ Comedy/War ‧ 1h 56m
description: When his Italian nation is occupied by Nazi German troops during WWII, Guido, an easy-going Jewish librarian, uses willpower, humour and imagination to shield his son from anti-Semitic horrors.

name: The Pianist
title: 2002 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 30m
description: During the WWII, acclaimed Polish musician Wladyslaw faces various struggles as he loses contact with his family. As the situation worsens, he hides in the ruins of Warsaw in order to survive.

name: Harry Brown
title: 2009 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 43m
description: Harry Brown, a retired Royal Marine, leads a lonely life with his only friend, Leonard Attwell. His life changes when Leonard is killed, following which Harry decides to seek revenge.

name: The Phantom of the Opera
title: Soundtrack album by Cast Of "The Phantom Of The Opera" Motion Picture and The West End Singers & Orchestra
description: The Phantom of the Opera is the soundtrack of the 2004 film which is based on the Andrew Lloyd Webber musical. There were two versions released, the standard 14-track release and a two-disc deluxe edition.

name: Sling Blade
title: 1996 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 2h 15m
description: Karl Childers, hospitalized since his childhood murder of his mother and her lover, is released to start life anew in a small town. But it's not long before he's on a collision course with his past.

name: Happiness
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 14m
description: This dark ensemble-comedy is centered on the three Jordan sisters. Joy (Jane Adams) moves through lackluster jobs with no sense of purpose. Now employed teaching adults, she is dating a student, Russian taxi-driver Vlad (Jared Harris). Helen (Lara Flynn Boyle) is an esteemed poet who becomes amused by her perverted neighbor, Allen (Philip Seymour Hoffman). And eldest sister Trish (Cynthia Stevenson) is married to Bill (Dylan Baker), a psychiatrist with a very disturbing secret life.

name: Arlington Road
title: 1999 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 59m
description: When his wife is killed in action by an extremist group, Michael, a professor, becomes apprehensive of cultural sub-groups. He is suspicious of his new neighbours who seem to be hiding a dark secret.

name: Devil in a Blue Dress
title: 1995 ‧ 1h 42m
description: When Easy loses his job, Albright offers him money to find Daphne, the girlfriend of a former mayoral candidate. Soon, Easy finds himself embroiled in a murder case involving cops and politicians.

name: The Hot Spot
title: 1990 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 10m
description: Harry Madox, an unemployed drifter, lands a job as a used car salesman in a small town. However, after he robs the town bank, two women take a liking to him.

name: The Straight Story
title: 1999 ‧ Drama/Road ‧ 1h 52m
description: Alvin Straight, a 73-year-old, learns that his estranged brother, Lyle is critically ill. Unable to drive, Alvin embarks on a journey from Iowa to Mt. Zion, by riding a lawn mower. Will he succeed?

name: Rabbits
title: 2002 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 50 mins
description: Rabbits is a 2002 series of eight short horror web films written and directed by David Lynch. Lynch himself referred to it as a sitcom. It depicts three humanoid rabbits, played by Scott Coffey, Laura Elena Harring[note 1] and Naomi Watts, in a room. Their disjointed conversations are interrupted by a laugh track.

name: Cure
title: 1997 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 55m
description: "Cure" is part atmospheric crime film and part philosophical meditation. Detective Takabe (Koji Yakusho) is tracking a series of identical murders, committed under the same bizarre circumstances. Nothing seems to connect the murders and Takabe becomes increasingly frustrated...

name: Dogville
title: 2003 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 58m
description: Grace Mulligan is on the run from gangsters and finds refuge in the small American town of Dogville. The residents agree to let her stay, but things take an unexpected turn when she makes mistakes.

name: Adaptation
title: 2002 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 54m
description: Screenwriter Charlie Kaufman is tasked with adapting a book by Susan Orlean into a screenplay. However, his personal problems and freeloading twin brother make the job extremely difficult.

name: Punch-Drunk Love
title: 2002 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 35m
description: A frustrated Barry Egan calls a phone-sex line to curb his loneliness. Little does he know that this will land him in huge trouble and also jeopardise his relationship with Lena.

name: Twin Peaks: Fire Walk with Me
title: 1992 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 2h 14m
description: FBI agents Sam and Chet set out to investigate the murder of Teresa, a waitress. However, Chet mysteriously disappears when he finds a clue to the case.

name: Eraserhead
title: 1977 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 29m
description: Henry, who's trying to survive the gloomy industrial landscape, discovers that he has become a father. His baby turns out to be a mutant lizard-like creature whose endless wailing drives him insane.

name: Mulholland Dr.
title: 1999 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 28m
description: Initially, "Mulholland Dr." was to mark David Lynch's return to television. It is a retooling of a script originally shot as a 94-minute pilot for a TV series (co-written with TV screenwriter Joyce Eliason) for the channel ABC, which had approved the script, but chose not even to air the pilot once it was done in 1999, despite Lynch's labours to cut the project to their liking. It was left in limbo until 18 month later French company Studio Canal Plus (also producer of 'The Straight Story') agreed to pay ABC $7 million for the pilot, and budget a few million more to turn the pilot into a two-hour, 27-minute movie. The cost of the film doubled to $14 million as sets had to be reconstructed and actors recalled.

name: Inland Empire
title: 2006 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 3 hours
description: As an actress begins working in a remake of an unfinished Polish film that was believed to be cursed, the lines between reality and fiction become blurred for her.

name: A Perfect Murder
title: 1998 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 47m
description: Steven finds that his wife Emily, a multi-millionaire, is having an affair with David, a struggling artist. Steven plans his wife's murder with David, only to get trapped further in the conspiracy.

name: The Devil's Advocate
title: 1997 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 2h 24m
description: Kevin gets an irresistible offer from a law firm in New York and he moves to the city with his wife. Soon, he gets consumed by his work, while his wife begins to suffer from visions and nightmares.

name: A Time to Kill
title: 1996 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 29m
description: African-American Carl kills the two white men who raped his daughter as their trial is set to begin. Carl hires a white American to defend and acquit him in a de facto segregationist southern US town.

name: Open Range
title: 2003 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 19m
description: Three cowboy friends, while free grazing their cattle across the vast prairies of the West, come across a town ruled by a kingpin rancher who governs the territory through fear, tyranny and violence.

name: The Last of the Mohicans
title: 1992 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 52m
description: When a British officer's daughter, Cora, gets caught in the crossfire during the French and Indian War, Hawkeye, a man adopted by the Mohicans, must save her.

name: The Wild Bunch
title: 1969 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 25m
description: A troop of aging outlaws plot a grand heist, before they could retire from the criminal world. They ride into a Texas border town in order to rob a local railroad office.

name: Once Upon a Time in the West
title: 1968 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 55m
description: A railroad tycoon hires a cruel mercenary to kill a man who owns prime estate. But when the man's widow inherits the land, only an outlaw and a mysterious gunslinger can protect her from being killed.

name: Breakdown
title: 1997 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 33m
description: When a couple drives cross-country to California, their car breaks down in a desolate region and the wife disappears. The husband's frantic search for his missing wife unveils a chain of crimes.

name: Red Rock West
title: 1993 ‧ Thriller/Noir ‧ 1h 38m
description: When a promised job for Texan Michael fails to materialize in Wyoming, Mike is mistaken by Wayne to be the hitman he hired to kill his unfaithful wife, Suzanne.

name: Die Hard with a Vengeance
title: 1995 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 11m
description: A terrorist, Simon Gruber, wants to rob the Federal Reserve Building. He engages disgraced police officer John McClane in a game where if the cop loses, it will result in bombs going off in New York.

name: Ransom
title: 1996 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 1m
description: Tom Mullen is a millionaire whose son has been kidnapped. The kidnappers are untraceable and have asked for a huge ransom. Teaming with the FBI, Tom comes up with a clever plan to rescue his son.

name: Glory
title: 1989 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 2m
description: During the American Civil War, Robert Gould Shaw is promoted to colonel of one of the Union Army's first all-black regiments. As he leads the group, he encounters prejudice on both sides of the war.

name: Malcolm X
title: 1992 ‧ Drama ‧ 3h 22m
description: Malcolm Little, an African-American leader, starts out as a small-time gangster. However, after hitting rock bottom, he becomes a member of the Nation of Islam.

name: Mississippi Masala
title: 1991 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 58m
description: After Mina's (Sarita Choudhury) Indian family is ousted from their home in Uganda by dictator Idi Amin, they relocate to Mississippi to start a new life. Mina falls for Demetrius (Denzel Washington), a young carpet cleaner, despite the protestations of their families over their racial difference. The families and their surrounding communities begin to feud, putting even more pressure on the couple's romance. Having to choose between family and love, Mina and Demetrius run away together.

name: Philadelphia
title: 1993 ‧ Drama/Trial drama ‧ 2h 6m
description: A young Philadelphia lawyer who is infected with AIDS keeps his homosexuality hidden from his employers. When he is suddenly dismissed, he hires a homophobic lawyer for a wrongful dismissal suit.

name: Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 47m
description: When four friends end up losing money to a gangster in a card game, they are forced to choose a crooked path to clear the debt and save themselves.

name: Kill Bill: Volume 1
title: 2003 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 51m
description: A pregnant assassin, code-named The Bride, goes into a coma for four years after her ex-boss Bill brutally attacks her. When she wakes up, she sets out to seek revenge on him and his associates.

name: Death Proof
title: 2007 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 50m
description: Julia, Shanna and Arlene are three best friends who like to spend their time in a local restaurant. Mike, a psychopathic killer, notices them in the restaurant and plans to kill them.

name: Bottle Rocket
title: 1996 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 31m
description: Anthony, Dignan and Bob are three friends who are fed up with life and want to get out of their hopeless situations. They decide to partake in a robbery and become rich.

name: O Brother, Where Art Thou?
title: 2000 ‧ Comedy/Adventure ‧ 1h 46m
description: After escaping prison, Ulysses, Delmar and Pete embark on a journey to find a hidden treasure. As lawmen pursue them, a new companion and a brush with antisocial elements turn their lives around.

name: The Godfather Part II
title: 1974 ‧ Crime/Drama ‧ 3h 22m
description: Vito's popularity in the underworld is on the rise, while his son, Michael's career is swinging downwards. In order to redeem himself, Michael must fight his enemies, including his own brother.

name: Cape Fear
title: 1991 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 2h 8m
description: After serving a 14-year prison sentence for raping a young woman, Max stalks Sam, his defence lawyer, and his family to take revenge for concealing evidence that was in his favour during the trial.

name: Gotti
title: 1996 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 56m
description: John Gotti Jr, an Italian-American gangster, goes on to become the boss of the Gambino crime family in New York. Things take an unexpected turn when the FBI finally manages to convict him.

name: A Bronx Tale
title: 1993 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 1m
description: Calogero, a teenager from the Bronx, befriends Sonny, a local mobster who initiates him into the gangster ways. His life takes a turn for the worse when he falls in love with his classmate Jane.

name: Once Upon a Time in America
title: 1984 ‧ Crime/Western ‧ 4h 11m
description: Noodles, who was a gangster during the Prohibition Era, returns to New York after a self-imposed exile to confront his past and make amends for his mistakes.

name: The Untouchables
title: 1987 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 59m
description: Despite Prohibition in the USA, a mobster, Al Capone, continues his illicit liquor business. A federal agent, Eliot Ness, is assigned to expose Capone's illegal business and bring him to justice.

name: Raising Arizona
title: 1987 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 34m
description: Herbert 'Hi' and Edwina 'Ed' McDunnough are childless and cannot adopt because of Hi's criminal past. Their yearning for a child leads them to kidnap one of the quintuplets of a rich businessman.

name: State of Grace
title: 1990 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 14m
description: After returning to his friends and love in Hell's kitchen, a stronghold of the Irish, Terry finds them in war with the Italian Mafia but what happens when it is revealed that he's an undercover cop?

name: Chinese Coffee
title: 2000 ‧ Drama/Indie film ‧ 1h 39m
description: Harry Levine (Al Pacino) is an aging author in Greenwich Village who fears that his best days might be behind him. Though he saw moderate success in the past, he's currently unemployed after losing his job as a restaurant doorman. When he calls his friend Jake Manheim (Jerry Orbach) to collect a debt, he also shares his latest manuscript, a story about Levine and Manheim's friendship, which leads to the re-opening of old, still unresolved wounds.

name: JFK
title: 1991 ‧ Thriller/Documentary ‧ 3h 26m
description: Not convinced of the verdict that Lee Harvey Oswald alone killed President Kennedy, a New Orleans district attorney sets out to uncover the truth behind the president's assassination.

name: The Sting
title: 1973 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 2h 9m
description: Swindler Johnny Hooker, whose partner is butchered by the henchmen of Doyle Lonnegan, a ruthless crime boss, seeks to take revenge. Aiding him is Henry Gondorff, a conman evading the FBI.

name: The Last Picture Show
title: 1971 ‧ Drama/Melodrama ‧ 1h 58m
description: In the early 1950s, friends Sonny Crawford and Duane Jackson deal with the trials and tribulations of growing up in a small town in Texas that is slowly dying.

name: Serpico
title: 1973 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 10m
description: A sincere policeman of New York reveals the extensive corruption in the local police force, hoping to get rid of the corrupt elements. But his dishonest comrades turn against him.

name: The Big Sleep
title: 1946 ‧ Noir/Crime ‧ 1h 54m
description: Private detective Philip Marlowe is hired by a rich family to deal with a blackmailer, Arthur Geiger. His life takes an unexpected turn as he pursues the case and Arthur is found dead.

name: The Third Man
title: 1949 ‧ Noir/Thriller ‧ 1h 44m
description: Novelist Holly arrives in Vienna at the invitation of his friend Harry only to learn that Harry has died. Unable to accept the inconsistent stories surrounding his death, he decides to probe the case.

name: One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest
title: 1975 ‧ Drama/Comedy drama ‧ 2h 13m
description: In order to escape the prison labour, McMurphy, a prisoner, fakes insanity and is shifted to the special ward for the mentally unstable. In this ward, he must rise up against a cruel nurse, Ratched.

name: Vertigo
title: 1958 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2h 8m
description: John, a retired detective from San Francisco, suffers from acrophobia. He is approached by an old friend, a rich shipbuilder, who wants John to investigate the weird activities of his wife, Madeleine.

name: Double Indemnity
title: 1944 ‧ Noir/Crime ‧ 1h 47m
description: Walter Neff, an insurance agent, is seduced by Phyllis Dietrichson, a married woman, into killing her husband for his insurance. However, Barton Keyes, an investigator, begins to suspect foul play.

name: North by Northwest
title: 1959 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 2h 16m
description: An advertising man, Roger Thornhill, lands himself in big trouble when he is mistaken for George Kaplan. On the run from the police and a foreign spy, he meets Eve, which leads to a bigger problem.

name: Network
title: 1976 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 1m
description: Howard Beale, an ageing news anchor, breaks character and speaks his mind on live television. His rant inspires a moral dilemma, a raving TRP and a live murder.

name: Cop Land
title: 1997 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 44m
description: Sheriff Freddy Heflin idolises the New York Police Department and hopes to join their ranks one day. However, his dreams are broken by revelations of corruption among the men he once admired.

name: Dog Day Afternoon
title: 1975 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 10m
description: A man decides to rob a local Brooklyn bank to pay for his lover's operation, but he is forced to take hostages after the heist does not go as planned.

name: Line of Fire
title: 2003 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Jonah Malloy is a feared mobster. During a gang shooting, federal agents are shot dead. This warrants an open war between hardened criminals and the police force.

name: Justice, USA
title: 2024 ‧ 1 season
description: Taking a behind the scenes look at the US Criminal Justice System.

name: Just Legal
title: 2005 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: David "Skip" Ross, 19, a brilliant legal prodigy, dreams of becoming a great trial lawyer. When he can't land a job at a prestigious L.A. firm because he's too young, Skip ends up working for Grant Cooper. Once a great lawyer, now burned out by the realities of life, Cooper is barely scraping by in his beachfront law office. Together, Skip and Cooper become defenders of the accused and crusaders for the unjustly wronged. Their cases vary from stories ripped from the headlines to clever mysteries with procedural twists. Skip's middle-class parents, Deborah and Lenny Ross, and his underachieving younger brother, Tom, are all extremely proud of Skip's accomplishments but are also concerned for his well-being. Always the underdogs, forced to do the gritty work of finding clues and tracking down witnesses in the beautiful but often dangerous world of Southern California, Cooper teaches Skip to be a lawyer and a man, while Skip renews Cooper's faith in the law and himself.

name: Law & Order Toronto: Criminal Intent
title: 2024 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A psychological thriller wrapped in a criminal investigation, "Law and Order Toronto: Criminal Intent" follows an elite squad of detectives who investigate high-profile crime and corruption in metro Toronto.

name: The Jinx: The Life and Deaths of Robert Durst
title: 2015 ‧ Documentary ‧ 2 seasons
description: A groundbreaking documentary directed and produced by Andrew Jarecki and produced and shot by Marc Smerling (the Oscar nominees behind `Capturing the Friedmans'). The story delves into the strange history of real estate heir Robert Durst, long suspected in the still-unsolved 1982 disappearance of his wife as well as the subsequent murders of family friend Susan Berman and neighbour Morris Black. It features an extended, revealing interview with Durst himself, with whom Jarecki developed a unique relationship following the release of `All Good Things',' Jarecki's 2010 feature about Durst's life starring Ryan Gosling and Kirsten Dunst. `The Jinx' results from nearly a decade of research by the filmmakers, who expose police files, key witnesses, never-before-seen footage, private prison recordings, and thousands of pages of formerly hidden documents.

name: Murder on Middle Beach
title: 2020 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: First-time filmmaker Madison Hamburg tries to solve his mother's violent murder near her Connecticut home in 2010.

name: Making a Murderer
title: 2015 ‧ Crime ‧ 2 seasons
description: Exonerated after spending nearly two decades in prison for a crime he did not commit, Steven Avery filed suit against Manitowoc County, Wis., and several individuals involved with his arrest. Shortly after, however, Avery found himself behind bars again, this time accused of the murder of 25-year-old photographer Teresa Halbach. She was last seen on Avery's property, where she was to photograph a vehicle. Avery and nephew Brendan Dassey were tried and (spoiler alert) convicted of the crime. But that's not the end of the story. When Columbia graduate students Laura Ricciardi and Moira Demos read about Avery, they felt his story would make an interesting documentary. Neither PBS nor HBO were interested, but Netflix took on their concept to produce the docuseries, which generated plenty of publicity and prompted petitions to have Avery's case reviewed, though officials in Wisconsin insist all the evidence is not presented in the program.

name: An American Murder Mystery: The Staircase
title: 2018 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: Michael Peterson finds his life in a mess after he discovers his wife dead at the bottom of the staircase in his house and he is the prime suspect.

name: Death on the Staircase
title: 2004 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: In 2001 novelist Michael Peterson's wife died, and he claimed she perished after falling down stairs at their home. The medical examiner, however, determined that she had been beaten with a weapon, which led to Peterson becoming a suspect in what would become a murder investigation. This series, which began with eight episodes in 2005 before being updated in 2013 and 2018, follows the investigation as it proceeds from Peterson's arrest to a verdict being reached in the ensuing trial. The real-life courtroom thriller offers a rare and revealing inside look at a high-profile murder trial and an examination of contemporary American justice.

name: Three Pines
title: 2022 ‧ Mystery ‧ 1 season
description: A police inspector investigates complicated cases in an idyllic Quebec village shrouded with deep secrets whilst facing looming aspects of his past.

name: The Innocence Project
title: 2006 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: The Innocence Project is a television drama series created by BBC Northern Ireland and first broadcast on BBC One on 9 November 2006. The series follows the work of Professor Jon Ford, who sets up The Innocence Project, peopled entirely by a hand-picked group of law students.

name: Accused: Guilty or Innocent?
title: 2020 ‧ Documentary ‧ 6 seasons
description: "Accused: Guilty or Innocent?" is an intimate account of what happens when someone is formally charged with a crime and sent to trial as told by the perspective of the accused, their legal team and their family members. Each episode follows the person's journey through the planning of their legal defense, the trial, and in the end, the trial. With the evidence piling up, these emotional stores give a firsthand look at what it is like when freedom is on the line. The dramatic inside stories, as they unfold, of people facing trial for serious crimes they were alleged to have committed.

name: American Nightmare
title: 2024 ‧ True crime ‧ 1 season
description: After a harrowing home invasion and kidnapping in 2015, a couple is accused of staging the ordeal when the woman reappears, haunting the couple with a new series of tortures.

name: Unlocked: A Jail Experiment
title: 2024 ‧ 1 season
description: At an Arkansas detention facility, a sheriff implements a radical social experiment to grant inmates more agency.

name: I Got a Story to Tell
title: 2022 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: An anthology series goes down dark, unsettling paths of the macabre where love, lust and terror cross paths.

name: I Lived With a Killer
title: 2019 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: Family members of killers, members of the victims' families, and detectives on each case open up about the emotions and shock experienced upon discovering the identities of murderers.

name: Matlock
title: 1986 ‧ Drama ‧ 9 seasons
description: Benjamin Matlock asks for a heavy sum before agreeing to fight a case. His fees may be high but his skills as an attorney ensure he wins cases he takes.

name: Equal Justice
title: 1990 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Men and women work in a big-city district attorney's office.

name: Close to Home
title: 2005 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Annabeth Chase, a young lawyer who has returned from her maternity leave, finds herself cornered by her new boss Maureen Scofield. But she battles the challenges that come her way and fights back.

name: Into the Fire: The Lost Daughter
title: 2024 ‧ 1 season
description: A tenacious mother unravels the complex mystery surrounding the 1989 disappearance of the daughter she placed for adoption.

name: This is the Zodiac Speaking
title: 2024 ‧ 1 season
description: A family searching for answers shares clues and eye-opening testimonies, about the prime suspect in the Zodiac murders.

name: The Later Daters
title: 2024 ‧ 1 season
description: Six golden singles learn the new rules of modern romance as they set out to find love and rediscover themselves.

name: I Am a Killer
title: 2018 ‧ Documentary ‧ 5 seasons
description: Featuring never before seen footage with unprecedented access to prisons across America, this crime documentary series gives an in-depth insight into the stories of prisoners who are awaiting their fate on death row. Each episode profiles a different prisoner convicted of capital murder and sentenced to death. Recounting the events that led up to their crime, the killers reveal their motivations and how they now view their actions, after time spent on death row. Different viewpoints and the impact of decisions made in a split second that have changed the course of the killers' lives throw into question the viewer's opinions towards the killers.

name: Stolen Youth: Inside the Cult at Sarah Lawrence
title: 2023 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: An exploration of the Sarah Lawrence cult's origins in 2010 on the Sarah Lawrence campus until its recent demise, when the last members find their own paths to survival.

name: A Friend of the Family
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: The harrowing true story of the Broberg family, whose young daughter Jan was kidnapped multiple times in the 1970s by a charismatic, obsessed family "friend." Devoted to their faith, family and community, the Brobergs were unprepared for the sophisticated tactics their neighbor used to exploit their vulnerabilities, drive them apart and turn their daughter against them, permanently altering their lives. And while many are apt to place blame on the parents, Jan Broberg Felt came to their defense in 2019 when she tweeted, "...my parents saved my life. They're the bravest people I know, willing to try to help the rest of you see what they didn't. That is the only reason we told our story."

name: Fight Night: The Million Dollar Heist
title: 2024 ‧ 1 season
description: In a city bursting with fight night anticipation, streetwise hustler Gordon "Chicken Man" Williams plants himself at the center of the action. His big ambitions, and even bigger talk, put him on a collision course with ruthless criminals, each consumed by their own insatiable hunger for the spoils of the event. As dawn breaks on a city reeling from the heist, JD Hudson, a pioneering Black detective, is thrust into a high-stakes game of cat and mouse as the body count rises. With time running out, JD and Chicken Man race against the clock to clear Chicken's name and survive the dangerous forces closing in.

name: Boston Legal
title: 2004 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: Alan Shore, an ethically challenged attorney, joins a powerful legal firm. With the help of his mentor Denny Crane, they win many civil cases, often using unethical methods.

name: The Chestnut Man
title: 2021 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: A figurine made of chestnuts is found at the scene of a grisly murder; from this creepy clue, two detectives hunt for a killer linked to a politician's missing child.

name: Reasonable Doubts
title: 1991 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Detective Dicky Cobb's life turns upside down when he is reassigned as an investigator to assistant DA Tess Kaufman, who is sensitive to the rights of the accused.

name: Blind Faith
title: 1990 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: When a business man is accused of killing his wife, his three sons stick by him and protest his innocence. What happens when they begin to doubt him?

name: It
title: 2017 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 2h 15m
description: Seven helpless and bullied children are forced to face their worst nightmares when Pennywise, a shape-shifting clown, reappears. The clown, an ancient evil torments children before feeding on them.

name: Halloween 4: The Return of Michael Myers
title: 1988 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 32m
description: Michael Myers wakes from his coma while he is being transferred to Smith's Grove Sanitarium. He manages to escape after killing his guards and decides to kill his niece before he is apprehended.

name: Halloween 5: The Revenge of Michael Myers
title: 1989 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 37m
description: A psychiatrist and a sheriff work together to stop the psychopath Michael Myers from killing his niece suffering from psychological trauma.

name: Hatchet III
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 21m
description: The ghost of Victor Crowley has bedevilled and terrorised Honey Island Swamp for decades. Marybeth teams up with a cop and his ex-wife to end the murderous rampage of Crowley for good.

name: Hellraiser III: Hell on Earth
title: 1992 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 37m
description: After a club owner accidentally unleashes Pinhead, an evil entity, from a puzzle box, the latter goes on a killing spree. A reporter who learns about him and his powers decides to stop him.

name: Wrong Turn 3: Left for Dead
title: 2009 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 32m
description: A group of friends out on a hiking trip find themselves trapped in the woods, along with convicts from a nearby prison. Together they must fight against a gang of disfigured cannibals.

name: Wrong Turn 2: Dead End
title: 2007 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 37m
description: Participants of a reality show are tasked with surviving in a remote West Virginia forest. There, they encounter a family of deformed cannibals who want to slaughter them all and dine on human flesh.

name: All About the Benjamins
title: 2002 ‧ Comedy/Action ‧ 1h 39m
description: A bounty hunter is set out to catch a con man who has skipped bail. Accidentally, they meet at a warehouse and witness a diamond scam. They forget about their grudges and team up to detain the looters

name: Civil Brand
title: 2002 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 35m
description: Things are tough at Whitehead Correctional Institute, a notorious women's prison. The inmates include Lil' Mamma (Lark Voorhies), a pregnant teen, and Nikki (N'Bushe Wright), the queen bee of Whitehead. The inmates are under the supervision of abusive warden Dease (Clifton Powell), who forces them to endure hours of hard labor, from which he profits. Eventually, the women band together and reach out to part-time prison guard Michael (Mos Def), a law student, who helps them fight for reform.

name: Tales from the Hood
title: 1995 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 38m
description: A creepy mortician, Mr. Simms (Clarence Williams III), attempts to scare teenage drug dealer Stack (Joe Torry) and his friends straight by telling them four horrifying stories. One is about a guilt-riddled cop (Anthony Griffith) who goes crazy after ignoring his corrupt partner (Michael Massee). He also tells of a meek schoolboy (Brandon Hammond) with terrifying supernatural powers. Although the young thugs want to take their drugs and escape Mr. Simms, he still has two more tales to tell.

name: It Came from Outer Space
title: 1953 ‧ Sci-fi/Horror ‧ 1h 21m
description: John Putnam, a stargazer, witnesses a spaceship landing in the Arizona desert, but none of the townsfolk believe him. Horror strikes, when residents begin to disappear.

name: Vampires
title: 1998 ‧ Horror/Western ‧ 1h 43m
description: Jack and his team of mercenaries must hunt down vampires and retrieve the Black Cross of Berziers, an ancient relic that, should it be obtained by vampires, will allow them to endure the sunlight.

name: The Night Flier
title: 1997 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 37m
description: Two investigative reporters for a tabloid magazine set out to find a vampire who travels by private plane killing victims in rural airports.

name: Sometimes They Come Back
title: 1991 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 38m
description: A school teacher returns to the town he grew up in, only to be haunted by the ghosts of high school thugs who were killed in a freak accident along with his brother.

name: Quicksilver Highway
title: 1997 ‧ Horror/Comedy horror ‧ 1h 30m
description: A travelling salesman is terrorised by a psychotic hitchhiker with chattering teeth, while a plastic surgeon's hands revolt against him.

name: The Haunting in Connecticut 2: Ghosts of Georgia
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 40m
description: Andy and Lisa move into an old Southern house in Georgia with their daughter. Soon, they discover that they are not alone and learn a haunting and destructive secret of the house.

name: Dracula: Dead and Loving It
title: 1995 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 28m
description: Count Dracula travels from his hometown Transylvania to London, where he learns about the attractive Mina. However, vampire hunter Van Helsing creates problems and makes the Count's chase arduous.

name: High Spirits
title: 1988 ‧ Comedy/Horror ‧ 1h 39m
description: Peter owns an Irish castle which has been turned into a bed and breakfast. He spreads a rumour saying the castle is haunted in an attempt to gain more customers.

name: The 'Burbs
title: 1989 ‧ Comedy/Horror ‧ 1h 41m
description: Ray, who wishes to relax in his suburban home, becomes increasingly suspicious of his bizarre neighbours, the Klopeks. With his friends, he is determined to prove that they represent a grisly cult.

name: Nightbreed
title: 1990 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 42m
description: A group of mutants attempt to escape a psychotic serial killer and redneck vigilantes with the help of a young man who discovers them.

name: Hellraiser: Bloodline
title: 1996 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 26m
description: Two demons that have different methods of torturing their victims, embark on a mission to kill Dr Merchant, who aims to build an invention that kills evil spirits and closes the gates of hell.

name: Castle Freak
title: 1995 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 35m
description: An American family (Jeffrey Combs, Barbara Crampton, Jessica Dollarhide) that has suffered tragedy inherits an Italian castle complete with bloodthirsty monster.

name: Fright Night
title: 1985 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 46m
description: When a teenager tells people that his next-door neighbour is a vampire, nobody believes him. Therefore, he requests the assistance of Peter Vincent, a has-been horror film actor, to solve this crisis.

name: Army of Darkness
title: 1992 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 36m
description: Zombie-battling hero Ash takes on an army of skeletons after being sent back in time.

name: Braindead
title: 1992 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 25m
description: Overprotective mother Vera Cosgrove (Elizabeth Moody), spying on her grown son, Lionel (Timothy Balme), as he visits the zoo with the lovely Paquita (Diana Peñalver), is accidentally bitten by the fearsome Sumatran rat-monkey. When the bite turns his beloved mother into a zombie, Lionel tries to keep her locked safely in the basement, but her repeated escapes turn most of the neighbors into the walking dead, who then crash a high-society party thrown by Lionel's boorish Uncle Les (Ian Watkin).

name: Scream 3
title: 2000 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 56m
description: As bodies begin dropping around the set of 'STAB 3', a movie sequel based on the gruesome Woodsboro killings, Sidney and the other survivors are once again drawn into a game of a horror movie mayhem.

name: Cherry Falls
title: 1999 ‧ Horror/Indie film ‧ 1h 34m
description: In the small town of Cherry Falls, a psychotic killer begins a bloodthirsty murder rampage. Mayhem ensues when the townspeople realise that the killer's victims are virgins.

name: Cult of the Cobra
title: 1955 ‧ Horror/Supernatural ‧ 1h 22m
description: Two GIs (Richard Long, Marshall Thompson) out of six cursed by snake worshippers expose a killer snake goddess (Faith Domergue) in New York.

name: The Terror
title: 1963 ‧ Horror/Indie film ‧ 1h 21m
description: Andre Duvalier, a French soldier, chases Helene after she rescues him amidst an ongoing war, only to stumble upon a desolate castle that houses the notorious Baron von Leppe.

name: The Ghost and Mr. Chicken
title: 1966 ‧ Comedy/Mystery ‧ 1h 30m
description: An aspiring reporter spends a night in a haunted mansion for a story. But what was supposed to be an open-and-shut case soon turns into a murder mystery when the elusive ghost plays a haunting tune.

name: The Old Dark House
title: 1963 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 26m
description: While delivering a car, salesman Tom finds its eccentric owner Casper dead. When the car crashes in a storm, Casper's relatives invite Tom to live in their mansion, where a series of murders commence.

name: The Pit and the Pendulum
title: 1961 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 25m
description: After his sister's sudden death, Francis insists on learning the truth about her demise. However, when his brother-in-law offers a vague explanation, Francis' probe leads him to a sinister mystery.

name: The Monster That Challenged the World
title: 1957 ‧ Sci-fi/Horror ‧ 1h 24m
description: The story revolves around an earthquake which unleashes a horde of giant prehistoric monsters.

name: The House That Would Not Die
title: 1970 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 14m
description: The heirs to a Georgetown manor learn that their family property is a breeding ground for the supernatural.

name: The Evil of Frankenstein
title: 1964 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 26m
description: Frankenstein's attempts to revive his old monster back to life go awry when Zoltan misuses it for his own selfish purposes.

name: The Night Walker
title: 1964 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 26m
description: A man wishes to make his daughter a reverend but his dreams are shattered when a religious scholar's son impregnates her.

name: The Innocents
title: 1961 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 40m
description: The Innocents is a 1961 gothic psychological horror film directed and produced by Jack Clayton, and starring Deborah Kerr, Michael Redgrave, and Megs Jenkins.

name: House of Usher
title: 1960 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 19m
description: Roderick and his sister, Madeline, are the last two in the doomed Usher family, and Roderick wants the lineage to end with them. But things change when his sister falls in love with Philip.

name: The Tingler
title: 1959 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 22m
description: A pathologist operates a deaf-mute woman to test his theory of 'The Tingler', a parasite that feeds on its host and grows when its host is scared, effectively crushing that person's spine.

name: The Comedy of Terrors
title: 1963 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 45m
description: To earn money to support his drinking habit, Waldo becomes an undertaker and murders people with the help of his assistant. However, the duo gets into trouble when they try to kill their landlord.

name: The Haunted House of Horror
title: 1969 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 32m
description: Trying to salvage an evening after a dull party, a group of English mods and their American friend, Chris (Frankie Avalon), decide to pay a visit to a supposedly haunted mansion. They lock themselves in, and, following a seance, one of them is brutally killed. Realizing the killer must be one of their own, unofficial ringleader Chris prevails on everyone to bury the body and keep quiet. It's only after the police begin investigating that the group decides to ferret out the killer.

name: Wes Craven's New Nightmare
title: 1994 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 52m
description: Freddy Kruger, a fictional villain, enters the real world to murder the people who have escaped from death in his films. Heather is requested by the film fraternity to reprise her role to kill Freddy.

name: Halloween
title: 2018 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 46m
description: After a narrow escape over four decades ago, Laurie Strode comes face-to-face with Michael Myers after he escapes from captivity. She must confront her worst fears and put an end to his killing spree.

name: Friday the 13th Part VI: Jason Lives
title: 1986 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 26m
description: Tommy returns to the grave to check if Jason is surely dead but accidently brings him back to life. Tommy has to stop Jason's ruthless killings and put him back where he belongs.

name: A Nightmare on Elm Street
title: 1984 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 31m
description: Several teenagers are killed by Freddy Krueger who torments them in their dreams. Nancy and her friends need to solve the mystery or they shall be killed too.

name: A Nightmare on Elm Street 2: Freddy's Revenge
title: 1985 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 27m
description: Teenager Jesse Walsh begins to have nightmares about supernatural killer Freddy Krueger, who wants to possess his body in order to carry out a reign of terror.

name: Sinister
title: 2012 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 50m
description: Ellison, a crime writer, moves his family to a house that once witnessed gruesome murders. Soon, when his research leads him to some eerie footage, things take a dark and harrowing turn.

name: The Conjuring 2
title: 2016 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 2h 14m
description: Peggy, a single mother of four children, seeks the help of occult investigators Ed and Lorraine Warren when she and her children witness strange, paranormal events in their house.

name: American Satan
title: 2017 ‧ Thriller/Musical ‧ 1h 52m
description: A hungry young rock band drop out of college and move to Los Angeles' Sunset Strip to chase after their dreams. However, they soon catch the dangerous attention of a sinister stranger.

name: Blade II
title: 2002 ‧ Action/Horror ‧ 1h 57m
description: A rare mutation gives birth to a new vampire community called the Reapers, who attack both humans and vampires. Blade, along with an elite vampire force, is asked to wipe out the Reaper's population.

name: Bones
title: 2001 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 36m
description: Jimmy Bones, a peace-loving citizen, is killed by corrupt cops. Over twenty years later, his neighbourhood has turned into a slum area and his spirit still lingers, trying to avenge his death.

name: Bram Stoker's Dracula
title: 1992 ‧ Horror/Romance ‧ 2h 7m
description: When Elisabeta commits suicide, an enraged Vlad Dracula swears to avenge her death. Things take a turn when he meets Mina and takes her to be the reincarnation of Elisabeta.

name: Detroit Rock City
title: 1999 ‧ Comedy/Musical ‧ 1h 35m
description: Four teenagers desperately want to attend a KISS concert. They are required to break a lot of rules to be able to reach the venue and gain entry into the concert.

name: The Texas Chainsaw Massacre: The Beginning
title: 2006 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 31m
description: Thomas who was born in a slaughterhouse is raised by a family despite his abnormal appearance and psychological problems. Years later, he and his deranged brother set off on a murder spree in Texas.

name: My Bloody Valentine 3D
title: 2009 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 41m
description: Ten years after a Valentine's Day massacre that claimed 22 lives, Tom returns to his hometown to find himself targeted as the main suspect. Only his ex-girlfriend believes that he is innocent.

name: Final Destination 3
title: 2006 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 33m
description: After Wendy has a premonition that her friends might lose their lives if they ride on a roller coaster ride, she manages to save them. But her friends continue to face life-threatening situations.

name: Toolbox Murders
title: 2004 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 35m
description: A young couple moves into a mysterious building called Lusman Arms. They are soon locked in a battle of survival, when unexpected and tragic events begin to unfold.

name: The Texas Chainsaw Massacre 2
title: 1986 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 40m
description: Serial killer Leatherface and his cannibalistic family terrorise Vanita, a radio DJ. Fortunately, a former Texas Ranger is hellbent on hunting them down.

name: Freddy vs. Jason
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 38m
description: Freddy who is losing power, resurrects Jason to terrorize the people of Springwood. But Jason starts intruding on Freddy's territory and this eventually leads to a stand-off between the two monsters.

name: The Texas Chainsaw Massacre
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 38m
description: A few friends are horrified when a hitch-hiker shoots herself in their car. Looking for help in a town, they find themselves being targeted by a family of cannibals and a chainsaw-wielding lunatic.

name: The Others
title: 2001 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 44m
description: Grace moves into a new house with her children in Jersey. However, when inexplicable events start to take place at the residence, Grace becomes convinced that the house is haunted.

name: Doctor Sleep
title: 2019 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 2h 32m
description: While Danny Torrance struggles to overcome his traumatic past, he finds a little girl sharing his gift of the shine. Thereafter, he goes on a quest to protect her from the bloodthirsty True Knot.

name: The Haunting in Connecticut
title: 2009 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 42m
description: In order to help their son recover, the Campbell family moves to upstate Connecticut. But they soon discover that their new Victorian abode has a disturbing history and is haunted.

name: Jeepers Creepers
title: 2001 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 30m
description: Darry and Patricia, returning home for spring break, encounter a nightmarish scenario in a secluded countryside when they bump into a flesh-eating creature that is on a ritualistic killing spree.

name: Dead Silence
title: 2007 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 29m
description: After the delivery of a mysterious package, Jamie's wife is found murdered. When he digs deeper, he realises that her death might have a connection with a deceased ventriloquist and her dummy.

name: I Still Know What You Did Last Summer
title: 1998 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 41m
description: Four high school teenagers try to cover up a hit-and-run case. A year later, they start receiving anonymous letters. Each one is attacked by a mysterious man who knows their deep, dark secret.

name: Stir of Echoes
title: 1999 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 39m
description: Blue-collared Tom disbelieves paranormal phenomena. A set of circumstances makes him allow his wife's sister Lisa to put him into a hypnotic trance. He then begins to see visions of a female ghost.

name: I Know What You Did Last Summer
title: 1997 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 41m
description: After a night of revelry, four friends accidentally run over a man and dump his body to conceal their secret, unaware that the following year brings a series of eerie events in their lives.

name: Halloween H20: 20 Years Later
title: 1998 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 26m
description: After escaping her brother Michael Myers's attacks, Laurie relocates to California and adopts a new identity. Twenty years later, Michael discovers her whereabouts and plans to kill her and her son.

name: Ghost Ship
title: 2002 ‧ Horror/Suspense ‧ 1h 31m
description: A salvage crew discovers a long-lost passenger ship floating lifelessly in a region, and as the crew members try to tow it back, strange things occur. Soon, they discover that the ship is haunted.

name: Final Destination 2
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 30m
description: Kimberly has a vision of a freak accident that takes place on the highway she is travelling through. She manages to save herself and a few others, but Death hunts them down for escaping their fate.

name: Jeepers Creepers 2
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 46m
description: A bus full of a high school basketball team, coaches and cheerleaders is stranded on a lonely road. They are soon attacked by The Creeper, a winged, flesh-eating monster that rises every 23 years.

name: Thirteen Ghosts
title: 2001 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 31m
description: Arthur, along with his two kids, inherits his Uncle Cyrus' glass house in which 12 ghosts are jailed. They, along with a nanny and attorney, then get trapped inside a devilish machine of that house.

name: Berserk: The Golden Age Arc II - The Battle for Doldrey
title: 2012 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 35m
