description: The Band of Hawkes are hired to take back the fortress of Doldrey and, in doing so, they hope to end the war.

name: Sword Art Online Progressive: Scherzo of Deep Night
title: 2022 ‧ Sci-fi/Fantasy ‧ 1h 40m
description: Two months have passed since the deadly game began, and Kirito and Asuna continue to make progress. They stop for treasure, but then they must face Asuna's least favourite monster.

name: Ghost Cat Anzu
title: 2024 ‧ Animation/Adventure ‧ 1h 34m
description: Karin, a headstrong 11-year-old girl, moves to rural Japan to live with her grandfather, a monk. However, she soon forms an unlikely friendship with a phantom feline that becomes her guardian.

name: Code Geass: Akito the Exiled 4 - From the Memories of Hatred
title: 2015 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1 hour
description: While W-0 is away, Leila and the remaining crew at base find themselves surrounded by Britannian Knightmares. Piloting the Vercingetorix, Shin Hyuuga leads the enemy charge, having usurped the position of Grand Master in the Knights of St. Michael. With her core members unavailable, it's up to Leila to protect her comrades, but this may be much tougher than she realizes: a spy lurking among them is finally ready to reveal himself. Left with no choice but to surrender, Leila arranges a meeting with Shin in order to ensure the safety of her squad. But as negotiations begin to fall apart, Akito and an unexpected ally return in the nick of time to turn things around.

name: Goblin Slayer: Goblin's Crown
title: 2020 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 25m
description: A young priestess begins training as an adventurer to fight dangerous monsters overtaking the world, and joins a group of inexperienced warriors to destroy a goblin nest.

name: Trinity Seven the Movie: Eternity Library and Alchemic Girl
title: 2017 ‧ Action/Romance ‧ 55 mins
description: Trinity Seven the Movie: The Eternal Library and the Alchemist Girl is a 2017 Japanese animated romantic comedy fantasy film directed by Hiroshi Nishikiori and written by Kenji Satō based on the Trinity Seven manga series, which Satō co-created with Akinari Nao.

name: OVERLORD: The Sacred Kingdom
title: 2024 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 2h 12m
description: Ains Ooal Gown, formerly Momonga, leads the Sorcerer Kingdom's undead forces to ally with the Sacred Kingdom and Slane Theocracy against Demon Emperor Jaldabaoth.

name: The Bunker
title: 2001 ‧ Horror/War ‧ 1h 35m
description: Claustrophobic supernatural World War Two chiller. When seven German soldiers realise they are trapped in a half-finished concrete bunker, and with US troops advancing, they try to find an escape route through the catacombs beneath the bunker - where unspeakable evil lurks.

name: Frankenstein's Army
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 26m
description: A squad of Russian soldiers must go to a remote East German village to locate missing comrades in the waning days of Word War II. Unearthing a plot to resurrect fallen soldiers, the squad becomes the target of cobbled-together monsters.

name: Olympus Has Fallen
title: 2013 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2 hours
description: A group of North Koreans seeking to reunify the Korean Peninsula storms the White House, holding the US president hostage in a bunker. Mike Banning, an ex-Secret Service agent, tries to rescue him.

name: Echo Torch
title: 2016 ‧ Sci-fi/Horror ‧ 21 mins
description: Synopsis. A photographer creates an electrical light - the Echo Torch - that exposes the presence of paranormal spirits. Using the torch to search for a woman from his past, he discovers a hidden world filled with beautiful spirits, strange creatures, and dangerous phantoms.

name: Megan
title: 2018 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 8 mins
description: Megan is a proof of concept film that pays homage to the Cloverfield franchise. It was released on YouTube on July 31, 2018 and immediately went viral.

name: Submarine Command
title: 1951 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 27m
description: Early in his naval career, Ken White (William Holden) is suddenly given command of his submarine, the USS Tiger Shark. To keep from being sunk, he orders a dive while the captain and another crewman are outside, and both are killed. White is promoted, but the events on the Tiger Shark continue to haunt him and also disrupt his marriage. Eventually, White takes a desk job. But when the Korean War flares up, White is called back to active duty and asked to lead the Tiger Shark once more.

name: Lord of Shanghai
title: 2016 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 51m
description: After being sold to a brothel as a maid, Cassia piques the interest of Chang Lixong, a gang leader. When Lord Chang is killed, she is rendered helpless and must fend for herself and their daughter.

name: The Sniper
title: 2021 ‧ War/Action
description: Learning about Abdolrasoul Zarrin, the Iranian sniper of the Iran-Iraq war, who is known as the best sniper in the contemporary world wars with a record of 3,000 successful shootings with Dragunov weapons.

name: R'ha
title: 2013 ‧ Sci-fi/Animation
description: R´ha is an animated science-fiction short movie created by Kaleb Lechowski during the first year of his studies. A member of an alien race is being interrogated and tortured by a machine.

name: Traveler
title: 2015 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 5 mins
description: A group of friends build a jet-powered craft to teleport across the universe. It's only when they succeed that their problems begin.

name: Uncharted Live Action Fan Film
title: 2018 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 14 mins
description: The Uncharted Live Action Fan Film is a 2018 action-adventure short film based on the Uncharted video game series by Naughty Dog.

name: Resident Evil: Degeneration
title: 2008 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 38m
description: When Harvardville is attacked by a warrior seeking revenge, Leon Kennedy and Claire Redfield join force to control a mutated monster unleashed by a deadly virus.

name: Batman: Under the Red Hood
title: 2010 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 15m
description: Red Hood, a villain who knows Batman's every move, takes Gotham City by firestorm as he begins cleaning it with the efficacy of Batman. The Joker then resurfaces to taunt his old nemesis, Red Hood.

name: SCP: Overlord
title: 2020 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 35 mins
description: SCP: OVERLORD is a short film created by Interspace Anomalies and Retro Digital and published by Evan Royalty onto YouTube on November 14th, 2020. It takes place in the SCP universe and contains a higher budget than its predecessor, SCP: Dollhouse. It was directed by Stephen Hancock and written by Evan Muir.

name: Emesis Blue
title: 2023 ‧ Horror/Animation ‧ 1h 48m
description: Emesis Blue is a 2023 Australian animated independent psychological horror fan film based on the multiplayer first-person shooter game Team Fortress 2. The film was produced entirely in Source Filmmaker, by the fan group Fortress Films, and released for free on YouTube on February 20, 2023.

name: Assassin's Creed: Embers
title: 2011 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 21 mins
description: Assassin's Creed: Embers is a 2011 Canadian animated short film created by UbiWorkshop, based on the Assassin's Creed video game franchise.

name: Tekken: Blood Vengeance
title: 2011 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 40m
description: Jin, his father, Kazuya, and his grandfather Heihachi battle to control the M Cell.

name: Blade Runner Black Out 2022
title: 2017 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 15 mins
description: Blade Runner Black Out 2022 is a 2017 anime short film directed by Shinichiro Watanabe and animated by Cygames Pictures. The short is one of three short films, that serve as prequels to the live-action film Blade Runner 2049. It debuted on 27 September 2017 on Crunchyroll.

name: Ghost in the Shell Arise: Border 1 - Ghost Pain
title: 2013 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 58 mins
description: When cyborg hacker Motoko Kusanagi is hired to investigate a devastating bombing, she battle fight her way through a maze of phantom memories to unlock her mysterious past, and track down the evil mastermind behind the attacks.

name: Harlock: Space Pirate
title: 2013 ‧ Sci-fi/Family ‧ 1h 55m
description: A soldier faces the insurmountable task of exposing the conspiracies concocted by the governing forces of the Earth in order to prevent them from taking complete control.

name: Appleseed
title: 2004 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 43m
description: Deunan Knute (Ai Kobayashi) is a female warrior who survives the Global War. When she meets her old love, Briareos Hecatonchires (Jûrôta Kosugi), she finds that he has become a cyborg due to his injuries from the war. Deunan soon learns that a new race of cyborgs called Bioroids have been created in the peaceful city of Olympus. However, Deunan also discovers that something is sabotaging the Bioroids, causing their lives to be very short, so she dedicates herself to finding out the cause.

name: Tom Clancy's Ghost Recon Wildlands: War Within the Cartel
title: 2017 film
description: The tattoo-faced kingpin of a Bolivian cartel hunts a traitor within his ranks.

name: Bone Tomahawk
title: 2015 ‧ Western/Horror ‧ 2h 13m
description: The small town of Bright Hope is terrorised by a tribe of cannibalistic savages known as the troglodyte clan. However, soon the town's men decide to put an end to the tribe.

name: A Fistful of Dollars
title: 1964 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 1h 39m
description: A stranger rides into a town known for the deadly rivalry between two of its factions-the Baxter's and the Rojo's. Instead of fearing for his life, the man plays the two sides to his own advantage.

name: For a Few Dollars More
title: 1965 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 12m
description: While chasing El Indio, a most-wanted criminal, Monco meets Colonel Douglas Mortimer, who incidentally is also looking for El Indio. They enter into a partnership and decide to split the reward.

name: The Good, the Bad and the Ugly
title: 1966 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 41m
description: A bounty hunting expedition brings two men together in an uncomfortable alliance while looking for buried treasure. They also battle with a wanted outlaw who wants to settle an old score with them.

name: Tombstone
title: 1993 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 14m
description: Wyatt lives a difficult life, always dealing with outlaws. He moves to Tombstone, Arizona, to finally relax, but he runs into the Cowboys and must bring peace back to the town.

name: Just Mercy
title: 2019 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 2h 16m
description: Attorney Bryan Stevenson fights the case of a man who is wrongfully convicted of committing murder and is sentenced to death by electrocution.

name: Queen of Katwe
title: 2016 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 2h 4m
description: Phiona's life changes after she meets Robert Katende, who teaches her to play chess. Under Katende's guidance, Phiona becomes a top player and sees an opportunity to escape from a life of poverty.

name: The Blind Side
title: 2009 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 2h 9m
description: Michael, a homeless African-American teenager, is adopted by a Caucasian family who helps him overcome his learning difficulties and achieve excellence in American football.

name: The Pursuit of Happyness
title: 2006 ‧ Family/Drama ‧ 1h 57m
description: Chris Gardner takes up an unpaid internship in a brokerage firm after he loses his life's earnings selling a product he invested in. His wife leaves him and he is left with the custody of his son.

name: Air
title: 2023 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 1h 52m
description: Sonny Vaccaro and Nike pursue basketball rookie Michael Jordan, creating a partnership that revolutionizes the world of sports and contemporary culture.

name: Moneyball
title: 2011 ‧ Sport/Comedy ‧ 2h 13m
description: Oakland Athletics general manager Billy Beane decides to challenge the old school selection methods. He sets off to assemble a baseball team using an innovative computer-generated analysis.

name: On The Line: The Richard Williams Story
title: 2022 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1h 33m
description: Richard Williams retraces his family's journey from the poverty-stricken streets of Louisiana to the grass courts of Wimbledon, fighting back against systems of racial oppression and changing the game of tennis forever.

name: Fightgirl Ayse
title: 2007 ‧ Action/Sport ‧ 1h 40m
description: Aicha, a high school student, wishes to learn the martial arts. However, she struggles while juggling between her studies and her passion for kung fu as her parents oppose her decision.

name: 21 Grams
title: 2003 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 4m
description: A severely ill mathematician, an ex-convict and a grief-stricken mother find their lives intertwined through a fatal automobile accident that changes them in ways they could never imagine.

name: Sleepers
title: 1996 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 27m
description: Four young men are sent to a detention centre after a prank goes wrong. There, they are abused by the guards, damaging their psyche. Thirteen years later, they decide to bring the culprits to justice.

name: Wind River
title: 2017 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 47m
description: Cory, a wildlife officer who is haunted by a tragedy that happened because of him, teams up with an FBI agent in solving a murder and hopes to get redemption from his past regrets.

name: 3:10 to Yuma
title: 2007 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 2m
description: A Civil War veteran and rancher, Dan Evans, agrees to guard Ben Wade, an outlaw, until he can be put in prison, in return for a reward which will help him buy back his farm and restore his honour.

name: Coach Carter
title: 2005 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 2h 16m
description: A sports goods store owner accepts the job of a basketball coach for his old high school, where he was a champion athlete. Dismayed by the attitudes of his players, he sets out to change things.

name: A Beautiful Mind
title: 2001 ‧ Thriller/Romance ‧ 2h 15m
description: John Nash, a brilliant but asocial mathematical genius, finds himself in pain when he encounters a cruel disorder. He ultimately overcomes his struggles and emerges free of any trauma.

name: Cinderella Man: The Real Jim Braddock Story
title: 2005 ‧ Documentary/Sport ‧ 55 mins
description: Boxer Jim Braddock clawed his way up from a hard-knocks life to win the Heavyweight Champion of the World title and became an inspiring hero of the Depression Era, as revealed in this biographical documentary. From his family life to his most famous fights and inevitable retirement, Braddock's amazing underdog story is told through rare footage and interviews with famous boxers, sports commentators, referees and historians.

name: Atypical
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: When Sam, a teenager on the autism spectrum, decides to take charge of his life and start dating girls, his family, especially his mother, struggles with his idea of independence.

name: Insatiable
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: For years Patty was overweight, which caused her to be bullied, ignored and underestimated by the people around her. But she is now thin and seeking revenge against those who ever made her feel bad about herself through fat-shaming. Enter Bob Armstrong, a disgraced attorney with a passion for coaching beauty pageant contestants. As one of the only people who sees Patty's potential, he takes her under his wing -- first as a legal client, then as a pageant contestant. Bob hopes to coach Patty to the top of the pageant game, but he and wife Coralee have no idea how deep her rage goes or how far she will go to exact revenge on the people she feels have wronged her.

name: Suburra
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Three young criminals, who are guided by a brutal underworld kingpin, find themselves in trouble when some strong people become their enemies.

name: How to Become a Tyrant
title: 2021 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: History's despots prove that gaining control and ruling with an iron fist requires learning the playbook for absolute power.

name: The Red Band Society
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: A group of teenagers befriend each other in a hospital when they realise it is the only way they could cure themselves of their suffering.

name: Yesterday We Were Still Children
title: 2022 ‧ Thriller
description: Yesterday We Were Still Children (TV Miniseries) When Peter snaps his actions cause his family ties to be broken forever, catapulting his three children into turmoil. His past finally catches up with him, also affecting the intertwined fates of three associated families.

name: Painkiller
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: The origins of the opioid crises in the United States, as seen through the eyes of perpetrators, victims, and truth-seekers.

name: Dirty Money
title: 2018 ‧ Documentary ‧ 2 seasons
description: There's a cliche that says "the rich get richer," and while that may be true it's not always done through legal or moral methods. This docuseries takes a look at stories of scandal and corruption in business, exposing acts of corporate greed and corruption.The episodes feature firsthand accounts of the unscrupulous activities from the perspectives of both the perpetrators and their victims. Some of the tales that are told include a car company that cheats emissions tests to save money and the drama and shady deals that abound in Donald Trump's business empire.

name: The Pharmacist
title: 2020 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: After losing his son in a drug-related shooting, small-town pharmacist Dan Schneider embarks on a crusade to bring a reckoning against the powerful figures behind the nation's devastating opioid epidemic.

name: The Traffickers
title: 2016 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: Nelufar Hedayat goes under the radar to expose the global black market trade. Crossing the globe from Asia to Africa, she meets the people trafficking illegal goods and the ones who set out to catch them.

name: Ghost Recon: Alpha
title: 2012 ‧ Action/War
description: Commandos must capture a war criminal and prevent the deployment of a devastating weapon.

name: Sisters in Arms
title: 2019 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 52m
description: Two French women volunteer to go to Syria and fight the war but everything changes when they form an unlikely bond with a Yazidi survivor.

name: Girls of the Sun
title: 2018 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 55m
description: Bahar, the leader of a battalion of women, leads them in the fight against extremists who captured their small Kurdish town and also hopes to find her son who is held hostage.

name: Hamburger Hill
title: 1987 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 50m
description: Soldiers of the US Army and the Army of the Republic of Vietnam try to gain control over the Dong Ap Bia mountain from the clutches of the People's Army of Vietnam.

name: Casualties of War
title: 1989 ‧ War/Crime ‧ 1h 59m
description: During the Vietnam War, Private Eriksson must fight against the enemy and his own squad leader Sergeant Tony Meserve when he orders the squad members to kidnap and rape a young Vietnamese girl.

name: Born on the Fourth of July
title: 1989 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 25m
description: Ron Kovic, a patriotic young American, joins the army to fight in the Vietnam War, but when an accident leaves him paralyzed, he feels betrayed by his country and turns into a human rights activist.

name: Meeting with Pol Pot
title: 2024 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 53m
description: Three French journalists accept a risky invitation from the Khmer Rouge to visit Cambodia in 1978. Their journey becomes a dangerous odyssey as they witness the regime's brutality and struggle to report the truth.

name: The Shadow in My Eye
title: 2021 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 1h 47m
description: The fates of several Copenhagen residents collide when a WWII bombing mission accidentally targets a school full of children.

name: Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind
title: 2004 ‧ Romance/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 48m
description: Joel finds out that his girlfriend, Clementine, has had him erased from her memories and decides to do the same. During the time of the clinical procedure, he realizes that he still loves her deeply.

name: Manic
title: 2001 ‧ Drama/Comedy ‧ 1h 40m
description: Lyle is admitted to the juvenile psychiatric ward of a hospital along with other troubled teens. Lyle is put off by his new surroundings and has problems adjusting. Will he adapt to his new life?

name: Mysterious Skin
title: 2004 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 45m
description: One youth (Brady Corbet) becomes obsessed with UFOs, while another (Joseph Gordon-Levitt) becomes a gay hustler in the years following a childhood trauma.

name: The Matrix Reloaded
title: 2003 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 18m
description: At the Oracle's behest, Neo attempts to rescue the Keymaker from the Merovingian. He realises that to save Zion he must confront the Architect. Meanwhile, Zion prepares for war against the machines.

name: Enemy of the State
title: 1998 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 2h 12m
description: Robert Dean accidentally gets hold of a videotape that contains evidence of congressman Phil Hammersley's murder. His life takes a drastic turn when he comes under the surveillance of NSA agents.

name: Road to Perdition
title: 2002 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 57m
description: A hit man is on the run after his son witnesses a murder committed by his boss. On one side is his loyalty while on the other he must save his son and also bring to task those who wronged him.

name: I, Robot
title: 2004 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 1h 55m
description: Del Spooner investigates the murder of Dr Alfred, who works at US Robotics, with the help of a robopsychologist. He tries to deduce if a robot has violated the laws of robotics and killed him.

name: A.I. Artificial Intelligence
title: 2001 ‧ Sci-fi/Adventure ‧ 2h 26m
description: David, a highly advanced robotic boy, longs to become human child so that he can regain the love of his foster mother who abandoned him. He goes on a long journey hoping to make his dreams come true.

name: Lord of Illusions
title: 1995 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 49m
description: Detective Harry D'Amour is approached by a mysterious woman who believes her husband is in danger. His investigations lead him into the dangerous world of a fanatic cult.

name: Until the End of the World
title: 1991 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 2h 59m
description: Claire goes to any extent to find Trevor McPhee, but with time discovers that his true identity is Sam Farber and there is more to him that meets the eye.

name: Hardware
title: 1990 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 34m
description: Sci-fi thriller set in a post-apocalyptic world, where a couple revives a robot, unaware that it was designed to kill humans.

name: Darkman
title: 1990 ‧ Action/Horror ‧ 1h 36m
description: A mentally unstable scientist is burned in an attack and later stretches his invention of the synthetic skin to the limit by taking on the faces of other people to take revenge.

name: Nirvana
title: 1997 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 1h 54m
description: Jimi, a successful computer game designer, finds that his latest product has been infected by a virus which has given consciousness to the main character of the game, Solo. Tormented by the memory of his girlfriend Lisa and begged by Solo to end its useless life, Jimi begins a search for Lisa through real and virtual worlds to destroy Solo before it is too late.

name: Natural Born Killers
title: 1994 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 1h 59m
description: Mickey and Mallory, who love each other, have had a violent childhood. They murder her abusive father and then road-trip, during which they kill many people. The tabloid media glamourises them.

name: Demolition Man
title: 1993 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 55m
description: When Sergeant John Spartan is thawed out of CryoPrison in 2032, he is told that Simon Phoenix, the psychopathic killer who was incarcerated with him, is on the loose and must be stopped at any cost.

name: Johnny Mnemonic
title: 1995 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 38m
description: Johnny is a data courier who literally carries data packages inside his head for a fee. This time he carries a package that is too large to hold for long and he must race against time to deliver it.

name: Bird Box
title: 2018 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 4m
description: Years after an unseen entity wreaks havoc on humankind by compelling people to commit suicide, Malorie and her two children, blindfolded, undertake a dangerous journey in a bid to survive.

name: The Shawshank Redemption
title: 1994 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 22m
description: Andy Dufresne, a successful banker, is arrested for the murders of his wife and her lover, and is sentenced to life imprisonment at the Shawshank prison. He becomes the most unconventional prisoner.

name: The Bone Collector
title: 1999 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 58m
description: Lincoln, a detective who has quadriplegia, is on the case of a serial killer who abducts his victims and brutally kills them. Soon, the killer begins to leaves clues for him and his partner.

name: Fight Club
title: 1999 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 19m
description: Unhappy with his capitalistic lifestyle, a white-collared insomniac forms an underground fight club with Tyler, a careless soap salesman. Soon, their venture spirals down into something sinister.

name: American Beauty
title: 1999 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 2h 2m
description: Lester's life seems perfect, having a respectable job and a family, but inside, he is slowly slipping into depression. Struggling with life, he gets infatuated with his daughter's friend, Angela.

name: Carlito's Way
title: 1993 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 24m
description: A former convict vows to leave drugs and violence behind and live a better life. However, circumstances begin to push him towards the same activities that put him in prison in the first place.

name: True Romance
title: 1993 ‧ Crime/Romance ‧ 2 hours
description: Clarence falls in love with Alabama, a prostitute. He decides to talk to her pimp so that they can be together but ends up killing him and runs away with drugs worth a fortune.

name: L.A. Confidential
title: 1997 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 18m
description: Three detectives from Los Angeles Police Department investigate multiple homicides. While unearthing the evidence and the suspects, the trail leads to corruption in their own department.

name: Se7en
title: 1995 ‧ Crime/Horror ‧ 2h 7m
description: Detectives Somerset and Mills, one a seasoned cop, the other a relatively new one, are paired up to solve murders. Together they attempt to find a killer who is inspired by the seven deadly sins.

name: V for Vendetta
title: 2005 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 12m
description: In a futuristic, totalitarian Britain, a freedom fighter known simply as V uses terrorist tactics to fight the oppressive society. Evey aids him in his mission to bring down the fascist government.

name: Minority Report
title: 2002 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 2h 25m
description: John works with the PreCrime police which stop crimes before they take place, with the help of three 'PreCogs' who can foresee crimes. Events ensue when John finds himself framed for a future murder.

name: The Road
title: 2009 ‧ Sci-fi/Adventure ‧ 1h 59m
description: In a post-apocalyptic world, a father must protect his son from a group of cannibals who have menaced the streets. They plan to head south, where there is a hospitable environment to live in.

name: Down by Law
title: 1986 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 47m
description: In a Louisiana prison two listless losers are stuck in a jail cell together. They are joined by a boisterous Italian tourist and suddenly an escape attempt is on the horizon.

name: Re-Animator
title: 1985 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 26m
description: Dan and his girlfriend find themselves in trouble after his fellow medical student, Herbert West, invents a drug to bring back the dead to life.

name: Blow Out
title: 1981 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 48m
description: A sound technician accidentally records the evidence that proves a car accident was a murder and consequently finds himself in danger.

name: Stranger Than Paradise
title: 1984 ‧ Comedy/Indie film ‧ 1h 29m
description: Willie is unhappy when his cousin Eva, from Hungary, comes to stay with him. However, as he starts bonding with her, circumstances separate them.

name: Blood Simple
title: 1984 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 39m
description: A man hires detectives to find out whether or not his wife has been cheating on him. He orders the detective to kill her off if his suspicions turn out to be true.

name: Withnail and I
title: 1987 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 47m
description: Two out-of-job actors travel to the English countryside to spend a weekend with their uncle. But they soon end up getting into enough trouble to put them off the idea of visiting the area again.

title: 1984 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 1h 53m
description: In a futuristic world which is controlled by an omniscient leader, Big Brother, where free thoughts, feelings and expressions are a sin, Winston Smith commits the crime of falling in love with Julia.

name: Paris, Texas
title: 1984 ‧ Drama/Indie film ‧ 2h 28m
description: A man wanders out of the desert not knowing who he is until one day his brother finds him and cures him of his sickness. As his memory returns, he makes contact with various ghosts from his past.

name: The King of Comedy
title: 1982 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 49m
description: Rupert Pupkin desperately wants to become a comedian and approaches talk show host Jerry Langford for a chance to perform on his show. When all fails, he teams up with Masha to kidnap Jerry.

name: Naked Lunch
title: 1991 ‧ Sci-fi/Horror ‧ 1h 55m
description: Blank-faced bug killer Bill Lee (Peter Weller) and his dead-eyed wife, Joan (Judy Davis), like to get high on Bill's pest poisons while lounging with Beat poet pals. After meeting the devilish Dr. Benway (Roy Scheider), Bill gets a drug made from a centipede. Upon indulging, he accidentally kills Joan, takes orders from his typewriter-turned-cockroach, ends up in a constantly mutating Mediterranean city and learns that his hip friends have published his work -- which he doesn't remember writing.

name: The Adventures of Baron Munchausen
title: 1988 ‧ Adventure/Fantasy ‧ 2h 6m
description: Baron Munchausen, along with his talented henchmen and an exuberant girl, sets out to save a town from being captured by the Turkish army.

name: Equilibrium
title: 2002 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 47m
description: A law enforcer, who works in a future where feelings are forbidden, finds himself in a difficult situation when the government he works for betrays him.

name: Lost Highway
title: 1997 ‧ Thriller/Noir ‧ 2h 15m
description: Fred Madison, a jazz saxophonist, shares an affectionate relationship with his wife, Renee. However, his life changes when he receives a threatening message from a mysterious man.

name: Gattaca
title: 1997 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 1h 46m
description: Vincent, a genetically inferior man who always aspired to travel in space, assumes the identity of a paraplegic in order to accomplish his goal.

name: 12 Monkeys
title: 1995 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 2h 9m
description: A prisoner is promised freedom if he agrees to go back in time and find information regarding a virus that has ravaged humanity. Although this mission is dangerous, he accepts it.

name: Strange Days
title: 1995 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 2h 25m
description: Lenny, a former cop, faces dangerous challenges when he finds out that Jeriko, a political activist, was murdered by a group of Los Angeles police officers.

name: Montage
title: 2013 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2 hours
description: Ha Kyung, a mother who lost her child to kidnapping and murder, teams up with two detectives to solve a child kidnapping case. The trio piece together clues and race against time to save a life.

name: Confession of Murder
title: 2012 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 59m
description: A serial killer releases a book confessing to his crimes after 15 years. While a detective and a victim's mother search for him, another killing spree causes chaos among the people.

name: Hit-and-Run Squad
title: 2019 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 2h 13m
description: Eun Shi-Yeon, a police lieutenant works on a hit-and-run investigation, with Police Constable Seo Min-Jae and Woo Sun-Young, as they try to catch Jung Jae-Cheol, a former race car driver.

name: The Roundup
title: 2022 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 46m
description: A police officer travels to Vietnam to extradite a suspect and discovers a murderer who has been targeting tourists for years.

name: Coin Locker Girl
title: 2015 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 1h 50m
description: Il-young tries to get away from her adoptive mother because she does not want to get involved in her mother's criminal activities.

name: New World
title: 2013 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 14m
description: Kang, the head of police, orders the undercover cop Ja-Seoung to participate in the New World project. However, Ja-Seoung must choose between following Kang's orders or staying loyal to Jeong Cheong.

name: Midnight Runners
title: 2017 ‧ Comedy/Action ‧ 1h 49m
description: Park Ki-joon and Kang Hee-yeol are two rookie police officers who stumble across a kidnapping. They go ahead and try to solve the case despite their inexperience in the field.

name: The Man from Nowhere
title: 2010 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 59m
description: An ex-special agent is involved in a convoluted drug ring drama. He has to save a drug smuggler's innocent daughter from being the victim of her parents' fight.

name: Escape
title: 2024 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
description: Following the struggles of a North Korean sergeant who is chased by a ruthless major after he defects.

name: Special Delivery
title: 2022 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 48m
description: A black-market cabbie drives criminals at breakneck speeds until she is left in charge of a fugitive's son.

name: Fabricated City
title: 2017 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 2h 6m
description: After Kwon, an exceptional gamer, is wrongly framed for murder, he along with his allies decides to find the real culprit and prove his innocence.

name: The Suspect
title: 2013 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 2h 17m
description: Ji Dong-chul is a defector who is on the trail of the person who murdered his family. He sets out to unravel the mystery after he is accused of killing the chairman of a powerful corporation.

name: Confidential Assignment 2: International
title: 2022 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 2h 9m
description: Im Chul Ryung heads back to South Korea in pursuit of a brutal and secret criminal organization.

name: The Outlaws
title: 2017 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 2h 1m
description: A detective struggles to keep the peace and put an end to a turf war between two Chinese-Korean gangs in Seoul.

name: The Roundup: No Way Out
title: 2023 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 1h 45m
description: Seven years after the roundup in Vietnam, Ma Seok-do joins a new squad to investigate a murder case. He soon starts to dig deeper when he finds out the case involves a synthetic drug and a gang of thugs.

name: The Roundup: Punishment
title: 2024 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 49m
description: While pursuing the developer of a drug trafficking app, Detective Ma Seok-do uncovers a deadly link to a vast online gambling syndicate, triggering an unprecedented alliance to take down the masterminds.

name: The Witch: Part 2. The Other One
title: 2022 ‧ Action/Horror ‧ 2h 17m
description: After a girl emerges as the sole survivor of a bloody raid on the research facility behind the top-secret Witch Program, she is rescued by a pair of civilians who soon realise that more danger lies ahead.

name: The Witch: Part 1 - The Subversion
title: 2018 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 5m
description: A young girl lives peacefully with her adoptive parents until she showcases her special talent to the world and an army of powerful men from her mysterious past attempt to track her down.

name: V.I.P.
title: 2017 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 2h 8m
description: When a serial killer from North Korea is on the loose, law enforcement agents from his country team up with their counterparts from South Korea and Interpol to apprehend him.

name: No Mercy
title: 2019 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
description: When Eun-hye doesn't come home from school, all the alarm bells go off for her older sister, In-ae. She tries to find her own way to save her sister.

name: The Childe
title: 2023 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 58m
description: Desperate to secure funds for his mother's surgery, an amateur boxer searches for the wealthy father he's never met. Traveling from the Philippines to Korea, he is relentlessly pursued and forced to confront a shocking truth.

name: John Wick: Chapter 3 – Parabellum
title: 2019 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 11m
description: John Wick is declared excommunicado and a hefty bounty is set on him after he murders an international crime lord. He sets out to seek help to save himself from ruthless hitmen and bounty hunters.

name: Mr. & Mrs. Smith
title: 2005 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 2 hours
description: A husband and wife struggle to keep their marriage alive until they realise they are both secretly working as assassins. Now, their respective assignments require them to kill each other.

name: The Beekeeper
title: 2024 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 45m
description: One man's brutal campaign for vengeance takes on national stakes after it's revealed he's a former operative of a powerful and clandestine organization known as Beekeepers.

name: Safe
title: 2012 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
description: Mei, a 12-year-old girl, is chased by Russian mobsters, Chinese Triads and corrupt policemen for the information she holds. She finds relief in the form of Luke Wright, a fighter who shields her.

name: Colombiana
title: 2011 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 48m
description: When Cataleya witnesses her parents' death, she goes on to become an expert assassin and sets out to seek revenge against the culprits.

name: Kill
title: 2023 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 45m
description: A train to New Delhi becomes a combat battleground as a pair of commandos faces off against an army of invading bandits.

name: Major
title: 2022 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 26m
description: Major Sandeep Unnikrishnan faces his biggest battle when he joins the task force to save the occupants at the Taj Hotel attacked by a terrorist group.

name: Neerja
title: 2016 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 2h 2m
description: Neerja, a flight attendant, boards Pan Am flight 73 in 1986. When the flight is hijacked by terrorists, Neerja risks her life to stall the terrorists from attacking the passengers on board.

name: The Attacks of 26/11
title: 2013 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 56m
description: Ten terrorists travel to India and launch several attacks at various places in South Mumbai. Subsequently, the Mumbai Police arrests Ajmal Kasab, one of the terrorists.

name: State Of Siege: Temple Attack
title: 2021 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 50m
description: Armed with state-of-the-art equipment and a plan, NSG commandos risk their lives to save innocent people caught in a terrorist attack on a temple in Gujarat.

name: The Moon
title: 2023 ‧ Sci-fi/Adventure ‧ 2h 9m
description: In the near future, South Korea's first manned mission to the moon ends in a tragic disaster. Five years later, a second spaceflight leaves astronaut Sun-woo stranded in space. Facing another fatal catastrophe, the Naro Space Center turns to its former managing director Kim Jae-guk to help bring Sun-woo back home safely.

name: Don't Look Up
title: 2021 ‧ Comedy/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 25m
description: Two low-level astronomers must go on a giant media tour to warn mankind of an approaching comet that will destroy planet Earth.

name: The Right Stuff
title: 1983 ‧ Adventure/Drama ‧ 3h 13m
description: As the Space Race ensues, seven pilots set off on a path to become the first American astronauts to enter space. However, the road to making history brings forth momentous challenges.

name: Descendants 2
title: 2017 ‧ Fantasy/Musical ‧ 1h 51m
description: Mal returns to the Isle of the Lost as she finds it difficult to adjust to royal life. Uma, her nemesis, unleashes her evil friends and captures King Ben, Mal's boyfriend, to seek revenge against her.

name: The Princess Switch
title: 2018 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 41m
description: One week before Christmas, a duchess switches places with an ordinary woman from Chicago, who looks exactly like her, and they each fall in love with each other's beaus.

name: Camp Cucamonga
title: 1990 ‧ Comedy/Family ‧ 1h 34m
description: An accountant (John Ratzenberger) and his wife do what he's always wanted to do: run a coed summer camp for teens.

name: A Mom for Christmas
title: 1990 ‧ Comedy/Fantasy ‧ 1h 36m
description: Jessica's wish for a mother during the Christmas season is granted when Amy, a mannequin, comes to life and enters Jessica's life as her new mother.

name: Lots of Luck
title: 1985 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 28m
description: A mechanic's (Martin Mull) wife (Annette Funicello) wins a $1 million lottery, followed by more luck and the woes of too much money.

name: Jurassic Park
title: 1993 ‧ Adventure/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 2m
description: An industrialist invites some experts to visit his theme park of cloned dinosaurs. After a power failure, the creatures run loose, putting everyone's lives, including his grandchildren's, in danger.

name: The Parent Trap IV: Hawaiian Honeymoon
title: 1989 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 40m
description: Newlyweds (Hayley Mills, Barry Bostwick) inherit a hotel in Hawaii and go there to run it with his teenage triplets (Leanna Creel).

name: The Parent Trap III
title: 1989 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 40m
description: Tricky teenage triplets (Leanna Creel) try to match their father (Barry Bostwick) with an interior decorator (Hayley Mills) who has a twin.

name: Ella Enchanted
title: 2004 ‧ Comedy/Fantasy ‧ 1h 41m
description: Fairy Lucinda puts baby Ella under the spell of obeying anyone. Life becomes awful for her due to her unwise father, cruel stepmother and stepsisters. Ella and Prince Charmont try to break the spell.

name: Freaky Friday
title: 2003 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 37m
description: Tess and her daughter, Anna, do not get along. However, things take a turn when, in a freak incident, they switch bodies and are forced to live each other's lives.

name: Daddy Day Care
title: 2003 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 32m
description: Charlie and his friend Phil start Daddy Day Care, a day care centre, after losing their jobs. However, Miss Harridan tries to shut their business when it threatens to directly compete with her own.

name: The Swap
title: 2016 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 40m
description: After a mysterious phenomenon causes classmates Ellie O'Brien and Jack Malloy to swap bodies, they are faced with complex family drama and school-life issues.

name: Elf
title: 2003 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 30m
description: Buddy, a human, is raised amongst elves at the North Pole. When he discovers that he is not an elf, he travels to New York to search for his biological father.

name: Princess Protection Program
title: 2009 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 30m
description: After a dictator invades her country, a princess is whisked away to a small rural area by her trusted staff. But she must learn to act like a normal teenager to ensure that her cover isn't blown.

name: Clueless
title: 1995 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 37m
description: Cher is a rich high-school student who is learning to cope with adolescence and its problems. She also helps a new student gain popularity and in the process discovers her own feelings for someone.

name: Mean Girls
title: 2004 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 37m
description: Cady joins a public school in Illinois. Her two classmates warn her to stay away from a coterie of girls led by queen bee Regina, but Cady joins them. However, she gets smitten with Regina's ex-love.

name: Adventures in Babysitting
title: 2016 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 45m
description: Jenny and Lola, two teenagers with completely opposite personalities, travel through the city to track down Trey, whom Jenny was supposed to babysit.

name: The Princess Diaries 2: Royal Engagement
title: 2004 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 53m
description: Princess Mia is in a fix when Viscount Mabrey, an egocentric nobleman, hinders her coronation stating that an unmarried woman cannot become a queen. However, Mia and her grandmother devise a plan.

name: A Cinderella Story
title: 2004 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 35m
description: Sam Montgomery is a good-natured young girl who is tormented by her stepmother and stepsisters. However, her online interaction with a handsome young man brings hope to her life.

name: The Princess Diaries
title: 2001 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 51m
description: A clumsy, shy teen discovers that she's the princess of a small European state. She is then coached and must prove that she is worthy of her title while trying to make it through her school year.

name: 13 Going on 30
title: 2004 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 38m
description: Jenna Rink makes an unusual wish on her birthday. Miraculously, her wish comes true and the 13-year-old Jenna wakes up the next day as a 30-year-old woman.

name: Father of the Bride Part II
title: 1995 ‧ Comedy/Family ‧ 1h 46m
description: George Banks lives with his wife and misses his daughter, who is married. Soon, he finds out that his daughter is pregnant but also gets another unexpected surprise along the way.

name: The Little Rascals
title: 1994 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 22m
description: When Alfalfa falls in love with a girl and tries to woo her, his fellow 'He-Man-Woman-Hating' club members try to sabotage his relationship.

name: Now and Then
title: 1995 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 40m
description: Four childhood friends gather together to prepare for the birth of Chrissey's baby. They wonder how the girls they were at 12 years could possibly have become the women they are now.

name: Twin Sitters
title: 1994 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 33m
description: When identical twin bodybuilders Peter and David save two young boys from the crossfire of a mob gunfight, Frank, the boys' wealthy father, makes a deal with them.

name: The Parent Trap
title: 1998 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 2h 8m
description: Identical twins Hallie and Annie are separated after their parents' divorce. Years later, they discover each other at a summer camp and decide to switch places in an effort to reunite their parents.

name: Purple Hearts
title: 2022 ‧ Romance/Musical ‧ 2h 2m
description: Cassie, a struggling singer-songwriter agrees to marry a troubled Marine, Luke for military benefits. The line between real and pretend begins to blur.

name: My Fault
title: 2023 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 57m
description: Noah has to leave her town, boyfriend and friends behind and move into the mansion of her mother's new rich husband. There she meets Nick, her new stepbrother. She soon discovers that, behind the image of a model son, Nick is hiding something.

name: Wedding Season
title: 2022 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 38m
description: Pressured by their parents to find spouses, Asha and Ravi pretend to date during a summer of weddings, only to find themselves falling for each other.

name: Love Hard
title: 2021 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 45m
description: After meeting her perfect match on a dating app, an L.A. writer learns she's been catfished when she flies 3,000 miles to surprise him for Christmas.

name: To All the Boys: P.S. I Still Love You
title: 2020 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 42m
description: As her relationship with Peter continues to grow, Lara Jean reunites with another recipient of one of her old love letters.

name: After We Collided
title: 2020 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 45m
description: Tessa breaks up with Hardin and begins working as an intern. Her life, however, gets even more dramatic as her co-worker gets attracted to her, while Hardin tries to fix their relationship.

name: The Kissing Booth
title: 2018 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 45m
description: A high school student finds herself face-to-face with her long-term crush when she signs up to run a kissing booth at the spring carnival.

name: The Kissing Booth 2
title: 2020 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 2h 11m
description: After a romantic summer together, Noah and Elle must adjust to a long-distance relationship as he leaves for Harvard and she begins her senior year of high school.

name: To All the Boys: Always and Forever
title: 2021 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 55m
description: Senior year of high school takes center stage as Lara Jean returns from a family trip to Korea and considers her college plans -- with and without Peter.

name: To All the Boys I've Loved Before
title: 2018 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 39m
description: Lara Jean, a high school girl, writes letters to the boys she is infatuated with but keeps them in her closet instead of mailing them. Things change when her sister discovers the letters.

name: Freaks and Geeks
title: 1999 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Growing up circa 1980, a misfit high-school student and his pals are probably destined to become new media millionaires, but right now they're stuck in school, where all the girls are a foot taller and bullies terrorize the gym class. Meanwhile, his older sister is flirting with the dope-smoking bad boys, cutting classes and questioning the point of getting good grades.

name: Rykter
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Rykter is a Norwegian teen drama television series about the life of Erik Nielsen, who had to move to the fictional island Vesterøy. It was produced by NRK3, which is part of the Norwegian public broadcaster NRK.

name: Absolute Beginners
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Two childhood friends enjoying their final seaside summer as they prepare for film school meet an aspiring athlete who ignites unfamiliar desires.

name: 13 Reasons Why
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Newcomer Katherine Langford plays the role of Hannah, a young woman who takes her own life. Two weeks after her tragic death, a classmate named Clay finds a mysterious box on his porch. Inside the box are recordings made by Hannah --- on whom Clay had a crush --- in which she explains the 13 reasons why she chose to commit suicide. If Clay decides to listen to the recordings, he will find out if and how he made the list. This intricate and heart-wrenching tale is told through Clay and Hannah's dual narratives.

name: Euphoria
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: A group of high school students struggle with drugs, love, social media and money as they come of age while trying to establish their identity.

name: Skins
title: 2007 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: The lives of a group of teenagers in Bristol, England, are followed through two years of sixth form, with the story line of this critically acclaimed series delving into such controversial subjects as substance abuse, sexuality, teenage pregnancy, personality and eating disorders, and mental illness. `Skins' is unique in its casting of amateur actors, and the fact that the cast is replaced every two seasons, when the characters leave school.

name: Heartbreak High
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Amerie, along with her news friends Quinni and Darren, must navigate love, sex and heartbreak at Hartley High.

name: Heartstopper
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Teens Charlie and Nick discover their unlikely friendship might be something more as they navigate school and young love.

name: FREE HBO: We Are Who We Are
title: 2020 ‧ 1 season

name: Sirens
title: 2011 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Rachid, Stuart and Ashley are three world-weary paramedics who are forced to deal with humanity at its dumbest. Swept along by an endless tide of bodily fluids (usually not their own), the trio bicker, fight and shag their way through the darkly funny whirlpool that is their lives. Take away the uniforms, the sirens and the fast driving and the three are three ordinary blokes trying to make it through another shift at work. But they have to fight to salvage their own lives after they're done saving others'.

name: Staged
title: 2020 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: David Tennant and Michael Sheen were due to star in a production of `Six Characters in Search of an Author' in the West End. The pandemic has put paid to that, but their director is determined not to let the opportunity pass him by.

name: Inside No. 9
title: 2014 ‧ Mystery ‧ 9 seasons
description: An anthology in which each story explores dark themes and occurs inside a mansion, a dressing room or a flat numbered nine.

name: The Program: Cons, Cults, and Kidnapping
title: 2024 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: Years after being sent to a disciplinary school, a woman who is haunted by her experiences decides to expose the corruption and abuse of the troubled teen industry.

name: Worst Roommate Ever
title: 2022 ‧ Documentary ‧ 2 seasons
description: Roommates with malevolent and sometimes violent intentions turn the lives of their unsuspecting victims into real-life nightmares.

name: Ripley
title: 2024 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: A wealthy man hires down-on-his-luck grifter Tom Ripley to travel to Italy to urge his vagabond son to return home; Tom's acceptance of the job is the first step in a life of deceit, fraud and murder.

name: Peep Show
title: 2003 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 9 seasons
description: This show is about two boys who are in their late twenties-Mark Corrigan and Jeremy Osbourne. The two meet at a fictional Dartmouth University and live together as roommates.

name: Chewing Gum
title: 2015 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 2 seasons
description: British writer and actress Michaela Coel plays 24-year-old Beyonce fanatic Tracey Gordon. The series is based on Coel's lead character in the semi-autobiographical monologue `Chewing Gum Dreams', which follows a young lady as she leaves behind adolescence and enters womanhood. Tracey deals with new adult challenges and her many conflicting interests, as she struggles with the strictness of her religious beliefs and her love of all things Beyonce. Tracey and her mates settle into a new phase in their lives while living in an estate in Tower Hamlets, east London.

name: Beef
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Two strangers get into a road rage incident that brings chaos into their lives.

name: After Life
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Tony had a perfect life -- until his wife Lisa died. After that tragic event, the formerly nice guy changed. After contemplating taking his life, Tony decides he would rather live long enough to punish the world by saying and doing whatever he likes. He thinks of it as a superpower -- not caring about himself or anybody else -- but it ends up being trickier than he envisioned when his friends and family try to save the nice guy that they used to know. Golden Globe winner Ricky Gervais stars in the comedy series, which he also writes and directs.

name: The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: It's the late 1950s and Miriam "Midge" Maisel has everything she has ever wanted -- the perfect husband, two kids and an elegant apartment on New York's Upper West Side. Her seemingly idyllic life takes a surprising turn when she discovers a hidden talent she didn't previously know she had -- stand-up comedy. This revelation changes her life forever as she begins a journey that takes her from her comfortable life on the Upper West Side through the cafes and nightclubs of Greenwich Village as she makes her way through the city's comedy industry on a path that could ultimately lead her to a spot on the "Tonight Show" couch. The series was created by Amy Sherman-Palladino ("Gilmore Girls").

name: Criminal Justice
title: 2008 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: The series revolves around Juliet Miller whose life is turned upside down after an incident that leaves her family fighting for life, love and survival.

name: Bloods
title: 2021 ‧ Comedy ‧ 2 seasons
description: Samson Kayo and Jane Horrocks star as Maleek and Wendy in this comedy drama, both paramedics at the south London emergency service. Maleek is a tough-acting loner and Wendy is an over-friendly divorcée, so when the two are partnered together, they seem a mismatched pair whose relationship is doomed from the start. However, as the duo endure the never-ending rush of 999 calls, put their lives at risk to save others, and struggle to gain the respect of their colleagues, they realise they might just be each other's life support.

name: Broad City
title: 2014 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: Ilana Wexler and Abbi Abrams are best friends who struggle with their low-paying jobs while they balance daily lives in New York City.

name: We Are Lady Parts
title: 2021 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 2 seasons
description: The members of an all-female punk band navigate through various challenges and experiences as they strive to make a mark in the world of music.

name: Catastrophe
title: 2015 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 4 seasons
description: Rob, an advertising executive from Boston, starts dating an Irish professor, Sharon, after he gets her pregnant on a wild business trip to London.

name: Smothered
title: 2023 ‧ Comedy ‧ 1 season
description: Tired of romantic disappointment, independent-minded Sammy embraces a life free of immaturity and dating apps until an unforgettable drunken night out with the kind-hearted Tom leads to the promise of three weeks of no-strings fun.

name: Man Like Mobeen
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Hilarity ensues as Mobeen, who was once a drug dealer, tries to escape his dark past and single-handedly raise his 15-year-old sister.

name: This Country
title: 2017 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: Creators Daisy May and Charlie Cooper introduce a documentary-style comedy about the lives and experiences of young people in modern, rural Britain by following the antics and events of cousins Kerry and Lee `Kurtan' Mucklowe. Each episode shines a light on the peculiar and the sometimes melancholy that comes with living far from the big city, while also poking fun at the idiosyncrasies of neighbours, friends and family. Despite higher levels of unemployment, lack of opportunity and entertainment, fun and mischief is still to be had with the village's scarecrow festival, the attempts of friends to start a business, and in the potential for romance with new arrivals to the village, amongst others.

name: Big Boys
title: 2022 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 2 seasons
description: Two boys from very different ends of the "spectrum of masculinity" become best friends at Brent University freshers' week; in their first year at university, they explore, experiment and try to discover themselves, helping one another along the way.

name: The Lovers
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Janet, a foul-mouthed Belfast supermarket worker, encounters Seamus under unusual circumstances. In complete opposition to her, he lives a London life, works as a political broadcaster, and has a celebrity girlfriend. Despite the apparent gulf in experiences between them, the two find themselves unexpectedly falling for each other. As their extraordinary relationship develops, they must each contend with a wide range of difficulties that stem from the extreme differences in their backgrounds and lives.

name: Stath Lets Flats
title: 2018 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: In the unstable world of London's property market, Stath tries to prove himself as the perfect heir to his father's flat-letting business despite his undesirable personality and incompetence.

name: Dreamland
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Set in the sun-drenched British seaside town of Margate, a dark exploration of the secrets, lies, loves and aspirations within a family of four sisters.

name: Sick of It
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Karl, a taxi driver, hits rock bottom after his girlfriend dumps him. As he struggles to move on, his consistently critical inner voice appears and starts guiding him in life.

name: Bad Sisters
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: The Garvey sisters are bound together by the premature deaths of their parents and the promises they made to always protect one another.

name: Lovesick
title: 2014 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: Dylan, a 20-something romantic, has been intimate with a long list of women during his quest for true love. When he discovers that he has a sexually transmitted disease, Dylan must go back and contact everyone he has slept with to tell them about his diagnosis. Each time Dylan seeks out a different person from his contact list, the show flashes back to a defining moment in a relationship that he would prefer to forget. Friends Evie and Luke, who have been with Dylan through it all over the last decade, travel down memory lane with him.

name: Love Soup
title: 2005 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Alice and Gil, who are both on the pursuit of finding the perfect partner, happen to be made for each other. However, their paths never cross.

name: I May Destroy You
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Arabella, a young woman, struggles to remember the events that took place during her night out with friends. However, she soon realises that she was drugged and taken advantage of.

name: Never Have I Ever
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: After a traumatic year, a first-generation Indian-American teenager wants to improve her status at school, but friends, family, and feelings don't make it easy on her.

name: Ginny & Georgia
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Teenage Ginny and her family yearn to put down roots in a picturesque New England town after years on the run.

name: Crashing
title: 2016 ‧ Comedy ‧ 1 season
description: Six individuals live in an abandoned hospital as its property guardians and strive hard to deal with their relationships with each other.

name: Killing Eve
title: 2018 ‧ Thriller ‧ 4 seasons
description: Being recruited by an intelligence agency puts Eve in the direct path of Villanelle, an assassin. Though the mission is to kill her, the two women find themselves strangely drawn to each other.

name: Normal People
title: 2020 ‧ Romance ‧ 1 season
description: Marianne, a teenager, is bullied by her peers at school while Connell enjoys popularity. As their relationship develops, complications take root.

name: Derry Girls
title: 2018 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: In Derry, Northern Ireland, a young girl and her cousin embark on many exciting adventures after they attend a Catholic girls' school in the midst of a national conflict.

name: Derek
title: 2012 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: This mockumentary-style comedy drama follows a group of outsiders living on the fringe of society. At the group's core is Derek Noakes, a tender, innocent man who works at a retirement home. Derek's love for his job and the people he cares for is evident in everything he does. Derek, who is in his 40s, is vulnerable to being ridiculed and ostracised due to his childlike naivete, lack of intelligence and social awkwardness. Among Derek's co-workers at the retirement home are Dougie, his friend and landlord, and Hannah, Derek's best friend who is smart and hard-working but unlucky in love. Writer-director Ricky Gervais stars in the title role, which is based on a character he created for his stand-up routine.

name: Fleabag
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: A dry-witted woman, known only as Fleabag, has no filter as she navigates life and love in London while trying to cope with tragedy. The angry, grief-riddled woman tries to heal while rejecting anyone who tries to help her, but Fleabag continues to keep up her bravado through it all. Comic actress Phoebe Waller-Bridge stars as the titular character on the series, which is based on Waller-Bridge's 2013 one-woman show of the same name.

name: Dead to Me
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Jen's husband recently died in a hit-and-run, and the sardonic widow is determined to solve the crime. Optimistic free spirit Judy has recently suffered a tragic loss of her own. The ladies meet at a support group and, despite their polar-opposite personalities, become unlikely friends. As the women bond over bottles of wine and a shared affinity for "The Facts of Life," Judy tries to shield Jen from a shocking secret that could destroy her life as she knows it. The dark comedy -- which explores the weirdly funny sides of grief, loss and forgiveness -- features a cast that includes TV veterans Christina Applegate and Ed Asner.

name: Extras
title: 2005 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 2 seasons
description: Andy Millman, a struggling actor, constantly looks for his big break while working as an anonymous background performer in film and television.

name: Day Break
title: 2006 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Detective Brett Hopper is having a really bad day. He's been framed for murder and is on the run. He wakes up to relive this same day over and over again, till he can figure out why and how to fix it.

name: Z Nation
title: 2014 ‧ Horror ‧ 5 seasons
description: Three years after a virus decimated the vast majority of America's population, turning them into flesh-eating zombies, a brave group tries to transport a survivor to the last working virology lab.

name: Behind Her Eyes
title: 2021 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: A single mother enters a world of twisted mind games when she begins an affair with her psychiatrist boss while secretly befriending his mysterious wife.

name: Mindhunter
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Catching a criminal often requires the authorities to get inside the villain's mind to figure out how he thinks. That's the job of FBI agents Holden Ford and Bill Tench. They attempt to understand and catch serial killers by studying their damaged psyches. Along the way, the agents pioneer the development of modern serial-killer profiling. The crime drama has a strong pedigree behind the camera, with Oscar-nominated director David Fincher and Oscar-winning actress Charlize Theron among the show's executive producers.

name: The Sinner
title: 2017 ‧ Thriller ‧ 4 seasons
description: Detective Harry Ambrose investigates various atrocious murder cases and tries to analyse the reasons behind ordinary people committing heinous crimes.

name: Love, Victor
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: "Love, Victor" is set in the world of the groundbreaking movie, "Love, Simon," which was inspired by Becky Albertalli's acclaimed young adult novel, "Simon vs. the Homo Sapiens Agenda," about a closeted gay teenager who is forced to come out after being blackmailed. The series stars Michael Cimino as Victor, who, like Simon, is on his own journey of self-discovery. Facing challenges at home, navigating the ups and downs of a new high school and exploring his sexual orientation, Victor reaches out to Simon when things become too difficult.

name: Skam
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: A group of high school students in Oslo and their problems with bullying, love and student life.

name: Slumdog Millionaire
title: 2008 ‧ Romance/Crime ‧ 2 hours
description: A teenager from the slums of Mumbai becomes a contestant on the show 'Kaun Banega Crorepati?' When interrogated under suspicion of cheating, he revisits his past, revealing how he had all the answers.

name: Hotel Mumbai
title: 2018 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 2h 3m
description: As terrorists enter the Taj Mahal Palace hotel in Mumbai and start ruthlessly killing people, the staff risks everything to keep their guests safe while waiting for help to arrive.

name: Cinderella Man
title: 2005 ‧ Sport/Thriller ‧ 2h 24m
description: James Braddock, a successful American boxer forced out of the sport by an injury, goes through impoverishment during the Great Depression. But fate leads to his dramatic re-entry into the sport.

name: Mystic River
title: 2003 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 17m
description: Childhood friends Jimmy, Dave and Sean are reunited after Jimmy's daughter gets murdered and Sean is the police officer assigned to the case. However, Jimmy suspects Dave is behind the murder.

name: Gran Torino
title: 2008 ‧ Thriller/Western ‧ 1h 56m
description: When Walt Kowalski's neighbour, Thao, tries to steal his 1972 Gran Torino, he decides to help him reform. However, Walt gets involved in a feud with a local gang leader when he saves Thao from them.

name: Kal Ho Naa Ho
title: 2003 ‧ Romance/Musical ‧ 3h 6m
description: Naina, a girl living a dreary life, finds herself a new person when Aman walks into her life. Even though she loves him, Aman claims to be a married man and convinces Rohit, her friend, to woo her.

name: Swades
title: 2004 ‧ Musical/Drama ‧ 3h 9m
description: Mohan, an Indian expatriate employed with NASA, travels to his country to track down his beloved nanny, Kaveri. During his stay, he finds himself advocating for reform in a village.

name: Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri
title: 2017 ‧ Crime/Comedy ‧ 1h 55m
description: Mildred Hayes is devastated after the rape and murder of her daughter. Months later, she protests and challenges the police officials when they fail to capture the culprit.

name: Moonlight
title: 2016 ‧ Thriller/Romance ‧ 1h 51m
description: Chiron, a young African-American boy, finds guidance in Juan, a drug dealer, who teaches him to carve his own path. As he grows up in Miami, Juan's advice leaves a lasting impression on him.

name: Minari
title: 2020 ‧ Drama/Teen ‧ 1h 55m
description: Jacob Yi moves to Arkansas with his wife and children to grow Korean produce and sell it to vendors. However, he faces several challenges in his quest which also threaten to destroy his family.

name: Cast Away
title: 2000 ‧ Adventure/Action ‧ 2h 23m
description: Chuck Noland wakes up on a deserted island after his plane crash-lands into the Pacific. Now, he must harness every skill he knows to survive the mental and physical agony of living alone.

name: 12 Strong
title: 2018 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 11m
description: Captain Mitch Nelson leads an elite team on a mission to fight the Taliban in Afghanistan. As he uses the aid of a local warlord, the situation becomes more dangerous and morally complicated.

name: Zero Dark Thirty
title: 2012 ‧ Thriller/War ‧ 2h 37m
description: A CIA analyst and her team are on a mission to track an infamous terrorist leader responsible for the 11 September attacks in the USA. Over time, they carry out operations to tackle him and his gang.

name: American Sniper
title: 2014 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 12m
description: After serving in Iraq for years, Chris Kyle, a lethal US sniper, returns home to his wife and son. However, he cannot cope with the traumatic experiences of war, affecting his life and relationships.

name: Omkara
title: 2006 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 2h 35m
description: Langda dreams of becoming Omkara's successor after the latter wins the election. But when Omkara appoints Kesu as his lieutenant, Langda feels betrayed and plots revenge.

name: Dev.D
title: 2009 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 2h 24m
description: After breaking up with his childhood love Paro, Dev finds solace in drugs and alcohol. He soon bumps into Chanda, a prostitute, and falls for her.

name: Delhi Belly
title: 2011 ‧ Comedy/Action ‧ 1h 43m
description: Tashi, Nitin and Arup, three strugglers who are also roommates, unknowingly become the target of a powerful gangster when they misplace his expensive diamonds.

name: Ludo
title: 2020 ‧ Comedy/Thriller ‧ 2h 30m
description: Four seemingly different stories intertwine in a game of fate and chance that includes a scandalous sex tape, a suitcase full of money and unsettled scores.

name: Munna Bhai M.B.B.S.
title: 2003 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 36m
description: Munna Bhai, a gangster, decides to fulfil his father's dream by becoming a doctor. With a little help from his loyal sidekick Circuit, he enrols in a medical college and gets to work.

name: The Royal Tenenbaums
title: 2001 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 49m
description: The Tenenbaums are a talented family of former child prodigies. However, they are not on the best of terms. When their ailing father summons them all, they find themselves under one roof.

name: Meet Joe Black
title: 1998 ‧ Romance/Fantasy ‧ 3h 1m
description: Disguised as a human, Grim Reaper Joe Black comes to Earth to escort back the soul of media tycoon William Parrish. But Joe's fascinating journey ends with him falling in love with William's daughter.

name: Legends of the Fall
title: 1994 ‧ Western/Romance ‧ 2h 13m
description: Colonel Ludlow moves to the Rocky Mountains with his three sons. When his youngest son brings home his fiancee, the other two also fall in love with her and a bitter rivalry breaks out between them.

name: Django Unchained
title: 2012 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 45m
description: Django, an African slave, is freed by a German bounty hunter and becomes his apprentice. Together, they attempt to rescue his wife, who has been enslaved by a charming but cruel plantation owner.

name: Green Book
title: 2018 ‧ Comedy/Musical ‧ 2h 10m
description: Amidst rampant racism in the 1960s southern America, an African American pianist hires an Italian American bouncer to drive him through his venues. They come closer in the course of their journey.

name: Emancipation
title: 2022 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 12m
description: Peter, a slave, flees a plantation in Louisiana after he was whipped within an inch of his life. He has to outwit cold-blooded hunters and the unforgiving swamps of Louisiana on a torturous journey north.

name: The Irishman
title: 2019 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 3h 29m
description: In the 1950s, truck driver Frank Sheeran gets involved with Russell Bufalino and his Pennsylvania crime family. As Sheeran climbs the ranks to become a top hit man, he also goes to work for Jimmy Hoffa -- a powerful Teamster tied to organized crime.

name: Gangs of New York
title: 2002 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 47m
description: Amsterdam sets out to avenge the death of his father who was killed in a gang fight at the hands of a crime lord, Bill 'The Butcher'. Whilst doing so, he gets caught up in the Civil War.

name: Goodfellas
title: 1990 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 26m
description: Henry grows up idolising mobsters in his impoverished neighbourhood. Things take a turn for the worse when he along with his friends Jimmy and Tommy decide to make their way up the mob hierarchy.

name: The Usual Suspects
title: 1995 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 46m
description: A con man is interrogated by the police after surviving a deadly shoot-out. When questioned about the incident, he reveals a story about five criminals led by a notorious mastermind named Keyser Soze.

title: 2021 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 2h 45m
description: Cricketer Kapil Dev gets an opportunity to make his country famous on the world stage when he captains the Indian national cricket team at the 1983 Cricket World Cup.

name: Dangal
title: 2016 ‧ Sport/Action ‧ 2h 41m
description: Mahavir Singh Phogat, a former wrestler, decides to fulfil his dream of winning a gold medal for his country by training his daughters for the Commonwealth Games despite the existing social stigmas.

name: Karthik Calling Karthik
title: 2010 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2h 35m
description: Karthik, an introvert, is always ridiculed by his boss and has faced many setbacks throughout his life. However, one day, he receives a phone call from a stranger who promises to transform his life.

name: Rock On!!
title: 2008 ‧ Musical/Drama ‧ 2h 25m
description: Four musician friends fail to make it big as a band due to a misunderstanding. Years later, they reignite their dream by forgetting their woes and embark on a journey they had left incomplete.

name: Maqbool
title: 2003 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 12m
description: Maqbool, an underworld don's henchman, falls in love with his boss's mistress, Nimmi, who instigates him to kill the don and become the next leader.

name: Haider
title: 2014 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 2h 40m
description: Haider, a young man, returns to Jammu and Kashmir when the state is bedevilled by a violent insurgency. He seeks closure regarding his father's disappearance, but the state's politics overpower him.

name: No Country for Old Men
title: 2007 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 2m
description: A hunter's life takes a drastic turn when he discovers two million dollars while strolling through the aftermath of a drug deal. He is then pursued by a psychopathic killer who wants the money.

name: Lincoln
title: 2012 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 2h 30m
description: Abraham Lincoln uses his powers as the president of the United States of America as he strives to abolish slavery and reunite his country during the Civil War.

name: Carandiru
title: 2003 ‧ Crime/Documentary ‧ 2h 25m
description: Drauzio Varella, a doctor, is treating prisoners in an overpopulated prison in Brazil. While doing so, he learns about their stories including how they got there.

name: City of Men
title: 2007 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 46m
description: Acerola and Laranjinha grow up in a slum of Rio de Janeiro without their fathers. When they become adults, a drug war between two gangs and revelations about their fathers threaten their friendship.

name: Elite Squad
title: 2007 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 1h 55m
description: Captain Nascimento is assigned a task to be completed before the Pope arrives to Rio de Janeiro. But with the captain planning to quit his job himself, will he be able to find a suitable substitute?

name: Frozen
title: 2010 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 33m
description: Three snowboarders are stranded on a chairlift while riding up Mount Holliston. When the night lights suddenly go off, they either need to find their way down or freeze to death.

name: Cidade de Deus
title: 2002 ‧ Crime/War ‧ 2h 13m
description: Two boys are brought up in a sadistic neighbourhood of Rio de Janeiro. Later, they adopt diverse professional paths, with one of them becoming a photographer and the other boy becoming a drug dealer.

name: Last Stop 174
title: 2008 ‧ Thriller/Documentary ‧ 1h 50m
description: Sandro is a troubled young man with a torturous childhood. His life is copious with getting on the wrong side of the law and making poor choices, the amalgamation of which determines his fate.

name: The Man Who Copied
title: 2003 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 2h 3m
description: Nineteen-year-old Andre wants to make money to woo his neighbour Silvia. He begins counterfeiting notes, participates in a lottery and finally plans a bank heist with his friend.

name: Lamarca
title: 1994 ‧ Action/Drama
description: Lamarca : A brilliant biopic which retraces the adventurous life of Brazilian army captain Carlos Lamarca. In the late 1980s and early 1990s, Brazilian film industry had witnessed a complete decline. It was both related to quality and quantity of films which were made in Brazil.

name: Four Days in September (O QUE E ISSO, COMPANHEIRO?)
title: 1997 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 50m
description: Based on a true story, "Four Days in September" is a moving account of the kidnapping in September, 1969 of the American Ambassador to Brazil, played by Alan Arkin. The drama unfolds as a group of young and often naive idealists join together to plot and carry out an act of terrorism, their only means of giving voice to their progressive dreams and visions in a military regime.

name: Em Nome da Lei
title: 2016 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 55m
description: The journey of idealistic Vitor, a young federal judge who decides to dismantle the mafia that dominates the border between Brazil and Paraguay. Inspired by true events.

name: Once Upon a Time in Rio
title: 2008 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 57m
description: De, a poor young man, develops feelings for Nina, a rich girl, and begins to face difficulties as he progresses through the relationship.

name: Elite Squad: The Enemy Within
title: 2010 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 55m
description: Nascimento is called in to stop a prison riot started by Beirada, who is eventually killed. Now a high ranking officer, he finds himself in a conflict between the government and paramilitary groups.

name: The Man of the Year
title: 2003 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 1h 56m
description: Maiquel, an insecure ordinary man, dyes his hair blonde after losing a bet with his friends. This event suddenly transforms him into a totally different person.

name: A Dog's Will
title: 2000 ‧ Comedy/Adventure ‧ 1h 44m
