description: Joao Grilo, a pathological liar, and his friend Chico, a coward, are struggling to make a living, which is when they come up with a cunning plan to solve their problems.

name: The Punisher
title: 2004 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 20m
description: The family of Frank Castle, an FBI agent, is slaughtered by a corrupt businessman who has ties with the underworld. Determined to kill the man and rid the world of evil, he becomes a vigilante.

name: 2 Coelhos
title: 2012 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 48m
description: 2 Coelhos is a 2012 Brazilian action thriller film written and directed by Afonso Poyart. The film features innovations that were not common in Brazilian films, including explosions, animations, elaborate special effects and pop culture references. It was released in Brazil on January 20, 2012.

name: Pictures of Ghosts
title: 2023 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1h 33m
description: The classic movie palaces from the 20th century in Recife, Brazil, are mostly gone. The city area is a sort of archaeological site that reveals aspects of life in society which have been lost.

name: Central Station (CENTRAL DO BRASIL)
title: 1998 ‧ Thriller/Documentary ‧ 1h 55m
description: Dora, a school teacher, helps illiterate people pen letters they wish to send loved ones. When one of her clients dies, she helps her son find his father.

name: Godfather of Harlem
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: After serving 10 years in prison, Bumpy Johnson returns home to find his neighbourhood ruled by the Italian mafia. Soon, he forms an alliance with a radical preacher to regain control of the streets.

name: For Life
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: After being sentenced to lifelong incarceration for a crime he did not commit, Aaron Wallace learns the law and litigates cases for other inmates while seeking justice for himself.

name: Snowfall
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: During the budding drug epidemic in Los Angeles in the early 1980s, a crime family decides to make money selling cocaine. Meanwhile, a CIA operative also gets involved.

name: Top Boy
title: 2011 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: This drama takes viewers into the housing estates of east London. There is tension between the drug gangs that operate almost openly and those who strive to live honest lives against the odds in the crime-riddled area. That tension is explored through the interlocking stories of 20-something drug dealer Dushane, who is determined to become the area's Top Boy, and good-natured but vulnerable teenager Ra'Nell, who is forced to grow up quickly following his mother's breakdown and enforced absence. The programme combines elements of a tense gangster thriller with subtle social realism, some tenderness, innocence and wry humour.

name: Boardwalk Empire
title: 2010 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: Enoch Thompson, the treasurer of Atlantic City, is friends with gangsters and politicians alike, resulting in the federal government taking special interest in him.

name: Gangland
title: 2007 ‧ Documentary ‧ 7 seasons
description: An insider look at the stories of some of America's most notorious street gangs, supported by interviews and rarely seen footage.

name: Gangsters: America's Most Evil
title: 2012 ‧ Documentary ‧ 6 seasons
description: This series documents the life and crimes of some of the most wanted criminals in the USA.

name: BMF
title: 2021 ‧ 2 seasons
description: Detroit brothers Demetrius and Terry Flenory become powerful figures in a multi-state drug and money laundering organization.

name: Power Book II: Ghost
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Tariq St. Patrick, the teenage son of a drug lord, goes to great lengths to release his mother, who is accused of a crime he committed, from prison.

name: The Chi
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: The lives of the residents of a tough and dangerous neighbourhood in South Chicago intertwine as they have to deal with a murder in their area.

name: The Sopranos
title: 1999 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: Tony Soprano, an Italian-American mafia head based in New Jersey, struggles to manage his family and criminal life and confides his affairs to his psychiatrist Jennifer Melfi.

name: Deadwood
title: 2004 ‧ Western ‧ 3 seasons
description: People flee to Deadwood, South Dakota, with the dream of getting rich. However, not everyone can survive the chaos and confusion the town has to offer due to the lack of law facilities.

name: The Wire
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: In the city of Baltimore, Detective James McNulty and his team investigate crimes and try their best to solve the bridge that exists between the drug kingpins and the law enforcement agencies.

name: Power Book III: Raising Kanan
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: "Power Book III: Raising Kanan" goes back to 1991 when Supras are the whip of choice and a fly shearling coat is a symbol of status in the hood. Kanan navigates this world of glamour and grit as he comes into his own and gets out of the shadow of his mother, Raq, who runs the streets of Southside Jamaica, Queens, with her brothers, Marvin and Lou-Lou. Despite Kanan being under their watchful eyes, danger lurks just around the corner. There's Unique, a rival dealer who has his eye on the family's turf, and Detective Malcolm Howard, a pestering cop who gets a kick out of harassing community members and getting under Raq's skin.

name: Power Book IV: Force
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Tommy Egan leaves New York behind and plans to take on Chicago, using his outsider status to break all the local rules and rewrite them on his quest to become the biggest drug dealer in the city.

name: Gotti: Godfather and Son
title: 2018 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: The four-hour documentary tells the father and son story of two men who were raised in the mob and became the reigning king and heir apparent of the Gambino crime family. Writer/director Richard Stratton gains exclusive access to John Gotti Sr. and his son, John Gotti Jr., including never-before-seen segments from the last visit between a son and his terminally ill father at a federal prison. It was then that Gotti Jr. asks his dad for his blessing to quit what might have been the last of the major mafia dynasties. In addition to in-depth, emotional accounts provided by Gotti Jr., interviewees include Colombo family soldier Larry Mazza, former FBI agents Bruce Mouw, Louis Digregorio and Jim Abbott, and criminal defense lawyers Bruce Cutler and Ron Kuby.

name: The Godfather Saga
title: 1977 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A compilation of "The Godfather," 1972, and "The Godfather, Part II," '74, follows a crime boss and his heir.

name: Crime Story
title: 1986 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: In 1960s Chicago, Lt. Mike Torello and the members of his Major Crime Unit carry on a near-epic battle against organized crime figures such as Ray Luca.

name: Tulsa King
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: New York mafia capo Dwight "The General" Manfredi is released from prison after 25 years and exiled by his boss to set up shop in Tulsa, Okla.; realizing that his mob family may not have his best interests in mind, Dwight slowly builds a crew.

name: From
title: 2022 ‧ Horror ‧ 2 seasons
description: The residents of a small town struggle to find a way out when mysterious unknown forces keep them from leaving.

name: Your Honor
title: 2020 ‧ Thriller ‧ 2 seasons
description: Adam, the son of a judge, gets entangled in a hit-and-run case which involves a member of a mafia family. As a result, his father tries to cover up his crime, in order to protect him from the law.

name: The Gangster Chronicles
title: 1981 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A historically based drama about the lives of gangsters Bugsy Siegel, Lucky Luciano and Al Capone.

name: The Offer
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Oscar-winning producer Albert S Ruddy chronicles his experiences and struggles while making his cinematic masterpiece, 'The Godfather'.

name: The Last Don
title: 1997 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: The Last Don, also known as Mario Puzo's The Last Don, is a 1997 American crime drama television miniseries directed by Graeme Clifford and written by Joyce Eliason, based on the 1996 novel The Last Don by Mario Puzo. It aired on CBS in three parts, on May 11, 13 and 14, 1997.

name: Wu-Tang Clan: Of Mics And Men
title: 2019 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: Wu-Tang Clan became a household name in rap/hip-hop circles soon after releasing its seminal debut, "Enter the Wu-Tang (36 Chambers)," in 1993. To celebrate its 25th anniversary, a four-part docuseries from filmmaker Sasha Jenkins looks back on the group's career, combining reflective interviews from each of the nine living members with never-before-seen archival footage and performances. Founding members RZA, GZA, Ol' Dirty Bastard, Inspectah Deck, Raekwon the Chef, U-God, Ghostface Killah, Method Man, Masta Killa and Cappadonna used ingenuity and entrepreneurial spirit to overcome the poverty and violence of 1970s and '80s Staten Island and Brooklyn. But it was music and their shared lyrical prowess that allowed them to form perhaps the most recognizable musical movement in the world.

name: The Get Down
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Ezekiel and Mylene, two promising music artists live in the Bronx. They must face their fears and prove themselves if they want to succeed in the music business.

name: The Breaks
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: VH1's 2016 original movie "The Breaks" tells the story of three friends united by their love of hip-hop, who work to make names for themselves in the music industry. Following the film's success and fans' demands for more, a same-titled series adaptation picks up the narrative in New York City, circa 1990, to continue exploring the guys' joy and suffering during the height of rap's golden age of creativity. "The Breaks" is inspired by "The Big Payback," a 40-year history of the hip-hop business written by journalist Dan Charnas.

name: American Gangster
title: 2006 ‧ Documentary ‧ 3 seasons
description: Ving Rhames talks about the rise and fall of some of the most dangerous Afro-American criminals and also their impact on the communities.

name: The Death Row Chronicles
title: 2018 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: Hip-hop's peak years are generally considered to encompass the 1990s, a rise that coincided with Death Row Records becoming one of the most notorious labels in the genre's history. This docuseries presents a warts-and-all history of Death Row, which was built by CEO Suge Knight into a multimillion-dollar company thanks to a legendary talent roster led by Dr. Dre, Tupac Shakur and Snoop Dogg. Series highlights include never-before-seen footage, a firsthand interview with someone who witnessed Shakur's murder in 1996, and comments from former Death Row artists and other key players in the label's rise and downfall.

name: Insecure
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: Best friends Issa and Molly belong to the same social background and face similar experiences. They always strive to find solutions to their problems by facing them together.

name: Power
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: James St Patrick, the owner of a nightclub, is wealthy and has everything he needs. However, he is also a drug lord but wishes to quit the life of crime.

name: The Shield
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: Vik Mackey and his three aides, Shane, Curtis and Ronnie, working for the Strike Team, use illegal methods to maintain law and order, whilst engaging in a series of undercover dealings secretly.

name: The White Lotus
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Dark secrets and twisted truths of the guests, the staff and the locale of a resort are unveiled over the course of a week that was supposed to be a relaxing vacation.

name: Blue Bloods
title: 2010 ‧ Drama ‧ 14 seasons
description: Frank, the police commissioner of New York, has two children, one in the police force and the other, is a lawyer. However, things don't go his way as he deals with problems both at work and at home.

name: Billions
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: Chuck Rhoades, a sincere but ruthless US attorney, engages in an egoistic battle with hedge fund kingpin Bobby 'Axe' Axelrod as they try to outdo each other in the competitive financial market.

name: Barry
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Barry, who kills to earn a living, discovers the joy of acting while he is looking for his target. Surprisingly, he loves it so much that he is ready to leave his old life behind.

name: Veep
title: 2012 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 7 seasons
description: Former Senator Selina Meyer gets an opportunity to serve as the Vice President of the United States. She tries to prevent various political uproars while juggling her public as well as private life.

name: Breaking Bad
title: 2008 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: Walter White, a chemistry teacher, discovers that he has cancer and decides to get into the meth-making business to repay his medical debts. His priorities begin to change when he partners with Jesse.

name: Ozark
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Created by Bill Dubuque ("The Accountant," "The Judge"), this drama series stars Jason Bateman as Marty Byrde, a financial planner who relocates his family from Chicago to a summer resort community in the Ozarks. With wife Wendy and their two kids in tow, Marty is on the move after a money-laundering scheme goes wrong, forcing him to pay off a substantial debt to a Mexican drug lord in order to keep his family safe. While the Byrdes' fate hangs in the balance, the dire circumstances force the fractured family to reconnect.

name: 30 Rock
title: 2006 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 7 seasons
description: Liz Lemon, head writer of a sketch comedy show, has to deal with her arrogant boss and eccentric stars. Regardless, she must run the TV show successfully without losing her mind.

name: Seinfeld
title: 1989 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 9 seasons
description: Stand-up comedian Jerry Seinfeld wrestles with life's most perplexing yet trivial questions with his eccentric friends George, Elaine and Kramer.

name: Succession
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: The Roy family controls Waystar RoyCo, a powerful global media and entertainment conglomerate. However, the unexpected retirement of the company's patriarch ignites a power struggle.

name: Justified
title: 2010 ‧ Western ‧ 6 seasons
description: Enforcing his own brand of justice, US Marshal Raylan, a strong-willed, quiet law-man haunted by his past, returns to his native town to see that justice is served to those in need.

name: Mayans M.C.
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: Ezekiel Reyes is a former convict who returns to his hometown with a new outlook on life. He becomes a gangster and falls deeper into the world of crime.

name: Godless
title: 2017 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: Notorious criminal Frank Griffin and his gang of outlaws are on a mission -- get revenge on Roy Goode, a former protege who betrayed the brotherhood. On the run, Roy seeks refuge in isolated mining town La Belle, N.M., where he lives with Alice Fletcher, a hardened widower and outcast. When word reaches La Belle, which is governed mainly by women, that Griffin is headed there, the residents of the town band together to defend against his murderous gang.

name: Gangs of London
title: 2020 ‧ Action ‧ 2 seasons
description: The city of London is being torn apart by the turbulent power struggles of the international gangs that control it, as well as the sudden power vacuum that's created when the head of London's most powerful crime family is assassinated.

name: Gangland Undercover
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Charles Falco, an ex-confidential informant of a US law enforcement unit, infiltrates Vagos, a notorious motorcycle gang, as an undercover agent. He faces obstacles galore over three years with Vagos.

name: Better Call Saul
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: Ex-con artist Jimmy McGill turns into a small-time attorney and goes through a series of trials and tragedies, as he transforms into his alter ego Saul Goodman, a morally challenged criminal lawyer.

name: Narcos
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: A DEA agent is sent to Colombia to capture the Colombian kingpin of cocaine, Pablo Escobar. Pablo rises above and beyond all institutions of power as the bloody conflict ensues.

name: True Detective
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Police officers and detectives around the USA are forced to face dark secrets about themselves and the people around them while investigating homicides.

name: Mare of Easttown
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A detective from Pennsylvania tries her best to prevent her life from falling apart while investigating a mysterious murder.

name: Norsemen
title: 2016 ‧ Comedy ‧ 3 seasons
description: The residents of an 8th-century Viking village experience political rivalry, social change and innovations that upend their culture and way of life.

name: Manhunt
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Security officer Richard Jewell thwarts a deadly explosion at the 1996 Atlanta Olympics. However, he soon finds himself in the middle of a gruelling investigation by the FBI.

name: The Alienist
title: 2018 ‧ Thriller ‧ 2 seasons
description: The best-selling book by Caleb Carr is the basis for "The Alienist," a psychological thriller set amidst the vast wealth, extreme poverty and technological innovation of 1896 New York. A never-before-seen ritualistic killer is responsible for the gruesome murders of boy prostitutes, and newly appointed police commissioner Theodore Roosevelt calls upon criminal psychologist Dr. Laszlo Kreizler, newspaper illustrator John Moore and police department secretary Sara Howard to conduct the investigation in secret. The brilliant, obsessive Kreizler is known as an alienist -- one who studies mental pathologies and the deviant behaviors of those who are alienated from themselves and society. His job, along with his controversial views, makes him a social pariah in some circles. But helped by a band of outsiders, Kreizler's tireless efforts eventually answer the question behind what makes a man into a murderer.

name: Narcos: Mexico
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: DEA agent Kiki Camarena is transferred to Guadalajara to take up a new post. However, he soon realises that his assignment will be difficult due to a dangerous drug cartel.

name: El Chapo
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Joaquin, widely known as El Chapo, joins the Guadalajara Cartel and climbs the ladder of power to establish the largest network of drug trafficking.

name: John Wick: Chapter 2
title: 2017 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 2m
description: John Wick, a retired hitman, visits Italy to pay off an inescapable blood debt. However, he soon finds himself cornered by every killer in the business due to an enormous bounty on his head.

name: John Wick: Chapter 4
title: 2023 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 49m
description: With the price on his head ever increasing, legendary hit man John Wick takes his fight against the High Table global as he seeks out the most powerful players in the underworld, from New York to Paris to Japan to Berlin.

name: John Wick
title: 2014 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 41m
description: John Wick, a retired hitman, is forced to return to his old ways after a group of Russian gangsters steal his car and kill a puppy gifted to him by his late wife.

name: John Wick: Chapter 3 Parabellum
title: 2019 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 11m
description: John Wick is declared excommunicado and a hefty bounty is set on him after he murders an international crime lord. He sets out to seek help to save himself from ruthless hitmen and bounty hunters.

name: Prison Break
title: 2005 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: An engineer installs himself in a prison he helped design, in order to save his falsely accused brother from a death sentence.

name: Prison Break: The Final Break
title: 2009 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 29m
description: A man (Wentworth Miller) hatches a plan to rescue his pregnant girlfriend (Sarah Wayne Callies) from a women's prison.

name: Flesh and Bone
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Claire Robbins joins the American Ballet Company in a bid to rise higher in the ranks of ballet dancers. Paul Grayson, the director of the academy, sees Claire as the saving grace for his company.

name: The 100
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: A nuclear conflict has decimated civilisation. A century later, a spaceship accommodating humanity's lone survivors dispatch 100 juvenile delinquents back to the Earth to determine its habitability.

name: Dexter
title: 2006 ‧ Drama ‧ 8 seasons
description: Dexter Morgan, a man with homicidal tendencies, lives a double life. He works as a forensic technician for the police department during the day and kills heinous perpetrators in his free time.

name: Daredevil
title: 2015 ‧ Action ‧ 3 seasons
description: Matt Murdock manages to overcome the challenges that he faces due to him being blind since childhood and fights criminals as a lawyer and Daredevil.

name: Dexter: New Blood
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Dexter, a serial killer, assumes a fake identity and lives a quiet life in New York. However, a series of events makes him fear the revival of his homicidal tendencies.

name: The Blacklist
title: 2013 ‧ Thriller ‧ 10 seasons
description: Raymond Reddington is a notorious criminal who is wanted by law enforcements agents. He agrees to help the police catch other criminals on the condition he gets to work with a new agent, Elizabeth.

name: Quantico
title: 2015 ‧ Thriller ‧ 3 seasons
description: A group of young FBI recruits travel to the Quantico base in Virginia to receive training to become special agents. Unfortunately, some of them possess secrets unknown to others.

name: Black Bird
title: 2022 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: As Jimmy Keene begins a 10-year prison sentence, he gets a offer; if he can elicit a confession from suspected killer Larry Hall, he will be freed; completing this mission becomes the challenge of a lifetime.

name: Designated Survivor
title: 2016 ‧ Thriller ‧ 3 seasons
description: When a mysterious attack kills the president and wipes out everybody in the line of succession, Thomas Kirkman, a lowly cabinet minister, is forced to rise to the occasion as the designated survivor.

name: 24: Live Another Day
title: 2014 ‧ Action ‧ 1 season
description: Jack Bauer escapes police custody after the president signs the peace treaty. Later, he is on a mission to stop a massive terrorist attack in London.

name: Tom Clancy's Jack Ryan
title: 2018 ‧ Thriller ‧ 4 seasons
description: Author Tom Clancy introduced the character of Jack Ryan in a series of books before Ryan headed to the big screen in several films. Now the former U.S. Marine is featured in an episodic series for the first time, with John Krasinski portraying Ryan in this Amazon original thriller that centers on Ryan as an up-and-coming CIA analyst. He is thrust into a dangerous field assignment for the first time and uncovers a pattern in terrorist communication. That launches him into the middle of a dangerous gambit with a new breed of terrorism that threatens destruction on a global scale.

name: Empire
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: A tycoon in the music industry plans to secure the future of his company by pitting his sons against each other. Meanwhile, his ex-wife plots to reclaim her share of the business.

name: The New Edition Story
title: 2017 film
description: A three-part miniseries, "The New Edition Story" follows the R&B/pop group from their humble beginnings as kids in Boston to global mega-stardom -- weathering the highs and lows of controversy, personnel changes, and the ultimate cost of fame. In 1978, 11-year-old Bobby Brown convinces friends Ricky Bell, Mike Bivins and Ralph Tresvant to perform in local talent shows. The boys are discovered soon after, sign a record deal, and produce their first No. 1 hit, "Candy Girl." Years later, tension within the group forces dramatic changes -- Bobby Brown is kicked out -- and New Edition is never the same.

name: Our Kind of People
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: "Our Kind of People" takes place in the aspirational world of Oak Bluffs on Martha's Vineyard, a historical stronghold where the rich and powerful Black elite have come to play for over 50 years. Strong-willed single mom Angela Vaughn sets out to reclaim her family's name and make an impact with her revolutionary hair care line that highlights the innate, natural beauty of Black women, but she soon discovers a dark secret about her own mother's past that will turn her world upside-down and shake up this community forever. The show is a soapy, thrilling exploration of race and class in America and an unapologetic celebration of Black resilience and achievement.

name: CrazySexyCool: The TLC Story
title: 2013 ‧ Musical/Drama
description: Following the story of TLC's humble beginnings in Atlanta, Ga., and the unprecedented rise to fame in the 1990s as one of the world's highest-selling female groups of all time.

name: Dave
title: 2020 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: Dave, a neurotic man, strongly believes that he is destined to be the next great rapper of the country. In order to realise his aspiration, he requests his friends to help him prepare.

name: Wu-Tang: An American Saga
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: In the early 1990s, a group of black men evolve from being torn between their musical aspirations and the drug trade to becoming one of the most prominent hip-hop musicians.

name: Atlanta
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Earn works as a manager for his cousin Alfred, an upcoming rapper, and they try to make a name for themselves in the music industry. Earn struggles with providing for his child and lover.

name: All the Queen's Men
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Marilyn "Madam" DeVille is a fierce businesswoman at the top of her game in the nightclub industry and surrounded by a band of trusted employees who want her to succeed, but she soon discovers that more money and more power means more problems.

name: All American
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: Spencer James is a rising football player who makes the shift to an affluent Beverly Hills school on his coach's advice. He struggles to find his footing as the new team is threatened by his arrival.

name: Games People Play
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Based on the book "Games Divas Play" by Angela Burt-Murray, this stylized drama series centers around a world of money, sex and glamour in Los Angeles. The ensemble cast of characters includes a desperate basketball wife trying to protect her family, a tenacious journalist struggling to rebuild a tarnished career, and a scandalous groupie looking to become a star, who all find it is murder trying to stay on top.

name: The Quad
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Dr Eva Fletcher must try and turn around a bankrupt university of which she is the president. Also, she must save her crumbling marriage and deal with her rebellious daughter.

name: Ambitions
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Created by Jamey Giddens and produced by Will Packer, "Ambitions" is a multigenerational family saga that explores love, power and politics in Atlanta. It centers around lawyer Stephanie Carlisle, the wife of Atlanta Mayor Evan Lancaster, and her rivalry with Amara Hughes, a prosecutor in the U.S. Attorney's Office who has just arrived in Atlanta with her husband, Titus. Stephanie and Amara used to be best friends who find themselves combatants in both their personal and professional lives. Stephanie's ambitious husband, Evan Lancaster, dreams of being Georgia's first African-American governor and will do anything to get there. Amara's husband, Titus, is the in-house counsel for a big pharmaceutical company fighting a class-action suit brought by Stephanie's powerful family.

name: Greenleaf
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: The Greenleaf family, which runs sprawling Memphis megachurch Calvary Fellowship World Ministries, appears to be a loving and caring clan. Beneath the surface, though, exists scandalous secrets and lies. Greed, adultery and sibling rivalry are among the issues that threaten to test the family's faith and tear the group apart. The scandalous happenings are uncovered by Grace, the estranged daughter of church leader Bishop James Greenleaf, when she returns home after a 20-year absence. Oprah Winfrey has a regular role on the show as Mavis, Grace's aunt.

name: Zatima
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Zac and Fatima navigate the ups and downs of their relationship.

name: Tyler Perry's Ruthless
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Ruth Truesdale becomes entangled in a scandalous cult of powerful sex crazed fanatics, with whom she must play along until she can find a way to free herself and her young daughter.

name: Kingdom Business
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: A behind-the-scenes look at the gospel music industry as seen through the lens of a drama unfolding around gospel queen Denita Jordan who is being challenged by an upstart young singer with a checkered past.

name: For Better or Worse
title: 2011 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 6 seasons
description: Follow the lives of a married couple, Marcus and Angela, as they go about their lives and face challenges life throws at them.

name: Sistas
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: Written, directed and executive produced by Tyler Perry, "Sistas" follows a group of single black women as they navigate the ups and downs of modern life, which includes careers, friendships, romances, and even social media. The comedy-drama series features Andi Barnes, an ambitious divorce lawyer, Danni King, a funny and fearless airport employee, Karen Mott, a street-smart hair salon owner, and Sabrina Hollins, a smart and stylish bank teller. The TV show takes viewers on a roller coaster ride of emotions and moments that epitomize "squad goals."

name: Midnight Mass
title: 2021 ‧ Horror ‧ 1 season
description: The arrival of a charismatic priest brings miracles, mysteries and renewed religious fervour to a dying town.

name: The Haunting of Bly Manor
title: 2020 ‧ Horror ‧ 1 season
description: A young governess arrives at Bly Manor and begins to see apparitions haunting the estate.

name: The Haunting of Hill House
title: 2018 ‧ Horror ‧ 1 season
description: This modern reimagining of the Shirley Jackson novel follows siblings who, as children, grew up in what would go on to become the most famous haunted house in the country.. Now adults, they are forced back together in the face of tragedy and must finally confront the ghosts of their past. Some of those ghosts still lurk in their minds, while others may actually be stalking the shadows of Hill House. The ensemble cast includes Oscar winner Timothy Hutton, Carla Gugino and Henry Thomas. Mike Flanagan, a veteran of the horror genre, created the series.

name: The Fall of the House of Usher
title: 2023 ‧ Horror ‧ 1 season
description: Siblings Roderick and Madeline Usher have built a pharmaceutical company into an empire of wealth, privilege and power; however, secrets come to light when the heirs to the Usher dynasty start dying.

name: Scream
title: 2015 ‧ Horror ‧ 3 seasons
description: MTV teams with super-producers Bob and Harvey Weinstein on a TV series adaptation of the hit horror film franchise. Instigated by a cyberbullying incident that goes viral, a brutal murder in Lakewood stirs memories of a crime spree from the town's past that has haunted some, intrigued others and maybe just spawned a new executioner. At the center of the story is a group of teenagers -- with two old friends struggling to reconnect at its heart -- who, says the network, "become lovers, enemies, suspects, targets and victims of a killer who's out for blood."

name: Marcella
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Despite leaving the Metropolitan Police Department due to her marital issues, Detective Marcella returns to her job and investigates a series of murders to track down the killer.

name: Locke & Key
title: 2020 ‧ Horror ‧ 3 seasons
description: Following their father's murder, three siblings move into a house filled with reality-bending keys; from the comics by Joe Hill and Gabriel Rodriguez.

name: You Don't Know Me
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A young man from South London is in the dock for murder. The evidence against him is overwhelming, but rather than let one of the barristers decide what's in his best interest, he chooses to exercise his right to tell his own story, in his own words. His story is extraordinary, it's about the woman he loves, who got herself into dangerous trouble. It's about how he risked everything to save her. He swears he's innocent, but in the end, the only thing that matters, is if you believe his story or not.

name: Lockwood & Co.
title: 2023 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: A girl with psychic abilities joins two teen boys a the ghost-hunting agency Lockwood & Co. to fight the deadly spirits plaguing London, doing their best to save the day without any adult supervision.

name: Knokke Off
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Twenty-somethings Louise Basteyns and Alexandre Vandael both come from a wealthy family. Together with their group of friends, they experience a carefree summer in luxurious Knokke. Despite all the partying, they feel pressure from their parents.

name: Made in Italy
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: An exploration of the birth of the Italian fashion industry during the 1970s through the story of Irene Mastrangelo, who gets a job at fashion magazine, Appeal.

name: Murders at BarLume
title: 2013 ‧ Drama ‧ 8 seasons
description: Massimo, the recently-divorced owner of the local watering hole, Barlume loves puzzles of all kinds, and his sharp mind comes in handy as he frequently finds himself moonlighting as an amateur detective.

name: Bang Bang Baby
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: In 1980s Milan, a shy and insecure teenager becomes the youngest member of a criminal organization in order to win the love of her father.

name: Call My Agent: Italy
title: 2023 ‧ Comedy drama ‧ 1 season
description: Call My Agent - Italia is an Italian comedy-drama television series that premiered on Sky Atlantic on 20 January 2023. The series depicts talent agents at the fictional agency CMA and their relationships with their clients, who are real Italian celebrities playing themselves.

name: The Great Battle
title: 2018 ‧ Action/War ‧ 2h 15m
description: In the late 7th-century, Yang Man-chun and his Goguryeo troops fight to protect Ansi Fortress from siege by soldiers of the Tang empire in an epic battle that spans 88 days.

name: Marie Antoinette
title: 2006 ‧ Drama/History ‧ 2h 3m
description: Maria Antonia, an Austrian princess, marries a French royal in 1770 to become Queen Marie Antoinette. However, what is supposed to be a charmed life takes a turn due to family drama and revolution.

name: Braveheart
title: 1995 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 58m
description: William Wallace, a Scottish rebel, along with his clan, sets out to battle King Edward I of England, who killed his bride a day after their marriage.

name: The Hollow Crown: Henry V
title: 2012 ‧ Drama ‧ 2h 19m
description: The fourth film in the series revolves around the newly crowned King of England, who transforms from an immoral youth to a purposeful monarch and relentlessly pursues his claim over Normandy.

name: The Tragedy of Macbeth
title: 2021 ‧ Thriller/Thriller ‧ 1h 45m
description: A Scottish lord becomes convinced by a trio of witches that he will become the next King of Scotland. His ambitious wife will do anything to support him in his plans of seizing power.

name: The Guernsey Literary and Potato Peel Pie Society
title: 2018 ‧ Romance/War ‧ 2h 4m
description: After the Second World War, Juliet Ashton, a writer, decides to write a book about the residents of Guernsey Island. However, Juliet's life changes completely after she visits that island.

name: Richard III: The King in the Car Park
title: 2013 ‧ Documentary
description: This documentary looks at the search for the remains of King Richard III of England (1452-1485). After being killed in the Battle of Bosworth Field (August 22, 1485), his remains were taken to Leicester and it was believed that he was buried at Greyfriars Church. The church no longer exists and its remains were now believed to be under a car park. Phillipa Langley of the Richard III Society convinced archaeologists at the University of Leicester to lead a dig and surprisingly, as it turned out, the first skeleton they found was subsequently proven to be that of the King through DNA tests which showed a match to Canadian Michael Ibsen, a direct descendant of Richard III's sister.

name: Kingdom of War: Part 1
title: 2007 ‧ War/Drama
description: The early years of King Naresuan, who spends his childhood as a hostage in Burma.

name: Troy
title: 2004 ‧ War/Adventure ‧ 2h 43m
description: Paris, the prince of Troy, convinces the beautiful Helen to leave her husband, King Menelaus, and come with him. But this enrages the king, and he declares war on Troy along with all his allies.

name: Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves
title: 1991 ‧ Adventure/Action ‧ 2h 23m
description: Robin Hood, an English nobleman, sets out with a group of exiled villagers to seek revenge against the sheriff of Nottingham, who is responsible for his father's death.

title: 2019 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 59m
description: Two soldiers, assigned the task of delivering a critical message to another battalion, risk their lives for the job in order to prevent them from stepping right into a deadly ambush.

name: Dunkirk
title: 2017 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 46m
description: During World War II, soldiers from the British Empire, Belgium and France try to evacuate from the town of Dunkirk during a arduous battle with German forces.

name: The Forgotten Battle
title: 2020 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 7m
description: In WWII's final years, a soldier in the German army, a British glider pilot, and a Dutch resistance fighter's paths intertwine. Their choices shape destinies, impacting not only their freedom but also that of others.

name: The Lighthouse
title: 2019 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 50m
description: In a remote island, Ephraim Winslow arrives as a lighthouse keeper and assists his elderly supervisor, Thomas Wake. As days pass, Winslow is haunted by strange and mysterious visions.

name: Richard III
title: 2016 ‧ Drama/History ‧ 2h 10m
description: "Richard III" is third episode of the second series of the British television series The Hollow Crown, based on the play of the same name by William Shakespeare. It was directed by Dominic Cooke, who also adapted the screenplay with Ben Power.

name: Cromwell
title: 1970 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 25m
description: Unable to tolerate King Charles's rigid and unreasonable polices, Oliver decides to take matters into his own hands. He leads a civil war to establish a parliament and plots to become the new ruler.

name: Munich – The Edge of War
title: 2021 ‧ Thriller/War ‧ 2h 3m
description: Set in the fall of 1938, Hitler prepares to invade Czechoslovakia, and the government of Neville Chamberlain desperately seeks a peaceful solution. A British civil servant and a German diplomat, former classmates, travel to Munich to discuss peace.

name: Hell House LLC
title: 2015 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 23m
description: Five years after fifteen people were killed during a haunted house tour, a documentary crew visits the scene to investigate what really happened.

name: Gonjiam: Haunted Asylum
title: 2018 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 34m
description: A crew of an online horror show decides to go to an asylum and stream from the inside to gain more viewers. Things take an unexpected turn when they begin to experience more than they imagined.

name: The Marsh
title: 2006 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 32m
description: Claire Holloway is both young and beautiful. She's a children's writer who keeps having nightmares of Rose Mash Farm. To save her life she must unravel what took place on the farm twenty years ago.

name: Noroi: The Curse
title: 2005 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 55m
description: A prominent paranormal journalist named Kobayashi goes missing shortly after completing a documentary. What begins as an investigation into strange noises soon evolves into the chilling mystery of a demonic entity named Kagutaba.

name: Grave Encounters
title: 2011 ‧ Horror/Suspense ‧ 1h 35m
description: In a bid to increase the ratings of their reality show, a production team locks itself in a psychiatric hospital that is allegedly haunted to find proof of paranormal activity.

name: The Autopsy of Jane Doe
title: 2016 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 26m
description: Two coroners start an autopsy of an unidentified girl to investigate the cause of her death. However, as they get closer to finding answers, bizarre events take place.

name: V/H/S/2
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 36m
description: A terrifying anthology of five stories comprising a college student's disappearance, an ocular implant, zombies, an Indonesian cult and an alien abduction.

name: Insidious: Chapter 2
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 46m
description: Josh Lambert and his family relocate to his mother's old house in the hopes of recovering from past trauma. However, they soon encounter strange and chilling paranormal events.

name: Insidious
title: 2010 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 43m
description: Josh and Renai move to a new house, seeking a fresh start. However, when their son, Dalton, mysteriously falls into a coma, paranormal events start occurring in the house.

name: The Conjuring
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 52m
description: Rod and Carolyn find their pet dog dead under mysterious circumstances and experience a spirit that harms their daughter Andrea. They finally call investigators who can help them get out of the mess.

name: Annabelle: Creation
title: 2017 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 49m
description: A doll-maker and his wife embed the spirit of their deceased daughter inside a doll. Years later, a nun and several girls from a shuttered orphanage become victims of the possessed doll, Anabelle.

name: Ginger Snaps
title: 2000 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 48m
description: Brigitte and Ginger are blood sisters who share a common passion for death. They find themselves in a difficult situation when Brigitte discovers Ginger undergoing changes after being bitten by a dog.

name: Ginger Snaps Back: The Beginning
title: 2004 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 34m
description: In early 19th-century Canada, orphaned sisters Ginger (Katharine Isabelle) and Brigitte (Emily Perkins) find themselves lost in a forest while riding on horseback. They're rescued by The Hunter (Nathaniel Arcand), a mysterious Native American who takes them back to Fort Bailey. Something strange has happened there, however. The few settlers who remain are suspicious of outsiders and keep tight-lipped about the situation, but Ginger soon discovers their secret for herself.

name: Underworld
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 2h 13m
description: Selene, a vampire orphaned due to a deadly werewolf attack, works for a vampire clan as a trained murderer. She must fight to save Michael, a skilled human doctor, from the machinations of werewolves.

name: Wrong Turn
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 25m
description: Chris and a group of five friends are left stranded deep in the middle of the woods after their cars collide. As they venture deeper into the woods, they face an uncertain and bloodcurdling fate.

name: The Craft
title: 1996 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 41m
description: A new student befriends three teenage girls from her high school who practise witchcraft against those who irk them. However, the consequences of joining the coven turn out to be disastrous.

name: Valerie and Her Week of Wonders
title: 1970 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 17m
description: Valerie, a thirteen-year-old girl, lives with her grandmother after the death of her parents. She is harassed by a monster who stole the earrings given to her by her mother.

name: Audition
title: 1999 ‧ Horror/Romance ‧ 1h 55m
description: A film producer, who is also a widower, auditions potential candidates to become his wife. He is interested in a ballerina but he later finds very disturbing incidents related to her.

name: The Love Witch
title: 2016 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 2 hours
description: Elaine (Samantha Robinson), a beautiful young witch, is determined to find a man to love her. In her gothic Victorian apartment she makes spells and potions, then picks up men and seduces them. However, her spells work too well, and she ends up with a string of hapless victims. When she at last meets the man of her dreams, her desperation to be loved drives her to the brink of insanity and murder.

name: Happy Death Day
title: 2017 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 36m
description: College student Theresa Gelbman continues to relive the day when she was killed to discover the identity of her murderer.

name: An American Werewolf in London
title: 1981 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 37m
description: A huge wolf assaults Jack and David in Britain, leading to Jack's death. As David recovers in a hospital, he is tormented by nightmares of a mangled Jack warning him that he is becoming a werewolf.

name: The Company of Wolves
title: 1984 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 35m
description: Young Rosaleen dreams that she lives in a forest with her family. When her sister is killed by wolves, she is sent to live with her grandmother while the villagers hunt the forest for the pack.

name: Bad Moon
title: 1996 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 20m
description: During a trip to Nepal, Ted, a photojournalist, gets bitten by a werewolf. Upon his arrival back home, Thor, the family dog, senses his affliction and it is up to him to save the day.

name: Cheerleader Massacre
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 25m
description: Pep-squad gals have little to cheer about when they become stranded in a psychotic killer's stomping ground.

name: Urban Legend
title: 1998 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 39m
description: When a series of murders take place in and around her university, Natalie begins to suspect that the deaths are inspired by various urban legends.

name: Drop Dead Gorgeous
title: 1999 ‧ Comedy/Thriller ‧ 1h 37m
description: An annual beauty pageant in small-town Minnesota turns ridiculously competitive and ultimately chaotic in this biting comedy. Amber Atkins (Kirsten Dunst), the daughter of hard-drinking mom Annette (Ellen Barkin), and Becky Leeman (Denise Richards), who is motivated by her former beauty-queen mother, Gladys (Kirstie Alley), are among the top contenders in the event. As Amber, Becky, and other local girls prepare for the big day, bizarre incidents occur, leading up to an ending with a bang.

name: Cruel Intentions
title: 1999 ‧ Romance/Thriller ‧ 1h 37m
description: Sebastian tries to seduce Annette, his headmaster's virgin daughter, to win a bet with his step-sister Kathryn. She wants his costly car while he wants a night with her. But Annette has other plans.

name: Idle Hands
title: 1999 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 32m
description: A teenaged slacker finds his parents turned into headless Halloween decorations and realises that his right hand has a blood-thirsty mind of its own that wreaks havoc.

name: An American Werewolf in Paris
title: 1997 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 45m
description: Andy, a tourist, falls in love with Serafine after rescuing her from a potentially fatal fall off the Eiffel Tower. However, he soon learns about her family background and their supernatural powers.

name: The Faculty
title: 1998 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 44m
description: When Casey Connor, Herrington High School's newspaper photographer, witnesses the murder of a nurse and sees her alive again, she decides to investigate the bizarre happenings.

name: Interview with the Vampire
title: 1994 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 2h 3m
description: Louis loses his will to live after his wife dies along with their child during labour. Lestat de Lioncourt, a vampire, takes a liking to Louise and turns him into a creature of the night.

name: Battle Royale
title: 2000 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 2h 2m
description: A group of ninth grade students have to fight a battle on a deserted island with meagre amenities. Some students decide to fight it off while others look for a way to escape from the island.

name: Sleepaway Camp II: Unhappy Campers
title: 1988 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 20m
description: Angela Baker (Pamela Springsteen), a psychotic transsexual, escapes from a mental hospital and surfaces at a summer camp as a counselor who lectures her teenage charges on proper moral behavior. Those teens who break her strict rules -- from the camp chatterbox or a sex-obsessed girl to the boys who are peeping Toms -- are murdered by the impostor in various gruesome ways. As more campers go missing, intrepid counselor Molly (Renee Estevez) begins to piece together the truth.

name: Sleepaway Camp III: Teenage Wasteland
title: 1989 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 24m
description: Psychotic Angela (Pamela Springsteen) is itching to do what she does best: slaughter dozens of teenage campers. As luck would have it, the previous site of her murders has been renamed and converted into an experimental summer camp meant to bring together privileged and lower-class teens. On the day the youths are boarding the buses to camp, Angela runs over a potential camper with a garbage truck and assumes her identity. Once she has infiltrated the camp, the real terror begins.

name: The Burning
title: 1981 ‧ Horror/Slasher ‧ 1h 31m
description: At summer camp, some teenagers pull a prank on the camp's caretaker, Cropsy (Lou David). But the joke goes terribly wrong, and the teens leave Cropsy for dead after setting him on fire. But no one keeps Cropsy down. A few years later, the burned and disfigured caretaker returns to camp equipped with his trusty shears, ready to unleash his particular brand of vengeance on a whole new group of teens. The murderous Cropsy stalks the campers in the woods, one by one.

name: Rushmore
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy/Indie film ‧ 1h 33m
description: Max, a student at Rushmore Academy, excels at everything except academics. He meets and falls in love with a teacher, Ms Cross, but later discovers that his mentor is also in love with her.

name: Welcome to the Dollhouse
title: 1995 ‧ Comedy/Indie film ‧ 1h 28m
description: Middle-school student Dawn Weiner (Heather Matarazzo) faces degradation at school -- where she is teased constantly -- and at home. The middle child between nerdy older brother Mark (Matthew Faber) and perky younger sister Missy (Daria Kalinina), Dawn can't seem to find a place to belong. Although she has a crush on a cute boy (Eric Mabius) whom her brother knows, she can only catch the attention of bully Brandon (Brendan Sexton Jr.), who threatens her to show affection.

name: The Virgin Suicides
title: 1999 ‧ Romance/Thriller ‧ 1h 37m
description: The story revolves around a group of guys who become obsessed with the girls of a conservative family.

name: The Doom Generation
title: 1995 ‧ Comedy/Thriller ‧ 1h 25m
description: Teens Jordan White (James Duval) and Amy Blue (Rose McGowan) pick up a handsome drifter named Xavier Red (Johnathon Schaech). Red tends to create combustible situations -- for example, a trip to a convenience store leads to a clerk getting decapitated. Afterward, the trio voyages through small-town America, where Amy is accosted by various men claiming to be her lovers, and she and Jordan find themselves drawn to Xavier. But can any amount of sex lift the sense of doom hanging over them?

name: Julien Donkey-Boy
title: 1999 ‧ Drama/Indie film ‧ 1h 34m
description: Harmony Korine's experimental drama about a disturbed young man and his nightmarish family life.

name: The Devil's Rejects
title: 2005 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 49m
description: Sheriff Wydell and his men attack and nab one of the Firefly's, a family of sadistic serial killers known as 'The Devil's Reject'. Those who escaped have now kidnapped a few more people at a motel.

name: Oculus
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 45m
description: A recently released inmate from a mental asylum learns from his sister that the murders he was convicted of committing were actually orchestrated by a supernatural entity, the Lasser Glass mirror.

name: Tag
title: 2015 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 25m
description: Mitsuko, a young student, encounters a series of horrifying incident set in alternate realities where people wind up dead in the most horrendous fashion.

name: Noriko's Dinner Table
title: 2005 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 2h 39m
description: A Japanese teenager (Kazue Fukiishi) runs away to Tokyo to join a weird Internet cult whose leader (Tsugumi) hires out members to clients who want to pretend they have a family.

name: Ju-On: The Curse 2
title: 2000 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 32m
description: Shunsuke Kobayashi visits the Saeki household and finds the corpse of Kayako Saeki hidden in the attic. Takeo Saeki reveals he has killed Kobayashi's pregnant wife Manami. Kayako's body rises as an Onryō to track down and kill the rampaging Takeo.

name: Ju-On: The Grudge
title: 2002 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 32m
description: An evil curse and vengeful spirits seem to linger in a house where the horrific murder of a woman and child took place and anyone who sets foot in the house doesn't step out alive.

name: Ju-On: The Grudge 2
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 32m
description: Actress Kyoko loses her unborn baby and her fiance lands in a coma post a car crash. In fact, Kyoko and the crew were cursed while filming in the home of Kayako who was brutally killed by her husband.

name: Ju-on: The Curse
title: 2000 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 10m
description: A teacher visits the house of one of his students after the boy goes missing, only to have a horrifying excuse for his absence from school.

name: Dumplings
title: 2004 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 31m
description: The infamous Aunt Mei (Bai Ling), a former gynecologist who performed abortions, makes dumplings with miraculous youth-restoring abilities. Mrs. Li (Miriam Yeung), a former actress desperate to make her womanizing husband (Tony Leung Ka Fai) pay attention to her again, initially refuses to eat them. However, after discovering their potency, she offers to pay Mei any price for more. Things are complicated when Mei is forced to flee the country and the dumplings' power begins to fade.

name: Lady Vengeance
title: 2005 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 55m
description: A woman is framed for murdering a six-year-old boy and is imprisoned for 13 years. After releasing from jail, she seeks revenge on the man responsible for committing the crime and framing her.

name: A Tale of Two Sisters
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 55m
description: On returning home from a mental health facility, two sisters find that along with their stepmother, they have to find a way to deal with their late mother's ghost who begins to haunt them.

name: Tomie
title: 1998 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 35m
description: Following some trauma in her past that has since been repressed, a young woman tries to recover her memories with the help of a psychiatrist.

name: Tomie: Forbidden Fruit
title: 2002 ‧ Horror/World cinema ‧ 1h 31m
description: When a lonely high school girl befriends a strange, mysterious and beautiful girl, is soon becomes clear that theirs was not a chance meeting.

name: Gozu
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 2h 9m
description: When Ozaki, a gang member who begins to go insane, his leader orders his brother Minami to end his life. Minami finds it challenging to go through with the mission and finds himself in a dilemma.

name: Ford v Ferrari
title: 2019 ‧ Sport/Action ‧ 2h 32m
description: Carroll Shelby, an automotive designer, and Ken Miles, a race car driver, join hands to build a trailblazing vehicle and compete against the Ferrari race cars.

name: Need for Speed
title: 2014 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 2h 10m
description: A street racer is framed by a rival who is also a wealthy business associate in a murder case. Upon his release, the street racer devises a plan with revenge in mind.

name: Nyad
title: 2023 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 2 hours
description: Sixty-four-year-old marathon swimmer Diana Nyad attempts to become the first person ever to swim from Cuba to Florida.

name: Ferrari
title: 2003 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 3h 35m
description: The story revolves around the life of Enzo Ferrari who rose from being a race driver to being the founder of automobile giant Ferrari.

name: The Champion
title: 2019 ‧ Sport/Comedy ‧ 1h 45m
description: After his latest screw-up, an extremely talented, unpredictable football player is given a personal tutor to help him in controlling his behaviour.

name: The Holdovers
title: 2023 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 13m
description: A curmudgeonly instructor at a New England prep school remains on campus during Christmas break to babysit a handful of students with nowhere to go. He soon forms an unlikely bond with a brainy but damaged troublemaker, and with the school's head cook, a woman who just lost a son in the Vietnam War.

name: The Wrestler
title: 2008 ‧ Sport/Thriller ‧ 1h 49m
description: An ageing wrestler struggles to keep up with life as he is too old to continue his wrestling career. He realizes that he has to come to terms with what life has to offer at this stage and move on.

name: The Boys in the Boat
title: 2023 ‧ Sport/War ‧ 2h 4m
description: During the height of the Great Depression, members of the rowing team at the University of Washington get thrust into the spotlight as they compete for gold at the 1936 Olympics in Berlin.

name: Nightcrawler
title: 2014 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 57m
description: Lou Bloom, a petty thief, becomes a photojournalist and sells footage of sensational and violent stories in Los Angeles to Nina, a news director. Soon, Lou turns desperate to stay ahead of the game.

name: Zodiac
title: 2007 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 37m
description: Robert Graysmith, a cartoonist by profession, finds himself obsessively thinking about the zodiac killer. He uses his puzzle-solving abilities to get closer to revealing the identity of the killer.

name: Baby Driver
title: 2017 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 55m
description: Doc forces Baby, a former getaway driver, to partake in a heist, threatening to hurt his girlfriend if he refuses. But the plan goes awry when their arms dealers turn out to be undercover officers.

name: The Departed
title: 2006 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 31m
description: An undercover agent and a spy constantly try to counter-attack each other in order to save themselves from being exposed in front of the authorities. Meanwhile, both try to infiltrate an Irish gang.

name: Seven
title: 1995 ‧ Crime/Mystery ‧ 2h 7m
description: Detectives Somerset and Mills, one a seasoned cop, the other a relatively new one, are paired up to solve murders. Together they attempt to find a killer who is inspired by the seven deadly sins.

name: Training Day
title: 2001 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 2m
description: When South Central Los Angeles sees the rise of drug dealers, Jake Hoyt is trained by Alonzo Harries of L.A.P.D to knock down the bad guys. But soon, his training methods draw objections from others.

name: Raging Bull
title: 1980 ‧ Sport/Action ‧ 2h 9m
description: A middleweight ascends through the ranks to achieve his first shot at a boxing title. But his personal life, laden with paranoia, jealousy and rage, scuttles his professional growth.

name: Chinatown
title: 1974 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2h 11m
description: Mrs Mulwray hires Detective Jake, who specializes in matrimonial cases, to spy on her husband, the builder of the city's water system. He finds himself in a web of deceit when Mr Mulwray dies.

name: Drive
title: 2011 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 40m
description: A stuntman and getaway driver falls in love with Irene who is married to a criminal. In a bid to protect her from her husband and some gangsters, he decides to cross over to the other side of the law.

name: End of Watch
title: 2012 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 49m
description: As policemen Brian and Miguel deal with the power struggle between Latino and Black gangs in Los Angeles, their raids on criminal cartels attract the attention of a ruthless Mexican drug cartel.

name: Memento
title: 2000 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 53m
description: Leonard Shelby, an insurance investigator, suffers from anterograde amnesia and uses notes and tattoos to hunt for the man he thinks killed his wife, which is the last thing he remembers.

name: The Silence of the Lambs
title: 1991 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 58m
description: Clarice Starling, an FBI trainee, seeks help from Hannibal Lecter, a psychopathic serial killer and former psychiatrist, in order to apprehend another murderer who has been claiming female victims.

name: Primal Fear
title: 1996 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 10m
description: The murder of an important archbishop leads to the involvement of Martin Vail, Chicago's best lawyer. As he studies the suspects, he becomes sure about certain things, but there's more to the case.

name: Creed
title: 2015 ‧ Sport/Action ‧ 2h 13m
description: Adonis Johnson, the son of a former heavyweight champion, dreams of becoming a boxer. Things take a turn when he finds his late father's friend, Rocky, in Philadelphia who agrees to mentor him.

name: Creed II
title: 2018 ‧ Sport/Action ‧ 2h 10m
description: In 1985, Ivan Drago killed Apollo Creed in a tragic boxing match. Under the guidance of his trainer Rocky, Apollo's son Adonis confronts Drago's son in an ultimate showdown.

name: Insomnia
title: 2002 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 58m
description: Will Dormer, a police detective, is sent to investigate a teenage girl's murder to a small fishing town where he accidentally shoots his co-detective and is afflicted by insomnia brought by the guilt.

name: Following
title: 1998 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 10m
description: A young writer living in London follows people in the hope of using their lives in his novels, but the hobby becomes an obsession and he soon finds himself going further than intended.

name: Mulholland Drive
title: 2001 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2h 27m
description: Rita, a dark-haired amnesiac, and Betty, a perky blonde actress, team up to find clues related to Rita's accident and ascertain her true identity.

name: La La Land
title: 2016 ‧ Musical/Romance ‧ 2h 8m
description: When Sebastian, a pianist, and Mia, an actress, follow their passion and achieve success in their respective fields, they find themselves torn between their love for each other and their careers.

name: Good Time
title: 2017 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 41m
description: When Sebastian, a pianist, and Mia, an actress, follow their passion and achieve success in their respective fields, they find themselves torn between their love for each other and their careers.

name: Requiem for a Dream
title: 2000 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 42m
description: Sara, a widow who lives a retired life, develops an obsession to lose weight and starts taking pills. However, she gets addicted to the medication and it takes a toll on her mental health.

name: There Will Be Blood
title: 2007 ‧ Western/Thriller ‧ 2h 38m
description: Daniel Plainview is a ruthless oil prospector who goes on a relentless pursuit to become the most powerful oil tycoon. For this, he even resorts to manipulating and using his adopted son.

name: The Hateful Eight
title: 2015 ‧ Western/Thriller ‧ 3h 7m
description: When a bounty hunter and his captured fugitive are caught in the middle of a snowstorm in Wyoming, they encounter a twisted turn of events as they seek refuge in a small lodge.

name: Hell or High Water
title: 2016 ‧ Western/Crime ‧ 1h 42m
description: Toby and his brother, Tanner, an ex-convict, resort to robbing banks when they are unable to afford their mortgage payments.

name: The Big Short
title: 2015 ‧ Comedy/Thriller ‧ 2h 10m
description: In the mid-2000s, a few finance experts observe the instability in the US housing market and predict its collapse. Through their research, they discover the flaws and corruption in the system.

name: Silver Linings Playbook
title: 2012 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 2h 2m
description: After being released from a mental institution, Pat meets Tiffany, who suffers from depression. She tells him that she will help him reunite with his wife if he becomes her partner in a competition.

name: Blade Runner
title: 1982 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 1h 57m
description: Rick Deckard, an ex-policeman, becomes a special agent with a mission to exterminate a group of violent androids. As he starts getting deeper into his mission, he questions his own identity.

name: Dune: Part Two
title: 2024 ‧ Sci-fi/Adventure ‧ 2h 46m
description: Paul Atreides unites with Chani and the Fremen while seeking revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family. Facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the universe, he must prevent a terrible future only he can foresee.

name: The Fall Guy
title: 2024 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 2h 5m
description: After leaving the business one year earlier, battle-scarred stuntman Colt Seavers springs back into action when the star of a big studio movie suddenly disappears. As the mystery surrounding the missing actor deepens, Colt soon finds himself ensnared in a sinister plot that pushes him to the edge of a fall more dangerous than any stunt.

name: Thor: Ragnarok
title: 2017 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 10m
description: Deprived of his mighty hammer Mjolnir, Thor must escape the other side of the universe to save his home, Asgard, from Hela, the goddess of death.

name: Captain America: The Winter Soldier
title: 2014 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 2h 16m
description: Steve Rogers, along with Black Widow and Falcon, must uncover the secrets hidden within S.H.I.E.L.D., while also battling a dangerous new enemy, who is only known as The Winter Soldier.

name: Avengers: Age of Ultron
title: 2015 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 21m
description: Tony Stark builds an artificial intelligence system named Ultron with the help of Bruce Banner. When the sentient Ultron makes plans to wipe out the human race, the Avengers set out to stop him.

name: Avengers: Infinity War
title: 2018 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 29m
description: As Thanos sets about his quest for finding the infinity stones and carrying out his twisted scheme, the Avengers join forces with their allies to stop him from causing chaos and destruction.

name: The Shift
title: 2023 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 1h 55m
description: After a tense encounter with a mysterious stranger with otherworldly powers, a man finds himself banished to a parallel Earth, where he fights to get back to the woman he loves.

name: Lone Survivor
title: 2013 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 1m
description: Marcus Luttrell and three Navy SEALs are sent to locate the Taliban leader Ahmad Shah in the Hindu Kush region of Afghanistan, where they become targets of enemy attacks.

name: Black Hawk Down
title: 2001 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 24m
description: When an elite force of American soldiers is tasked with the mission to nab a Somalian warlord's top lieutenants, they find themselves ambushed by a large group of heavily-armed Somalis instead.

name: The Expendables 3
title: 2014 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 2h 6m
description: Barney assembles a new and younger team to capture Stonebanks, a co-founder of the Expendables. However, Stonebanks ends up capturing the new team and challenges an escaped Barney to save them.

name: The Expendables
title: 2010 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 43m
description: A group of tough mercenaries are tasked with a mission to overthrow a South American dictator. The situation regresses after they learn that the dictator is a puppet in the hands of an ex-CIA agent.

name: The Expendables 2
title: 2012 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 43m
description: All hell breaks loose when Barney, along with his band of old-school mercenaries, sets out on a path of carnage after one of their comrades gets killed during a simple task assigned by Mr. Church.

name: The Toxic Avenger
title: 2023 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 42m
description: A janitor becomes a social outcast when a freak accident at a chemical factory turns him into a mutant. However, he soon uses his newfound superhuman strength to battle slimy criminals and a corrupt CEO.

name: Saving Private Ryan
title: 1998 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 49m
description: During the Normandy invasion of World War II, Captain John Miller is assigned the task of searching for Private James Ryan, whose three brothers have already been killed in the war.

name: Inception
title: 2010 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 2h 28m
description: Cobb steals information from his targets by entering their dreams. He is wanted for his alleged role in his wife's murder and his only chance at redemption is to perform a nearly impossible task.

name: Midway
title: 2019 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 18m
description: The decisive plunge taken by the United States Navy under the directives of iron-willed admirals helps defeat the Japanese fleet near Midway Atoll.

name: The Hunt for Red October
title: 1990 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 2h 15m
description: CIA analyst Jack Ryan must do what it takes to prove that Marko Ramius, the captain of a nuclear Soviet submarine that suddenly changed route towards the USA, is trying to defect and not attack.

name: The Martian
title: 2015 ‧ Sci-fi/Adventure ‧ 2h 31m
description: Mark Watney, an astronaut, strives to survive in Mars when a space mission goes wrong. While he undergoes different challenges, his colleagues in NASA exhaust all options to bring him home.

name: Apollo 13
title: 1995 ‧ Adventure/Drama ‧ 2h 20m
description: Astronauts Lovell, Haise and Swigert of the Apollo 13 moon mission find themselves stranded when their spacecraft gets damaged. Soon, NASA tries to bring them back before it is too late.

name: Mission: Impossible – Rogue Nation
title: 2015 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 11m
description: After the closure of the Impossible Missions Force, its agent Ethan Hunt tries to avoid being captured by the CIA as he seeks to prove the existence of the Syndicate, a sophisticated terrorist outfit.

name: Ex Machina
title: 2014 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 1h 50m
description: Caleb Smith, a young programmer, gets a chance to become a part of a strange scientific experiment where he is expected to assess artificial intelligence by interacting with a female robot.

name: Arrival
title: 2016 ‧ Sci-fi/Mystery ‧ 1h 56m
description: Louise Banks, a linguistics expert, along with her team, must interpret the language of aliens who have come to Earth in a mysterious spaceship.

name: The Man Who Knew Infinity
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 48m
description: Srinivasa Ramanujan, an exceptionally gifted young mathematician, writes to Professor G H Hardy at Trinity College, Cambridge, and a beautiful friendship ensues between them.

name: The Theory of Everything
title: 2014 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 3m
description: Stephen Hawking gets unprecedented success in the field of physics despite being diagnosed with motor neuron disease at the age of 21. He defeats awful odds as his first wife Jane aids him loyally.

name: Shutter Island
title: 2010 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2h 18m
description: Teddy Daniels and Chuck Aule, two US marshals, are sent to an asylum on a remote island in order to investigate the disappearance of a patient, where Teddy uncovers a shocking truth about the place.

name: The Prestige
title: 2006 ‧ Thriller/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 10m
description: Two friends and fellow magicians become bitter enemies after a sudden tragedy. As they devote themselves to this rivalry, they make sacrifices that bring them fame but, with terrible consequences.

name: Catch Me If You Can
title: 2002 ‧ Crime/Comedy ‧ 2h 21m
description: Frank Abagnale Jr is a con man who poses as a pilot, doctor and lawyer and cashes forged cheques worth millions before his 21st birthday, despite being constantly chased by FBI agent Carl Hanratty.

name: The Whale
title: 2022 ‧ Drama/Melodrama ‧ 1h 57m
description: In a town in Idaho, Charlie, a reclusive and unhealthy English teacher, hides out in his flat and eats his way to death. He is desperate to reconnect with his teenage daughter for a last chance at redemption.

name: Moonrise Kingdom
title: 2012 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 34m
description: Two 12-year-olds, who live on an island, fall in love with each other and elope into the wilderness. While people set out on a search mission, a violent storm approaching them catches their attention.

name: The Life Aquatic with Steve Zissou
title: 2004 ‧ Comedy/Adventure ‧ 1h 59m
description: While working on a documentary at sea, an oceanographer's work partner gets killed by a shark. Soon, along with a crew, he sets off on an expedition to exact revenge on the aquatic animal.

name: Isi & Ossi
title: 2020 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 53m
description: They couldn't be any more different: Isi (20) is a billionaire's daughter from posh Heidelberg, Ossi (23) lives in the nearby working-class town of Mannheim, raised by his poor, struggling single mother.

name: Kill Boksoon
title: 2023 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 17m
description: Gil Bok-Soon is a single mother and merciless murderer who works for Cha Min-Kyu's M.K. Ent. Before renewing her contract, Bok-Soon engages in a kill-or-be-killed confrontation.

name: The Chaser
title: 2008 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 2h 3m
description: An ex-policeman runs a small ring of prostitutes. When he finds out one of the women is missing, he begins hunting down a serial killer who is preying on his girls.

name: The Swindlers
title: 2017 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 1h 56m
description: Park, a public prosecutor, and Ji-sung, a fraudster, work together to track down an infamous con artist. However, both of them have their own personal motives.

name: Recalled
title: 2021 ‧ Mystery/Thriller ‧ 1h 39m
description: Soo-jin begins to see the future of other people after losing her memories from an accident. As she slowly regains her memories and her visions start becoming reality, Soo-jin must uncover the truth.

name: A Hard Day
title: 2014 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 51m
description: A corrupt detective has a hit-and-run accident while leaving his mother's funeral. He manages to cover it up but soon gets a mysterious call from a man claiming to have witnessed the accident.

name: Midnight
title: 2021 ‧ Thriller/Thriller ‧ 1h 43m
description: A woman with hearing impairment witnesses a serial killer stabbing someone. Soon, she becomes his next target as her brother and mother try to protect her from harm.

name: The Flash
title: 2014 ‧ Sci-fi ‧ 9 seasons
description: Barry Allen, a forensic investigator in Central City, gains the power of superhuman speed from a freak accident. He decides to use it to fight crime as the Flash, a costumed superhero.

name: The Falcon and the Winter Soldier
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Falcon and the Winter Soldier are a mismatched duo who team up for a global adventure that will test their survival skills -- as well as their patience.

name: Menace II Society
title: 1993 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 37m
description: Caine a drug dealer and car thief is kicked out of his grand-parents house due to his life of crime. His troubles don't end there as he is wanted by the police for the killing of a Korean grocer.

name: Boyz n the Hood
title: 1991 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 52m
description: Three childhood friends, Darrin, Tre and Ricky, who struggle to cope with the distractions and dangers of growing up in a Los Angeles ghetto.

name: New Jack City
title: 1991 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 40m
description: Two cops take it on themselves to bring down a notorious drug lord who has gotten away from the law for much too long.

name: South Central
title: 1992 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 40m
description: After spending 10 years in jail, Bobby comes out to start a new life, only to find out that his son is now a criminal.

name: Straight Outta Compton
title: 2015 ‧ Musical/Crime ‧ 2h 27m
description: A hip-hop group from Compton, California, spirals into several controversies because of their brash lyrics and revolutionising music, igniting a culture war.

name: Love Jones
title: 1997 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 50m
description: Two urban African-Americans, Darius (Larenz Tate), an aspiring writer, and Nina (Nia Long), an aspiring photographer, share an instant connection after a chance meeting at a Chicago club. The two bond over music, photography and poetry, and eventually begin a torrid romance. However, when Nina decides to move to New York and mend her relationship with her ex-fiancé, Marvin (Khalil Kain), it leaves Darius heartbroken, and the couple's future in jeopardy.

name: Eve's Bayou
title: 1997 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 49m
description: When Eve catches her father with another woman in the barn, she is completely shaken. She visits a voodoo priestess when her belief in family loyalty begins to crumble.

name: Biggie & Tupac
title: 2002 ‧ Documentary/Indie film ‧ 1h 48m
description: Nick Broomfield examines the lives and murders of rappers Biggie Smalls and Tupac Shakur and the rivalry between East Coast and West Coast music that culminated in their deaths. The film looks at the former friendship of the two artists and also investigates possible cover-ups and police corruption.

name: The Wood
title: 1999 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 46m
description: Three friends reminisce about their youth as one of them prepares to get married. However, when the groom goes missing, his companions must find him before it is too late.

name: Jason's Lyric
title: 1994 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2 hours
description: Jason is in love with Lyric. He wants to begin a new life with her but his troubled young brother and the nightmares of his childhood act as a hindrance.

name: Paid in Full
title: 2002 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 38m
description: A teen, envious of the high-rolling lifestyle of his drug-dealing friends, joins the business and moves to the top of the Harlem drug world while rivals conspire to bring about his fall.

name: A Low Down Dirty Shame
title: 1994 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 1h 48m
description: Andre Shame, a detective, leaves the police force after he fails to solve a case of drug lord, Ernesto Mendoza. Years later, when the case is re-opened, Andre vows to decipher the assignment.

name: Dead Presidents
title: 1995 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 1h 59m
description: Anthony struggles to give direction to his life while trying to find the right job. Dejected, he teams up with his friends and tries to rob an armored truck carrying cash.

name: The Best Man
title: 1999 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 2 hours
description: When a copy of his tell-all book finds its way to an ex-flame, a writer must attempt to keep its contents a secret from his friends.

name: Next Friday
title: 2000 ‧ Comedy/Stoner ‧ 1h 38m
description: Craig, a young boy, helps his uncle, Elroy, pay off his debt to save his house from being auctioned through stealing from their neighbours.

name: Friday After Next
title: 2002 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 28m
description: When a burglar robs Craig and D-Day on Christmas Eve, the penniless cousins must acquire rent money quickly. Chaos ensues as they get hired as a security guard and stumble into trouble.

name: Roll Bounce
title: 2005 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 52m
description: When their local roller-skating rink closes down, a group of teenagers from the south side of Chicago enter the roller skating contest at a ritzy rink on the north side.

name: Baby Boy
title: 2001 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 10m
