description: As a Nazi German submarine patrols the Atlantic Ocean during WWII, the crew experiences long periods of inactivity and intense bouts of warfare against the foe, as they try to maintain their morale.

name: Galaxy of Terror
title: 1981 ‧ Sci-fi/Horror ‧ 1h 21m
description: The crew of a rescue spaceship encounters a gigantic pyramid-like structure and soon their worst fears turn into reality. The pyramid is believed to be the cause of their predicament.

name: Logan's Run
title: 1976 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 2 hours
description: In the year 2274, although things seem perfect, the government is operating a secret plan. People over the year of thirty are executed and those who try to escape are tracked down.

name: Sorcerer
title: 1977 ‧ Adventure/Action ‧ 2h 1m
description: Four men from different parts of the globe are trying to hide from the law. They are offered ten thousand dollars and legal citizenship to transport a shipment of dangerously unstable nitroglycerine.

name: Three Days of the Condor
title: 1975 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 57m
description: A bookish CIA researcher is shocked to see that all of his co-workers are suddenly murdered. With an assassin tailing him at every turn, he must now figure out who wants him dead.

name: Soylent Green
title: 1973 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 1h 37m
description: In a dystopian New York City, a police detective investigates the murder of a businessman from a synthetic food corporation. However, his investigation begins to lead him towards a sinister truth.

name: Escape from New York
title: 1981 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 39m
description: Gruff Snake Plissken, an ex-soldier turned convict, is sent to Manhattan, now a maximum security prison, to rescue the stranded US President.

name: Assault on Precinct 13
title: 1976 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 31m
description: A group of individuals trapped in a police station are attacked by a horde of street gang members.

name: The French Connection
title: 1971 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 44m
description: New York City cop Doyle and his partner are trying to bust a drug cartel based in France. Albeit short-tempered, Doyle is a dedicated cop whose nemesis, Alain Charnier, is too polished for a criminal.

name: The Warriors
title: 1979 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 30m
description: In New York City, the members of a gang called The Warriors are framed for the death of a charismatic leader. With other gangs out for revenge against them, they must get back to their home turf.

name: Dirty Harry
title: 1971 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 42m
description: When San Francisco is plagued by the terror of a maniac who calls himself Scorpio, Inspector Harry is assigned the task to track down Scorpio with the help of his partner Inspector Chico.

name: Deep Red
title: 1975 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 2h 6m
description: Jazz pianist, Marcus Daly, witnesses a murder. Things don't seem so bad afterwards, despite the fact that he's shaky, but then strange things start to happen.

name: The Conversation
title: 1974 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 53m
description: Harry Caul, a reticent surveillance expert, gets into trouble when he suspects the couple he secretly recorded is going to be murdered by his client.

name: Dawn of the Dead
title: 1978 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 2h 7m
description: As hordes of zombies swarm over the U.S., the terrified populace tries everything in their power to escape the attack of the undead, but neither cities nor the countryside prove safe. In Pennsylvania, radio-station employee Stephen (David Emge) and his girlfriend, Francine (Gaylen Ross), escape in the station helicopter, accompanied by two renegade SWAT members, Roger and Pete. The group retreats to the haven of an enclosed shopping center to make what could be humanity's last stand.

name: Night of the Living Dead
title: 1968 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 36m
description: A group of unsuspecting people get trapped in an old farmhouse after the dead unexpectedly rise from the grave and seek the living as food.

name: Defiance
title: 2008 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 17m
description: The story of the film revolves around three Jewish brothers in Nazi-occupied Eastern Europe. They turn a group of war refugees into powerful freedom fighters against the Nazi regime.

name: One Life
title: 2023 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 1h 50m
description: London broker Nicholas "Nicky" Winton helps rescue hundreds of predominantly Jewish children from Czechoslovakia in a race against time before the Nazi occupation closes the borders. Fifty years later, he's still haunted by the fate of those he wasn't able to bring to safety.

name: Anthropoid
title: 2016 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 2 hours
description: With limited intelligence and equipment, two Czech soldiers in exile return to their Nazi-occupied homeland and execute a mission to assassinate SS officer Reinhard Heydrich.

name: Valkyrie
title: 2008 ‧ Thriller/War ‧ 2h 4m
description: During World War II, a team of Nazi officers plan a coup to arrange Operation Valkyrie, which will enable them to take charge of Berlin. But they have to assassinate Hitler to implement the operation.

name: Downfall
title: 2004 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 36m
description: As the Allied forces get closer to the Nazi capital, Hitler and his comrades barricade themselves in the Fuhrerbunker. Many vow to stand by Hitler, but Traudl, his personal secretary, tries to escape.

name: Inglourious Basterds
title: 2009 ‧ War/Adventure ‧ 2h 33m
description: Shosanna wants to avenge her family's death by the Nazis. Years later, she finally gets the opportunity, but things change when a group of Jewish-American guerilla soldiers have a similar plan.

name: The Siege of Jadotville
title: 2016 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 48m
description: An Irish commander and his battalion of 150 men withstand a siege by 3,000 Congolese troops led by French and Belgian mercenaries working for mining corporations.

name: Winter in Wartime
title: 2008 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 1h 44m
description: During the final stages of World War II in the Nazi-occupied Netherlands, fourteen-year-old Michiel unwittingly gets involved with the Resistance after he saves Jack, a wounded British soldier.

name: The East
title: 2020 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 2h 21m
description: A soldier, deployed to suppress post-WWII rebellion in Indonesia, finds himself torn between duty and conscience when he joins an elite task force led by an increasingly ruthless commander.

name: Escape from Sobibor
title: 1987 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 2h 23m
description: Prisoners of a concentration camp fight a battle of conscience as they must make a decision to either stay and die or kill the soldiers and escape the camp.

name: Battle for Sevastopol
title: 2015 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 2m
description: Lyudmila Pavlichenko impresses her peers in the Russian army with her exceptional skills. However, the German High Command considers Lyudmila as a potential threat and passes an order to kill her.

name: The Captain
title: 2017 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 1h 58m
description: During the Second World War, a young German soldier attempts to escape a horrific regime by impersonating a Nazi officer.

name: T-34
title: 2019 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 19m
description: A group of brave soldiers, who are held captive in a German concentration camp, devises a plan to evade in their heavily damaged T-34 tank during World War II.

name: Persian Lessons
title: 2020 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 7m
description: Gilles, a young Jewish man in a concentration camp, has his life saved when executioners realise he owns a Persian book. Brought before a camp officer who wants to learn Farsi, Gilles agrees to teach him despite not knowing a word of the language.

name: The Photographer of Mauthausen
title: 2018 ‧ Thriller/War ‧ 1h 50m
description: Catalan photographer and militant communist Francisco Boix records the horrors committed inside the walls of a Nazi concentration camp in Mauthausen, and the evidence he saves is used to indict numerous Nazi leaders during the Nuremberg trials.

name: Max Manus: Man of War
title: 2008 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 58m
description: After the Finnish Winter War against the Soviet troops, adventurer Max Manus comes back to his home. When he learns that his country is occupied by the German army, he joins the resistance movement.

name: Land of Mine
title: 2015 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 1h 40m
description: After WWII, German soldiers in Danish captivity are given the task of clearing the beaches of landmines. With no training or equipment, they try to survive this mission and gain their freedom.

name: Coherence
title: 2013 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 1h 29m
description: Eight friends come together one evening for a dinner party. They soon experience a chain of strange events after a comet passes the Earth.

name: Triangle
title: 2009 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 39m
description: After a yachting accident, a group of friends take refuge in an abandoned cruise liner. However, they soon realise that they are being stalked by a stranger who wants to hunt them down.

name: Moon
title: 2009 ‧ Sci-fi/Mystery ‧ 1h 37m
description: Astronaut Sam, the sole employee working at a lunar station with his computer, GERTY, is nearing the end of his three-year work contract. Just before he returns home, he meets with a fatal accident.

name: Beyond the Infinite Two Minutes
title: 2020 ‧ Comedy/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 10m
description: A cafe owner discovers that the TV in his cafe suddenly shows images from the future, but only two minutes into the future.

name: The Tunnel
title: 2011 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 30m
description: A film crew learns of a government cover-up about the abandoned train tunnels beneath the heart of Sydney, and decides to go inside to try to find the truth. Very quickly the group begins to realise that perhaps the cover-up was for a good reason.

name: Mr. Nobody
title: 2009 ‧ Sci-fi/Fantasy ‧ 2h 18m
description: When humans become immortal, a 118-year-old Nemo, Earth's last mortal, recounts his life story to a reporter, explaining to him things that he did at various junctures of his life.

name: Vacancy
title: 2007 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 25m
description: A couple stuck at a secluded motel see that several video cameras are attached to their room. They realise that unless they flee, they will become the next victims of a snuff film.

title: 2007 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 52m
description: A man who specializes in debunking paranormal occurrences checks into the fabled room 1408 in the Dolphin Hotel. As he settles in, he confronts genuine terror. Stars: John Cusack, Samuel L. Jackson.

name: High Tension
title: 2003 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 31m
description: Alexia and her friend Marie go on a vacation to Alexia's farmhouse. The leisure trip turns horrific when a serial killer breaks into their house.

name: Lake Mungo
title: 2008 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 29m
description: Alice drowns while swimming and her family begins experiencing inexplicable events in their home. The family hires a parapsychologist whose investigation unveils Alice's secret double life and leads them all to Lake Mungo.

name: The Last House on the Left
title: 2009 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 50m
description: A couple shows kindness to a group of strangers, unaware that the same men just assaulted their daughter. However, when the truth is revealed, the devastated parents plan revenge.

name: Martyrs
title: 2008 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 39m
description: Lucie and Anna who have been victims of child abuse embark on a journey to take revenge on their perpetrators.

name: Wolf Creek
title: 2005 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 39m
description: Horror tale of backpacking friends out in the Australian wilderness whose car breaks down. They accept help from an eccentric local who turns out to be a tourist-hating maniac.

name: You're Next
title: 2011 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 35m
description: Aubrey and Paul invite their family to their estate to celebrate their anniversary. Their party turns into a nightmare when the family is attacked by masked assassins.

name: Splinter
title: 2008 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 22m
description: A young couple and an escaped convict get trapped in a secluded gas station while hiding from a fungal parasite that turns its victims into dangerous hosts. To survive, they must work together.

name: House of Wax
title: 2005 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 53m
description: A group of friends stranded on the way to a football match approach an abandoned wax museum for help. But the events that unfold find them running from the murderous brothers who manage the place.

name: House on Haunted Hill
title: 1999 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 33m
description: A millionaire offers a group of diverse people 1 million dollars to spend the night in a haunted house with a horrifying past.

name: The Patient
title: 2022 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: Therapist, Alan Strauss, is held prisoner by a patient, Sam Fortner, who reveals himself to be a serial killer. Sam has an unusual therapeutic demand for Alan: curb his homicidal urges. In order to survive, Alan must unwind Sam's disturbed mind and stop him from killing again but Sam refuses to address critical topics, like his mother Candace. Alone in captivity, Alan excavates his own past through memories of his old therapist, Charlie, and grapples with waves of his own repressed troubles -- the recent death of his wife, Beth, and the painful estrangement from his religious son, Ezra. Over the course of his imprisonment, Alan uncovers not only how deep Sam's compulsion runs, but also how much work he has to do to repair the rift in his own family.

name: When They See Us
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: In 1989 a jogger was assaulted and raped in New York's Central Park, and five young people were subsequently charged with the crime. The quintet, labeled the Central Park Five, maintained its innocence and spent years fighting the convictions, hoping to be exonerated. This limited series spans a quarter of a century, from when the teens are first questioned about the incident in the spring of 1989, going through their exoneration in 2002 and ultimately the settlement reached with the city of New York in 2014. The cast is full of Emmy nominees and winners, including Michael K. Williams, John Leguizamo, Felicity Huffman, and Blair Underwood. Oscar nominee and Emmy winner Ava DuVernay co-wrote and directed the four episodes.

name: Inside Man
title: 2022 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: A prisoner on death row in the U.S. and a woman trapped in a cellar under an English vicarage cross paths in an unexpected way.

name: Mind Over Murder
title: 2022 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: "Mind Over Murder" chronicles the bizarre and psychologically complex story of six individuals who were convicted for the 1985 murder of beloved 68-year-old grandmother Helen Wilson, in Beatrice, Neb. Despite five of the individuals originally confessing to the crime, the "Beatrice Six" as they became known, were exonerated by DNA evidence in 2009, in a turn of events that divided the rural town and incensed the family of Helen Wilson. As the filmmakers track the case from the murder, through investigation, trial, exoneration and two civil suits, shifting perspectives cloud the truth. A stranger-than-fiction tale emerges that raises questions about the reliability of confessions and memory in criminal cases.

name: 2001: A Space Odyssey
title: 1968 ‧ Sci-fi/Adventure ‧ 2h 29m
description: Humanity discovers a mystifying, artificial object buried underneath the lunar surface. With the assistance of HAL 9000, an intelligent computer, mankind embarks on an interesting quest.

name: The Thing
title: 1982 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 49m
description: A research team finds an alien being that has fallen from the sky and is starting to hunt them down. Things take a sinister turn when they realise that the creature can take the shape of its victims.

name: Brazil
title: 1985 ‧ Sci-fi/Comedy ‧ 2h 22m
description: In a retro-future world, Sam Lowry, a clerk in the ministry department, is given the task to rectify an administrative error. However, in the process, he becomes the enemy of the state.

name: Aliens
title: 1986 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 2h 17m
description: Ellen Ripley is sent back to the planet LV-426 to establish contact with a terraforming colony. Once there, she encounters the Alien Queen and her offspring and has to fight them to survive.

name: Total Recall
title: 1990 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 53m
description: Douglas Quaid tries to find the reason behind his recurring dream about Mars. He soon learns that a false memory has been planted into his brain and the people responsible for this want him dead.

name: Ghost in the Shell
title: 1995 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 23m
description: In a futuristic world where brain hacking has become rampant, a cyborg policewoman and her partner set out to find the main culprit behind the crime, the Puppet Master.

name: Videodrome
title: 1983 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 29m
description: Max, a television programmer, stumbles upon a show that leaves a subliminal impact on the viewers. As he unearths the origins of the program, he embarks on a hallucinatory journey.

name: Taxi Driver
title: 1976 ‧ Crime/Noir ‧ 1h 54m
description: Travis, an ex-marine and Vietnam veteran, works as a taxi driver in New York City. One day, he decides to save an underage prostitute from her pimp in an effort to clean the city of its corruption.

name: Metropolis
title: 1927 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 2h 33m
description: In the city of the future, wealthy industrialists reign from their ivory towers while the workers toil away. However, a leader's decision to enlist a mad scientist could lead the city to ruin.

name: Men in Black
title: 1997 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 38m
description: James, an NYC cop, is hired by Agent K of a secret government agency that monitors extraterrestrial life on Earth. Together, they must recover an item that has been stolen by an intergalactic villain.

name: Mars Express
title: 2023 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 1h 25m
description: Aline Ruby and her partner are hired by a businessman to track down a hacker; On Mars, they explore the planet's capital city where they find a missing girl who holds a secret about the robots that threaten to change the face of the universe.

name: Cowboy Bebop: The Movie
title: 2001 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 55m
description: Spike Spiegel and his team of bounty hunters are in hot pursuit of a terrorist who has killed scores of people in Mars with a biological weapon and stop him before he strikes again.

name: Passengers
title: 2016 ‧ Romance/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 56m
description: During a voyage to a distant planet, Jim's hypersleep pod malfunctions which wakes him up. So, he and fellow passenger work together to prevent their spaceship from meeting with a disaster.

name: Interstellar
title: 2014 ‧ Sci-fi/Adventure ‧ 2h 49m
description: When Earth becomes uninhabitable in the future, a farmer and ex-NASA pilot, Joseph Cooper, is tasked to pilot a spacecraft, along with a team of researchers, to find a new planet for humans.

name: Children of Men
title: 2006 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 49m
description: In 2027, humanity faces extinction after it fails to reproduce for 18 years. When, a woman gets pregnant, a federal agent protects her as she holds the key to humanity's survival.

name: Nighthawks
title: 1981 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 39m
description: Newly elected to the anti-terrorist force, two elite police officers are assigned a mission to eliminate an international terrorist. Being their initial assignment, will they succeed in this task?

name: The Hitcher
title: 1986 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 37m
description: While transporting a car from Chicago to San Diego, Jim Halsey (C. Thomas Howell) picks up a hitchhiker named John Ryder (Rutger Hauer), who claims to be a serial killer. After a daring escape, Jim hopes to never see Ryder again. But when he witnesses the hitchhiker murdering an entire family, Jim pursues Ryder with the help of truck-stop waitress Nash (Jennifer Jason Leigh), pitting the rivals against each other in a deadly series of car chases and brutal murders.

name: Thelma & Louise
title: 1991 ‧ Adventure/Crime ‧ 2h 10m
description: Docile housewife Thelma accompanies her pal Louise, an independent waitress, on a brief fishing trip. However, when Louise kills a man who attempts to rape Thelma, the two become fugitives of the law.

name: American Psycho
title: 2000 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 42m
description: Patrick Bateman, a wealthy investment banker, hides his psychopathic ego from his friends. Later, his illogical fantasies escalate and he submits to an uncontrollable bloodlust.

name: Donnie Darko
title: 2001 ‧ Thriller/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 53m
description: Donnie Darko, an awkward teenager, befriends Frank, a figure in a bunny costume only he can see, who informs Donnie that the world will end in 28 days, 6 hours, 42 minutes, and 12 seconds.

name: American History X
title: 1998 ‧ Crime/Crime ‧ 1h 59m
description: Danny Vinyard is a high school student and also a neo Nazi in the making. His brother, a former neo Nazi, who is released after a three year stint in prison, tries to talk him out of his wrong ways.

name: The Matrix
title: 1999 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 16m
description: Neo, a computer programmer and hacker, has always questioned the reality of the world around him. His suspicions are confirmed when Morpheus, a rebel leader, contacts him and reveals the truth to him.

name: The Big Lebowski
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 57m
description: Two goons mistake 'the Dude' Lebowski for a millionaire Lebowski and urinate on his rug. Trying to recompense his rug from the wealthy Lebowski, he gets entwined in an intricate kidnapping case.

name: Good Will Hunting
title: 1997 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 6m
description: Will Hunting, a janitor at MIT, is a mathematical genius. But circumstances force him to join therapeutic sessions, where he confronts his past, re-evaluates his present and thinks of his future.

name: Reservoir Dogs
title: 1992 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 39m
description: Six criminals, hired to steal diamonds, do not know each other's true identity. While attempting the heist, the police ambushes them, leading them to believe that one of them is an undercover officer.

name: The Dark Knight Rises
title: 2012 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 45m
description: Bane, a brutal revolutionary who has been excommunicated from the League of Shadows, attacks Gotham City and ruins its long era of peace. Bruce Wayne vows to prevent the city's nuclear annihilation.

name: Ocean's Eleven
title: 2001 ‧ Crime/Comedy ‧ 1h 56m
description: Danny Ocean, a gangster, rounds up a gang of associates to stage a sophisticated and elaborate casino heist which involves robbing three Las Vegas casinos simultaneously during a popular boxing event.

name: Heat
title: 1995 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 50m
description: McCauley, a professional thief, hopes to pull off one last heist before he retires. However, he is under the constant surveillance of a police detective, Hanna, who tries to thwart his plan.

name: Tron: Legacy
title: 2010 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 2h 5m
description: Sam misses his father, a virtual world designer, and enters a virtual space that has become much more dangerous than his father intended. Now, both father and son embark upon a life-and-death journey.

name: Pacific Rim
title: 2013 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 11m
description: A war ensues when the Kaiju, the monstrous sea creatures, attack human beings. The scientists develop massive robots, Jaegers, to combat them. However, they seem futile against the Kaiju's onslaught.

name: Jumanji: The Next Level
title: 2019 ‧ Comedy/Action ‧ 2h 3m
description: When Spencer goes missing, his group of friends return to Jumanji to travel unexplored territories and help him escape the world's most dangerous game.

title: 2022 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: The Duttons face a new set of challenges in the early 20th century, including the rise of Western expansion, Prohibition, and the Great Depression.

name: Yellowstone
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: The Duttons own the largest ranch in America and deal with their internal conflicts. However, they must also fend off land encroachers to protect their property.

name: 1883: A Yellowstone Origin Story
title: 2023 ‧ 1 season
description: A prequel to "Yellowstone," the Dutton family flees poverty in Texas and embarks on a journey through the Great Plains to seek a better future in Montana.

name: Joe Pickett
title: 2021 ‧ Western ‧ 2 seasons
description: A game warden and his family navigate through various experiences and challenges in a constantly shifting political and socio-economic landscape.

name: Hell On Wheels
title: 2011 ‧ Western ‧ 5 seasons
description: After the brutal murder of his wife, Cullen Bohannon, an ex-soldier, embarks on a mission to exact revenge on the group of Union soldiers.

name: Into the West
title: 2005 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: During the Westward expansion, the lives of two individuals, one a White settler and the other a Native American, become deeply interconnected when the former marries the latter's sister.

name: Comanche Moon
title: 2008 ‧ Western
description: After an art dealer, an Oxford professor, and a British aristocrat fall victim to a crooked financier's stock swindle, they work together to get their money back.

name: Hatfields & McCoys
title: 2012 ‧ History ‧ 1 season
description: The rivalry between the Hatfields and the McCoys is one of the oldest and best-known family feuds in American history. This miniseries, featuring a cast led by Kevin Costner and Bill Paxton as the family patriarchs, tells the story of the feud that nearly launched a war between Kentucky and West Virginia. Devil Anse Hatfield and Randall McCoy were close friends until near the end of the Civil War, when they return to their homes -- Hatfield in Kentucky and McCoy in West Virginia -- to increasing tensions and misunderstandings that quickly lead to all-out warfare between the clans (partially caused by a stolen pig). As hostilities grow and outside forces join the fight, the states where the families live are brought to the brink of another war as the feud makes international headlines, the states' governors clash and the U.S. Supreme Court eventually intervenes.

name: The Ranch
title: 2016 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 8 seasons
description: Ashton Kutcher stars in this Netflix-original sitcom as Colt, who returns home to his family's ranch in Colorado after his semi-pro football career ends in failure. Colt plans to run the ranching business with his father, Beau (Sam Elliott), whom he hasn't seen in 15 years at the time of his homecoming. In addition to proving himself to his father and navigating family dynamics, Colt is torn between his current girlfriend and his high school sweetheart, Abby (Elisha Cuthbert), when she expresses doubts about her fiance.

title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: An anti-corruption investigation leads to the fall of the First Republic in Italy. Amidst the chaos, rises a new political party founded by media tycoon Silvio Berlusconi.

name: Lawman
title: 1958 ‧ Western ‧ 4 seasons
description: Dan Troop (John Russell) takes over in Laramie after the previous marshal is killed.

name: Dark Winds
title: 2022 ‧ Thriller ‧ 2 seasons
description: Two Navajo police officers join hands to look for clues and uncover the secrets behind a brutal double murder while battling their own demons and beliefs.

name: Law of the Plainsman
title: 1959 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: Sam Buckhart was an Apache who had saved the life of a U.S. officer. When the officer died, he left Sam money that he put towards his education.

name: Return to Lonesome Dove
title: 1993 ‧ Western
description: Return to Lonesome Dove is a 1993 American four part television miniseries, written by John Wilder involving characters created in Larry McMurtry's Western novel Lonesome Dove which was broadcast by CBS and first aired on November 14–17, 1993.

name: Wanted Dead or Alive
title: 1958 ‧ Western ‧ 3 seasons
description: Josh Randall is a veteran of the Civil War turned bounty hunter. He wanders the Wild West capturing outlaws.

name: Streets of Laredo
title: 1995 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: A railroad company hire a former Texas ranger, captain Woodrow Call, to track down an elusive Mexican bandit.

name: Hard Sun
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Two policemen with contrasting personalities are forced to cooperate when they stumble onto a murder case that leads them to top-secret documents that might challenge the existence of humans.

name: Broken Trail
title: 2006 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: Prent Ritter and his nephew Tom Harte journey from Oregon to Wyoming to sell horses to the British Army. On the journey they feel morally obliged to rescue five Chinese girls from slave trade.

name: The Lincoln Lawyer
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Idealistic lawyer Mickey Haller runs his practise out of the back of his Lincoln Town Car, taking on cases big and small across Los Angeles.

name: Dead Man's Walk
title: 1996 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: Two young Texas rangers forge a lifelong friendship as they encounter Comanches, the Mexican army and harsh terrain in 1840s Texas.

name: Lonesome Dove: The Series
title: 1994 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: A man lives in Curtis Wells, Montana, in 1870.

name: Lonesome Dove: The Outlaw Years
title: 1995 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: A bounty hunter deals with changes in his home town of Curtis Wells, Montana.

name: Unforgiven
title: 1992 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 11m
description: William Munny, a widower with two young kids, was once a very vicious gunfighter who gave up everything after marriage. Now, a man named Schofield Kid brings him an offer that he cannot refuse.

name: The Outlaw Josey Wales
title: 1976 ‧ Western/War ‧ 2h 15m
description: After watching his wife and child death in the hands of Captain Terrill, Josey Wales, a Missouri farmer, joins the Confederate Army to take revenge. However, things don't work out as per the plan.

name: Centennial
title: 1978 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: The evolution of a Colorado town and the people who call it home for various reasons: money, freedom or crime.

name: Hallmark Channel: Ride
title: TV series
description: A family ensemble following the lives of a rodeo dynasty as they struggle to keep their beloved ranch afloat.

name: When Hope Calls
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: In the early 1900s, sisters Lillian and Grace open an orphanage in a northwestern town which is on the cusp of change; the sisters strive to find happiness and romance while meeting the challenges of taking care of the children in their care.

name: When Calls the Heart
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 11 seasons
description: Elizabeth Thatcher, a young teacher who lives a wealthy life, finds her life changed when she is assigned her first classroom assignment in a small coal mining town.

name: Chesapeake Shores
title: 2016 ‧ Family ‧ 6 seasons
description: Abby O'Brien, a divorced mother of two, is confronted with memories of her troubled past when she visits her hometown in Chesapeake Shores to help her sister, Jess, renovate their ancestral inn.

name: Heartland
title: 2007 ‧ Drama ‧ 17 seasons
description: When Amy loses her mother in an accident, she decides to continue her work of healing abused horses. Soon, her life changes with the arrival of her estranged father and New York-based sister.

name: Love's Christmas Journey
title: 2011 ‧ Western/Romance ‧ 2h 52m
description: Ellie mourns the death of her husband and daughter. She visits her brother Aaron and his kids to spend time with them during Christmas. She befriends new people there. But Aaron suddenly goes missing.

name: Carter
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: An awkward public disappointment in Hollywood forces Harley to return to his Ontario home and self-introspect. He joins his friend, a detective, to deploy his acting skills and solve real-life cases.

name: County Rescue
title: 2024 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Dani is an EMT in training who believes her calling is to save lives; she soon finds herself tested each day when she must compete with two other trainees for one job opening.

name: Mystery 101
title: 2019 ‧ Crime ‧ 1 season
description: Amy Winslow, a literature professor who specialises in mystery fiction, uses her skills to solve crimes along with detective Travis Burke.

name: Walker, Texas Ranger
title: 1993 ‧ Action ‧ 9 seasons
description: Cordell Walker, a Texan ranger, is accompanied by his close associates in the crime-fighting business. He uses his martial arts expertise to bring the bad guys to justice.

name: The American West
title: 2016 ‧ Western ‧ 1 season
description: AMC has proven its considerable skill in producing historical Western content (`Broken Trail', `Hell on Wheels'). The network dips into the same well again with the limited event series `Robert Redford's The West', a docudrama that shows how, in the aftermath of the Civil War, the United States transforms into the `land of opportunity', a violent world dominated by cowboys, Indians, outlaws and law men. Across eight episodes, little-known stories are told of Western legends such as Jesse James, Billy the Kid, Wyatt Earp, Crazy Horse and Sitting Bull. The series also features exclusive interviews with notable names from classic Western films, including James Caan, Tom Selleck, Kiefer Sutherland, Ed Harris and more.

name: Black Sails
title: 2014 ‧ History ‧ 4 seasons
description: The feared pirate Captain Flint fights for the survival of New Providence Island after the pirates in West Indies are declared as enemies of mankind.

name: Copper
title: 2012 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Detective Kevin Corcoran takes the help of Robert Morehouse, the son of a rich industrialist and Matthew Freeman, an African American physician, to solve crimes in the Five Points neighbourhood.

name: Oz
title: 1997 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: Inmates in the Oswald Maximum Security Correctional Facility face challenges head on behind bars and do all they can to stay alive.

name: Rough Riders
title: 1997 ‧ War ‧ 1 season
description: Explores the journey of the cavalry group led by Theodore Roosevelt in a charge up San Juan Hill during the Spanish-American War.

name: Hudson
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: While left in charge of Maggie's Diner for the week, Jade Virani butts heads with the new girl in town while they vie for the new manager position.

name: Northern Rescue
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: After his wife dies, search and rescue commander John West uproots his three children, moving the family from Boston to his rural hometown of Turtle Island Bay. The death affects each of their lives as John and his kids cope with their loss. Along the way, John faces situations that challenge him personally and professionally while his offspring deal with typical issues that face kids and teenagers, including school and friendships.

name: Virgin River
title: 2019 ‧ Romance ‧ 5 seasons
description: Seeking a fresh start, a nurse practitioner moves from Los Angeles to a remote Northern California town and is surprised by what -- and who -- she finds.

name: Hudson & Rex
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: Charlie Hudson, a detective of St John's Police Department, teams up with Rex, a trained German Shepard who has excellent hearing, and solves crimes in his jurisdiction.

name: Wind at My Back
title: 1996 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: During the Great Depression of the 1930s, the Bailey Family is struggling to survive in the small mining town of New Bedford in Northern Ontario, wracked not only by economic hardship but also by an unexpected death. Widowed, homeless and broke, Honey Bailey is forced to separate her family and sends her children to live with relatives while she concentrates on rebuilding her life so she can get them back. The family continues to face one hardship after another throughout the '30s as they fight to stay together, learning valuable lessons along the way.

name: Sweet Magnolias
title: 2020 ‧ Romance ‧ 3 seasons
description: Lifelong friends lift each other up as they juggle relationships, family and careers in the small Southern town of Serenity.

name: Fire Country
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Bode Donovan, a young convict seeking redemption, joins an unconventional prison release firefighting program in Northern California, where he and other inmates are partnered with elite firefighters to extinguish massive, unpredictable wildfires. It's a high-risk, high-reward assignment, and the heat is turned up when Bode is assigned to the program in his rural hometown, where he was once a golden all-American son until his troubles began. Five years ago, Bode burned down everything in his life, leaving town with a big secret. Now he's back, with the rap sheet of a criminal and the audacity to believe in a chance for redemption.

name: Street Outlaws
title: 2013 ‧ Reality ‧ 14 seasons
description: Oklahoma City's street racers participate in a contest to showcase their driving skills and compete against each other to win the title.

name: Country Comfort
title: 2021 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 1 season
description: At a crossroads in her career, country singer Bailey takes a job as a nanny for cowboy Beau and his five children.

name: That '70s Show
title: 1998 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 8 seasons
description: Eric, a high school student, and his group of teenage friends struggle to lead purposeful lives whilst going through the tumultuous phase of adolescence.

name: The Upshaws
title: 2021 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: In Indiana, a working-class African American family struggles to make it work and make it right without the blueprints to do it.

name: Last Man Standing
title: 2011 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 9 seasons
description: Mike Baxter, a marketing director of an outdoor sporting goods store, tries taking charge of his family that is dominated by the women of the house.

name: The Kominsky Method
title: 2018 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: He may be in his twilight years, but aging acting coach Sandy Kominsky isn't ready to ride off into the sunset just yet. The once-famous Kominsky and his longtime agent, Norman Newlander, keep each other laughing as they tackle the curveballs that life throws at them while navigating their later years in Los Angeles, a city that values youth and beauty. The Netflix original sitcom has a strong Hollywood pedigree; it was created by multiple Emmy winner Chuck Lorre and stars Oscar winners Michael Douglas and Alan Arkin as Kominsky and Newlander, respectively.

name: Grace and Frankie
title: 2015 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 7 seasons
description: For as long as they can recall, Grace and Frankie have been rivals. Their one-upmanship comes crashing to a halt, however, when they learn that their husbands have fallen in love with each other and want to get married. As everything around the ladies is coming apart, the only thing they can really rely on is each other. This Netflix original re-teams Jane Fonda and Lily Tomlin ("9 to 5") as Grace and Frankie, respectively, bringing their chemistry to the small screen. It's a casting reunion on a grand scale, as Tomlin is reunited with her co-star from "The West Wing," Martin Sheen, who plays Grace's husband, Robert. And Fonda is back with Sam Waterston, her co-star from "The Newsroom," who plays Frankie's husband, Sol.

name: One Day at a Time
title: 2017 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 4 seasons
description: A Cuban-American family comprising three generations learns to love and laugh as its members deal with various problems and situations.

name: Family Reunion
title: 2019 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: A family struggles to make the transition from life in Seattle to Georgia, where the extended family lives.

name: Season of the Witch
title: 2011 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 35m
description: In the 14th century CE, a Crusader, Behmen, sees that Austria has been devastated by the Black Death. The church blames a witch for the ruin and orders him to send her to a monastery to purify her.

name: Hansel & Gretel: Witch Hunters
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 28m
description: Hansel and Gretel are bounty hunters who track down witches for a living. They are tasked with rescuing the children who have been abducted by witches to be sacrificed on Blood Moon night.

name: Van Helsing
title: 2004 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 2h 11m
description: Van Helsing, a legendary monster hunter, travels to Transylvania with his sidekick in order to kill Dracula and protect the last surviving member of the ancient Romanian family.

name: Atomic Twister
title: 2002 ‧ Thriller/Action
description: When tornadoes strike a nuclear plant, its cooling system gets disrupted dangerously, triggering the possibility of a calamitous meltdown. The lives of people living close to the plant are at stake.

name: Night of the Twisters
title: 1996 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 1h 32m
description: Thriller about a series of destructive tornados and the people who work together to save the community in their wake. A man and his stepson find that their turbulent relationship is tested when tornados hit town. When the full force of the twisters hits, the young man leads his stepbrother and best friend to safety, before setting off on a dangerous mission to find missing family members.

name: Tornado Alley
title: 2011 ‧ Documentary/Drama ‧ 43 mins
description: Tornado Alley documents two unprecedented missions seeking to encounter one of Earth’s most awe-inspiring events—the birth of a tornado. Filmmaker Sean Casey’s personal quest to capture the birth of a tornado with a 70mm camera takes viewers on a breathtaking journey into the heart of the storm. A team of equally driven scientists, the VORTEX2 researchers, experience the relentless strength of nature’s elemental forces as they literally surround tornadoes and the supercell storms that form them, gathering the most comprehensive severe weather data ever collected.

name: Twister
title: 1996 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 53m
description: Jo Harding is a meteorologist on the brink of divorce from her husband, Bill. Before separating, they team up to develop a weather alert system by putting themselves in the paths of violent tornadoes.

name: Armageddon
title: 1998 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 2h 31m
description: NASA astronauts observe that a large asteroid will hit earth in the next eighteen days and destroy life. They realise that their only hope of survival is Harry Stamper, an oil driller.

name: Twisters
title: 2024 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 2m
description: Haunted by a devastating encounter with a tornado, Kate Cooper gets lured back to the open plains by her friend, Javi, to test a groundbreaking new tracking system. She soon crosses paths with Tyler Owens, a charming but reckless social-media superstar who thrives on posting his storm-chasing adventures. As storm season intensifies, Kate, Tyler and their competing teams find themselves in a fight for their lives as multiple systems converge over central Oklahoma.

name: The Day After Tomorrow
title: 2004 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 2h 4m
description: When a sudden worldwide storm begins to plunge the entire planet into a new ice age, paleoclimatologist Jack Hall undertakes a dangerous trek to New York City to save his son from the disaster.

name: Speed
title: 1994 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 56m
description: A disgruntled, dangerous man plants a bomb in an elevator. When his mission fails, he plants a bomb in a local bus and threatens to set it off unless his demand is met.

name: The Tuskegee Airmen
title: 1995 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 46m
description: Hannibal Lee and his fellow pilots overcome racist opposition to become a reputed group of US airmen in the Second World War.

name: Catch-22
title: 2019 ‧ War ‧ 1 season
description: During WWII, Yossarian, a US Army Air Forces bombardier, makes plans to get himself relieved from work. To achieve this, he decides to make use of Catch-22, a hilarious rule on insanity.

name: Generation War: Our Mothers, Our Fathers
title: 2013 ‧ War ‧ 1 season
description: Five friends from Berline WW2 separate them, they were thinking that it's just a period of time and they will be back together again. Many incredible experiences, hardships and horrors of war will ch

name: Grant
title: 2020 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: "Grant" is the quintessentially American story of a humble man who overcomes incredible obstacles to rise to the highest ranks of power. With a seamless blend of dramatic scenes, expert commentary and enhanced archival imagery, this three-part miniseries uncovers the true legacy of the unlikely hero who led the nation during its greatest tests, including the Civil War and Reconstruction. Grant reunifies a fractured nation, battles the KKK and emerges as a champion for civil rights and equality for all Americans.

name: World War II: From the Frontlines
title: 2023 ‧ 1 season
description: Through enhanced archival footage and voices from all sides of the conflict, this docuseries brings WWII to life like never before.

name: The Man in the High Castle
title: 2015 ‧ History ‧ 4 seasons
description: This series, loosely based Philip K. Dick's novel of the same name, takes a look at what the world might look like had the outcome of World War II turned out differently. In this dystopian scenario, the Axis powers won the war, leading to the United States being divided into three parts, an area controlled by the Japanese, a Nazi-controlled section, and a buffer zone between the two. Despite the oppression, a new hope emerges when films turn up that seem to show a different world. A woman believes the films contain the key to freedom and is determined to find their mysterious guardian.

name: The Bloody Hundredth
title: 2024 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1h 2m
description: Chronicling the true stories of the WWII airmen who belonged to the 100th Bomb Group; the real-life heros who inspired the TV series, "Masters of the Air," share their harrowing experiences; narrated by Tom Hanks and featuring Steven Spielberg.

name: The Passing Bells
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: This drama tells the story of the conflict of World War I as it unfolds, through the eyes of two ordinary young men. `The Passing Bells' follows wide-eyed Thomas and stubborn Michael over the course of five years as they grow up, lose friends and find love all amidst the horror of the battle. Before the war, Thomas is a small-town 17-year-old who secretly signs up for the military as an act of rebellion against his parents. The conflict, however, takes its toll on him through the years and he needs to muster up all of his courage to get himself through it and return to his loved ones back home. Michael, the son of a farmer, dreams of adventure, heroism and impressing girlfriend Katie, who he wants to marry. During the battle, he struggles to cope with the losses he endures and shuts out everything around him to focus on getting back to Katie and the life that he left when he entered the war. On the homefront, the guys' families anxiously await word from the front lines.

name: 37 Days
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Take a look at the details of all that took place weeks before the beginning of World War I.

name: The Great War
title: 1964 ‧ Documentary ‧ 2 seasons
description: Archive footage and interviews with veterans tells the story of World War One.

name: 14 - Diaries of the Great War
title: 2014 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: When war broke out in Europe in July 1914, people on all sides believed it would be over by Christmas. Little could they know just how wrong they were. A look at WWI through the scope of unpublished letters and journals.

name: Gallipoli
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Seventeen-year-old Thomas `Tolly' Johnson lies about his age to enlist with his brother in the Great War and finds himself at Gallipoli, caught up in the key battles that shaped the ANZAC legend.

name: Home Fires
title: 2015 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Follows the lives of six women in rural Cheshire who are deeply affected by the Second World War and try to cope up with the trauma of being away from their loved ones.

name: Our World War
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Soldiers fight to protect their country from the enemy in World War I and overcome several challenges on the battlefield which scar them for life.

name: Island at War
title: 2004 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Drama set against the historical events of the occupation of the Channel Islands during World War Two. The islands - including the fictional setting for our story, the island of St Gregory - were occupied at the beginning of June 1940.

name: My Mother and Other Strangers
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A small rural community in Northern Ireland struggle to come to terms with the influx of American soldiers when a US Army Air Force base is set up in the middle of the neighbourhood.

name: Transatlantic
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: An American journalist, during 13 months spent in France in 1940-41, manages to arrange safe passage out of France and on to the US for more than 2000 refugees who are in danger of losing their lives.

name: War and Remembrance
title: 1988 ‧ History ‧ 1 season
description: Emperor Yung Ching wants his fourth son to succeed him but Wan Sin and Chow King On are against his decision, so they get him kidnapped. Later, when he is rescued by Chiang, he becomes evil.

name: The Winds of War
title: 1983 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Victor Henry, a Naval officer and a close confidant of President Roosevelt, undergoes various life-changing experiences in his personal and professional life during the early years of World War II.

name: War & Peace
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: As Napoleon Bonaparte's conflict with Russia reaches its peak, a few members of five aristocratic families foresee their lives changing forever.

name: The Crimson Field
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A team of doctors, nurses and women volunteers work together in a tented field hospital to heal the bodies and souls of men wounded in the Great War. Staff numbers are low and the volunteers are desperately needed, yet there are some who see the women as more of a threat than a lifeline, making the daily battle to keep the war machine churning all the more daunting. For volunteer nurses Kitty Trevelyan, Flora Marshall and Rosalie Berwick, it becomes clear that no training could have prepared them for this work, but a breath of fresh air soon arrives at the hospital in the form of Sister Joan Livesey, a disarming and spirited nurse with a decided mischievous edge.

name: The Long Road Home
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: The First Cavalry Division of the US army gets ambushed during the siege of the Sadr City in Baghdad. The family of the soldiers wait for more than 48 hours to get updates of the war.

name: The Unit
title: 2006 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: A secret US military group conducts covert operations across the world. While the agents face several life-threatening situations during missions, their spouses try to keep their work confidential.

name: John Adams
title: 2008 ‧ History ‧ 1 season
description: The series revolves around the life of the second President of the United States of America, John Adams and traces his formative years and the first fifty years of USA's development.

name: Baghdad ER
title: 2006 ‧ Documentary/War ‧ 1h 4m
description: Baghdad ER is a documentary released by HBO on May 21, 2006. It shows the Iraq War from the perspective of a military hospital in Baghdad.

name: War Sailor
title: 2022 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 30m
description: Merchant sailors are caught in the middle of the Atlantic Ocean during Germany's invasion of Norway and hijacked into working for the Allied war effort.

name: Sharpe's Peril
title: 2008 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 42m
description: Sharpe is asked to lead an army of soldiers who belong to the East India Company when a bandit attack kills their officer, while travelling in a goods train.

name: Spearhead
title: 1978 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Michael Billington, Stafford Gordon and Lawrence Davidson star in this tough and gripping 1970s drama series about life in the British Army.

name: Ultimate Force
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Sergeant Henno Garvie and his team are part of missions that put their lives on the line in a bid to save the nation. When an operation goes wrong, they find themselves pushed to extreme limits.

name: Hornblower: The Even Chance
title: 1998 ‧ War/Adventure ‧ 1h 33m
description: Young Hornblower (Ioan Gruffudd) joins the British navy and encounters a bully who challenges him to a duel.

name: Soldier Soldier
title: 1991 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: The life of the officers and men of the King's Fusiliers infantry regiment, at home and at battle. Featuring the daily lives of a group of soldiers in 'B' Company, 1st Battalion The King's Fusiliers.

name: Cadfael
title: 1994 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: A monk, formally a crusader but now an herbalist in charge of the gardens of Shrewsbury Abbey, is often called upon to solve mysterious crimes around the country.

name: Star Trek: Deep Space Nine
title: 1993 ‧ Sci-fi ‧ 7 seasons
description: A Starfleet crew stationed at Deep Space Nine discovers a wormhole that is home to powerful aliens. They are tasked with guarding it while also dealing with threats coming their way.

name: Dad's Army
title: 1968 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 9 seasons
description: During World War II, George Mainwaring, a bank manager, appoints himself as the leader of the local Home Guard contingent comprised of regular town folk too old to join the British Army.

name: Spooks
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 10 seasons
description: MI5, a clandestine counter-terrorism division of the British security service, faces several challenges as the members work round the clock in order to safeguard the nation.

name: Danger UXB
title: 1979 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: The great Blitz has taken London by surprise. A young Royal Engineer Officer finds himself posted to a Bomb Disposal Company to combat the hundreds of unexploded bombs in London.

name: Father Ted
title: 1995 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: Three priests try to work together and manage the parish on Craggy Island after the bishop banished them for their actions in the past.

name: Red Cap
title: 2003 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Following the exploits of the Special Investigation Branch, a detective charged with one of the most demanding of all military jobs: the investigation of serious crimes committed by, or against, members of the British Army.

name: Sea Patrol
title: 2007 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: As the hard-working crew members of a boat patrol the northern sea border of Australia, they face issues regarding immigration, illegal fishing as well as trafficking of drugs and people.

name: London's Burning
title: 1988 ‧ Drama ‧ 14 seasons
description: Heroic firefighters of the Blue Watch at the Blackwall fire station in London risk their lives to rescue those caught in fire hazards.

name: Merseybeat
title: 2001 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Following the personal and professional lives of one shift of police officers from Newton Park police station in Merseyside.

name: Rose and Maloney
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Two investigators working for the Criminal Justice Review Agency take on claims of miscarriages of justice, assessing whether there are grounds to reopen old cases.

name: Bluestone 42
title: 2013 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: This comedy drama about a British bomb disposal detachment details the camaraderie and bonds shared between the soldiers in the unit as they risk their lives defusing bombs. Among the soldiers in the unit are Captain Nick Medhurst, the wisecracking leader of the team; Nick's eager second in command, Corporal Christian "Millsy" Mills; Corporal Lynda Bird, who just wants to be one of the guys; and Lance Corporal Simon Lansley whose one job is to protect Nick but has bigger ambitions - to become an officer.

name: Soldier of Fortune, Inc.
title: 1997 ‧ Action ‧ 2 seasons
description: S.O.F. is a secret team of military specialists, who takes on the most secretive and dangerous of missions. Team members include leader Major Matthew Q. Shepherd, weapons expert Benny Riddle and espionage specialist Margo Vincent.

name: Prime Suspect 1973
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: The life of Jane Tennison changes when her career in the police force is welcomed with sexism and chauvinistic behaviours as she tries to solve the murder of a young female escort.

name: Fatherland
title: 1994 ‧ Thriller/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 46m
description: In a world ruled by the Nazis, a detective and a journalist discover evidence of the genocide by Hitler and set out to stop the United States from forging an alliance with Germany.

name: The Ipcress File
title: 1965 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 49m
description: Harry Palmer, a secret agent for the British government, deals with the bureaucracy of his own agency while investigating the sudden brainwashing of a group of British scientists.

name: Conspiracy
title: 2001 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 1h 36m
description: A body of officials belonging to the Nazi government of Adolf Hitler meet at the Wannsee Conference in 1942 to implement the last phase of the Holocaust.

name: Control
title: 2007 ‧ Musical/Drama ‧ 2h 2m
description: Biography of Ian Curtis, the enigmatic singer of Joy Division whose personal, professional, and romantic troubles led him to commit suicide at the age of 23.

name: Plebs
title: 2013 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: Marcus, Stylax and their slave Grumio go about their daily life in ancient Rome while trying to get girlfriends, hold down their jobs and climb the social ladder.

name: Twenty Twelve
title: 2011 ‧ Sport ‧ 2 seasons
description: The show follows the trials and hardships that the members of the Olympic Deliverance Commission have to undergo while preparing to organise the 2012 London Olympics.

name: W1A
title: 2014 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: Ian Fletcher, the Head of the Olympic Deliverance Commission, becomes the Head of Values at BBC. He takes care of the functions and purposes of the BBC.

name: Rise of the Nazis
title: 2019 ‧ History ‧ 4 seasons
description: Historians and experts provide an in-depth look into the life and mind of Adolf Hitler, who led the Nazi Party to rise to power in the 1930s, and the crimes committed during his reign.

name: Pompeii: The New Dig
title: 2024 ‧ 1 season
description: The excavation of an entire block of the city, unearthing what life was like before the eruption and the horror faced by the victims, and those who survived, when Vesuvius erupted in AD 79.

name: Blood Diamond
title: 2006 ‧ Thriller/Adventure ‧ 2h 23m
description: Solomon is abducted and forced to work in diamond mines, where he finds a priceless diamond and hides it. When Danny learns of it, he promises to help him find his family in exchange for the diamond.

name: Spy Game
title: 2001 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 2h 6m
description: When Nathan, a CIA operative, learns that his friend is incarcerated in China, he takes it upon himself to free them from the Chinese enslavers.

name: Special Forces
title: 2003 ‧ Action/War ‧ 1h 33m
description: After an American journalist is caught by a group of terrorists, the US sends a Special Forces Team to rescue her.

name: Guy Ritchie's The Covenant
title: 2023 ‧ Action/War ‧ 2h 3m
description: During the war in Afghanistan, a local interpreter risks his own life to carry an injured sergeant across miles of gruelling terrain.

name: Rambo
title: 2008 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 32m
description: John, a former US soldier who fought in Vietnam, is haunted by the unpleasant memories of war. An incident with a small-town sheriff flips a switch within him, which triggers his violent side.

name: First They Killed My Father
title: 2017 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 2h 16m
description: At the dawn of the Khmer Rouge in Cambodia, Loung Ung, a five-year-old girl, and her family decide to flee and take shelter in camps. Soon, when her father is executed, the horrors begin to intensify.

name: Johnny Mad Dog
title: 2008 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 38m
description: An African teen (Christophe Minie) leads a band of young fighters on a bloody rampage through local villages.

name: Hotel Rwanda
title: 2004 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 2h 1m
description: Paul Rusesabagina, a hotel manager, leads a happy life with his wife and children in Rwanda. He displays immense courage by saving the lives of many helpless refugees during a communal war.

name: All Quiet on the Western Front
title: 2022 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 27m
description: War breaks out in Germany in 1914. Paul Bäumer and his classmates quickly enlist in the army to serve their fatherland. No sooner are they drafted than the first images from the battlefield show them the reality of war.

name: Shooting Dogs
title: 2005 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 55m
description: In 1994 Rwanda, simmering tensions between Hutus and Tutsis boil over into full-scale genocide. Two men, a priest named Father Christopher (John Hurt) and British schoolteacher Joe Connor (Hugh Dancy), get caught up in the conflict and stay behind to help those who seek shelter at the Ecole Technique Officielle.

name: Donnie Brasco
title: 1997 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 27m
description: An undercover FBI agent infiltrates one of the five crime families in New York and rises through the ranks quickly in order to bring it down for good.

name: Eastern Promises
title: 2007 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 40m
description: Anna Khitrova, a midwife, finds a diary of Tatiana, a teenage pregnant girl who died during her childbirth. Anna senses a mystery attached to Tatiana's death and that prompts her to read the diary.

name: Judas and the Black Messiah
title: 2021 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 6m
description: William O'Neal, a petty criminal, is tasked by the FBI to infiltrate the Illinois chapter of the Black Panther Party. Further, he must get close to and provide intelligence on Fred Hampton.

name: The World's Fastest Indian
title: 2005 ‧ Sport/Adventure ‧ 2h 7m
description: New Zealander Burt Munro is a motorcycle enthusiast who spends years rebuilding and perfecting a 1920 Indian motorcycle. Eventually, he puts everything on the line and sets a land speed world record.

name: Hostiles
title: 2017 ‧ Western/Adventure ‧ 2h 15m
description: After fighting for more than two decades against the Cheyenne forces, an army captain, Joseph, is forced to escort the ailing Cheyenne leader to safety.

name: True Grit
title: 2010 ‧ Western/Adventure ‧ 1h 50m
description: Mattie, a teenager, seeks revenge on Tom, who murdered her father. She convinces Rooster Cogburn, a ruthless hunter, to assist her in finding Tom. They develop a special bonding during the manhunt.

name: Dances with Wolves
title: 1990 ‧ Western/Adventure ‧ 3h 56m
description: Lt John J Dunbar is assigned to a western Civil War outpost following a serious injury. In his new surroundings, his life changes when he meets the Lakota tribe of American Indians.

name: Beasts of No Nation
title: 2015 ‧ 2h 17m
description: A young Agu's life changes for the worse when war strikes his village and his family is massacred. Later, he is forced to join a rebel faction and become a cold-blooded killer.

name: 94 Terror
title: 2018 ‧ 1h 46m
description: 94 Terror is a 2018 Ugandan war-drama film set in the Rwandan genocide of 1994. The film premiered on 14 December 2018 at a red carpet event at Theatre Labonita in Kampala and won Best Viewers' Choice Movie Award at the 2018 Uganda Film Festival Awards in the first week after the release.

name: A Sunday in Kigali
title: 2006 ‧ 1h 58m
description: A disillusioned journalist falls in love with a young Rwandan woman, but civil war separates them.

name: The Trial of the Chicago 7
title: 2020 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 9m
description: The film is based on the infamous 1969 trial of seven defendants charged by the federal government with conspiracy and more, arising from the countercultural protests in Chicago at the 1968 Democratic National Convention. The trial transfixed the nation and sparked a conversation about mayhem intended to undermine the U.S. government.

name: The Hurt Locker
title: 2008 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 11m
description: Sergeant William James is tasked with training a bomb disposal team during the Iraq War. But his ideologies and reckless approach towards the job gives rise to conflicts with his subordinates.

name: The True Story Of Black Hawk Down
title: 2003 ‧ Documentary/War ‧ 1h 32m
description: On October 3rd, 1993, 120 Delta Force Commandos and Army Rangers were dropped into the heart of Mogadishu, Somalia. Their mission was a fast daylight raid to kidnap lead terrorist Mohammed Farrah Aidid, who had been killing U.N. workers delivering food to starving Somalis. Aidid’s goal was to control the country by controlling all the food.  The mission abruptly changed to a rescue operation. Surrounded by Somali militia, a fierce firefight ensued that left American troops trapped and fighting for their lives. The ordeal left 18 American men dead, 70 wounded, with 3,000 Somalis casualties.  This brilliant documentary tells the true story of "Black Hawk Down" through the memories and voices of the American Special Forces survivors. Also included are Somali militiamen as they recount their harrowing experiences of battle.

name: Greyhound
title: 2020 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 31m
description: U.S. Navy Cmdr. Ernest Krause is assigned to lead an Allied convoy across the Atlantic during World War II. His convoy, however, is pursued by German U-boats. Although this is Krause's first wartime mission, he finds himself embroiled in what would come to be known as the longest, largest and most complex naval battle in history: The Battle of the Atlantic.

name: Pearl Harbor
title: 2001 ‧ War/Romance ‧ 3h 3m
description: Rafe and Daniel, two friends, become army pilots and meet Evelyn, a navy nurse. Rafe and Evelyn fall in love before he is rumoured dead. Evelyn and Daniel eventually develop feelings for each other.

name: Platoon
title: 1986 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2 hours
description: A young American volunteer deals with the horrors of warfare and morally ambiguous politics when he watches the soldiers in his platoon patrol, fight and die in the jungles of Vietnam.

name: World War Z
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 56m
description: Out of nowhere, Gerry, an ex-United Nations employee, finds himself in a race against time as he investigates a threatening virus that turns humans into zombies.

name: Train to Busan
title: 2016 ‧ Action/Horror ‧ 1h 58m
description: Seok-woo and his daughter are on a train to Busan on the latter's birthday to see his wife. However, the journey turns into a nightmare when they are trapped amidst a zombie outbreak in South Korea.

name: The Odd Family: Zombie on Sale
title: 2019 ‧ Comedy/Horror ‧ 1h 52m
description: When a pharmaceutical company's illegal experiments inadvertently create a zombie, the strange Park family finds it and tries to profit from it.

name: Project Wolf Hunting
title: 2022 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 2h 1m
description: A group of police officers fights against dangerous criminals being transferred on a cargo ship bound for Busan, South Korea.

name: Zombieland: Double Tap
title: 2019 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 39m
description: Tallahassee, Columbus, Wichita and Little Rock embark on a mission to slay evolved zombies to protect humanity while struggling with their emotional battles.

name: Zombie School
title: 2014 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 27m
description: At Chilsung school, a lawless school filled with troublemakers, the teachers suddenly turn into zombies and start to attack everyone. The students must band together and survive against the horde of zombie teachers.

name: The Hidden Face
title: 2011 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 43m
description: Adrian, an orchestra conductor, is distraught after his girlfriend Belen leaves him. Things take a turn for the worse when his new live-in girlfriend Fabiana discovers a key and hears tapping sounds.

name: Marshland
title: 2014 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 45m
description: Pedro and Juan, two detectives, who share different ideologies, need to put their differences aside and hunt down a serial killer who mercilessly kills women.

name: The Best Offer
title: 2013 ‧ Thriller/Romance ‧ 2h 11m
description: Virgil Oldman, a wealthy art auctioneer, takes the help of a young artificer, Robert, to understand and woo Claire Ibbetson, a young heiress, who hires him to auction off an antique collection.

name: The Invisible Guest
title: 2016 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 46m
description: Adrian Doria finds himself in trouble when he becomes the key suspect in the murder of his girlfriend. He hires a famous defence lawyer and together they try to figure out a way to clear his name.

name: Door Lock
title: 2018 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 43m
description: Kyung Min, a young woman who lives alone in a studio apartment, finds herself in a dangerous situation when she discovers someone trying to enter her home.

name: The Loved Ones
title: 2009 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 24m
description: In order to avoid a ghostly figure in the road, Brent Mitchell wraps his car around a tree, killing his father. While his mother goes to pieces, Brent escapes into a marijuana fuelled world of pain and guilt.

name: The Secret in Their Eyes (El secreto de sus ojos)
title: 2009 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 9m
description: Benjamin Esposito is a retired legal counsellor who is working on a novel centred around murders that occurred years ago in Buenos Aries. Twenty years later, the unresolved case still haunts him.

name: Backyard
title: 2009 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 2m
description: Officer Blanca Bravo (Ana de la Reguera) arrives in Juarez, Mexico -- a grim nexus of corporate colonialism and sexual tourism -- to investigate a rash of killings targeting female migrant workers. But with no help from the locals, bringing the responsible parties to justice becomes a frustrating exercise. As Bravo rails against indifference and local corruption, she finds herself on a collision course with Mickey Santos (Jimmy Smits), a Mexican mogul with a taste for young prostitutes.

name: We Need to Talk About Kevin
title: 2011 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 52m
description: Eva, a single mother, has a strained relationship with her son Kevin, since his childhood. As Kevin grows older, he continues to defy and rebel against Eva.

name: Incendies
title: 2010 ‧ War/Mystery ‧ 2h 10m
description: A dying mother writes to her children Jeanne and Simon requesting them to fulfil her last wishes. Following her instructions, they discover a world full of hatred, differences and love.

name: Seven Blessings
title: 2023 ‧ Drama/Comedy ‧ 1h 51m
description: Marie travels from France to Israel, where her family now lives, to marry her one true love. A week of festive meals honor the bride, but old wounds are reopened.

name: The Crimson Rivers
title: 2000 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 46m
description: Two French cops, investigating separate murders, find a common link between the killings. As more murders occur, the two find an increasing number of horrific details pointing to a conspiracy.

name: Alien (1979)
title: 1979 ‧ Sci-fi/Horror ‧ 1h 57m
description: The crew of a spacecraft, Nostromo, intercept a distress signal from a planet and set out to investigate it. However, to their horror, they are attacked by an alien which later invades their ship.

name: From Hell
title: 2001 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 2h 2m
description: As political turmoil and a royal scandal destabilise England, the brutal murders of prostitutes in East London terrorise the citizens. Inspector Frederick finds himself probing the complex case.

name: Crimson Rivers II: Angels of the Apocalypse
title: 2004 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 40m
description: Called to a French monastery following the appearance of a dead body, Detective Pierre Niemans (Jean Reno) finds himself investigating what appears to be a radical cult killing that's based on obscure passages from the Bible. When fellow detective Reda (Benoît Magimel) shows up, his own murder investigation intertwining with Niemans', it becomes clear that a grand conspiracy is underway, one that spans the globe and reaches all the way back to World War II.

name: Vatel
title: 2000 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 43m
description: France 1671, and with war brewing against Holland, the penniless Prince de Conde invites King Louis XIV to his country chateau for a three-day feast of magnificent proportions. Desperate for a commission as a general the prince wants no expense spared and places Vatel, a man of honour, talent and low rank, in charge of proceedings.

name: Posetioci
title: 1993 ‧ Comedy/Fantasy ‧ 1h 47m
description: After being drugged by a witch, a knight kills the father of his lover, believing him to be a bear. Thereafter, he asks a wizard to send him back in time before the murder but is sent to the future.

name: Vidocq
title: 2001 ‧ Mystery/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 40m
description: Vidocq, a famous detective, disappears without a trace while pursuing a supernatural serial killer. His young biographer Etienne Boisset decides to continue the investigation to uncover the mystery.

name: Among Wolves
title: 2010 ‧ Adventure/Drama ‧ 2 hours
description: A child is sold to a tribe in the remote mountains. However, he manages to survive and lives among a pack of wolves for 12 years.

name: The Last Samurai
title: 2003 ‧ Action/War ‧ 2h 34m
description: An American military officer is ordered to train the first Japanese army in the Western tactics of warfare. However, a samurai tries to stop him from eradicating the traditional fighting techniques.

name: Overlord
title: 2018 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 51m
description: Towards the end of World War II, American paratroopers set out to destroy a German radio tower. Soon enough, things take a murky turn when they come across a vicious secret.

name: Wasabi
title: 2001 ‧ Comedy/Action ‧ 1h 34m
description: Hubert, a French policeman, faces problems with his senior after the latter disapproves of his working style. He goes back to Japan where he finds out why his girlfriend left him years ago.

name: 22 Bullets
title: 2010 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 57m
description: Charly, a retired mobster, lives peacefully with his wife and two children. One day, he is ambushed in a parking lot and left for dead with 22 bullets in his body but he survives and vows revenge.

name: 8 MM : Huit Millimetres
title: 1999 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2h 3m
description: Tom Welles, a private detective, is approached by a wealthy widow, Mrs. Christian, who wants him to determine whether an 8MM film, showing the murder of a girl, is authentic.

name: 36th Precinct
title: 2004 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 51m
description: Two Parisian cops compete for the post of Police Chief and get increasingly ruthless in their attempt to outdo the other, till there seems no difference between them and the criminals they chase.

name: Léon
title: 1994 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 50m
description: After her family is murdered, Mathilda, a 12-year-old girl, is reluctantly taken in by Leon, a professional assassin. Mathilda soon becomes his protege and takes up the assassin's trade.

name: Red Dragon
title: 2002 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 2h 4m
description: Will Graham, a retired FBI agent with special psychological abilities, is assigned a job to capture an enigmatic serial killer. However, he must seek help from his rival, Dr Hannibal Lecter.

name: Blow
title: 2001 ‧ Crime/Crime ‧ 2h 4m
description: After entering the dangerous world of drugs, George Jung decides to become a smuggler. However, when he begins to lose meaningful relationships, he understands the consequences of his decision.

name: What Lies Beneath
title: 2000 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 2h 10m
description: Claire moves with Norman to his old house, where she experiences disturbing supernatural activity. Soon, she discovers a shocking truth about her husband and Madison, his student who is dead.

name: The Three Musketeers: D'artagnan
title: 2023 ‧ Adventure/Action ‧ 2h 1m
description: Young D'Artagnan arrives in Paris, trying to find the attackers who left him for dead. He instead finds a real war brewing and joins the king's three musketeers - Athos, Porthos and Aramis - as they work to ensure the future of France.

name: Oppenheimer
title: 2023 ‧ Thriller/Historical drama ‧ 3 hours
description: During World War II, Lt. Gen. Leslie Groves Jr. appoints physicist J. Robert Oppenheimer to work on the top-secret Manhattan Project. Oppenheimer and a team of scientists spend years developing and designing the atomic bomb. Their work comes to fruition on July 16, 1945, as they witness the world's first nuclear explosion, forever changing the course of history.

name: Free State of Jones
title: 2016 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 19m
description: After serving as a medic in the Civil War, Newton Knight returns home to safeguard his family. Branded as an outlaw deserter, he forms a rebellion against the corrupt Confederate government.

name: Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World
title: 2003 ‧ Adventure/War ‧ 2h 18m
description: In May 1805, during the Napoleonic Wars, British Captain Jack Aubrey of HMS Surprise orders his team to drown, seize or char the French privateer Acheron. But he realises soon that the task is tough.

name: Modigliani
title: 2004 ‧ Drama ‧ 2h 8m
description: Amedeo Modigliani, an Italian artist, decides to enter a painting competition to win money and marry the girl of his dreams. However, things take an unusual turn after he is mugged and left for dead.

name: Anatomy of a Fall
title: 2023 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 32m
description: A woman is suspected of her husband's murder, and their blind son faces a moral dilemma as the sole witness.

name: Io Capitano
title: 2023 ‧ Adventure/Drama ‧ 2h 1m
description: Longing for a brighter future, two Senegalese teenagers embark on a journey from West Africa to Italy. However, between their dreams and reality lies a labyrinth of checkpoints, the Sahara Desert, and the vast waters of the Mediterranean.

name: Perfect Days
title: 2023 ‧ Drama/Narrative ‧ 2h 5m
description: Hirayama feels content with his life as a toilet cleaner in Tokyo. Outside of his structured routine, he cherishes music on cassette tapes, reads books and takes photos. Through unexpected encounters, he reflects on finding beauty in the world.

name: There’s Still Tomorrow
title: 2023 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 58m
description: In postwar Rome, a working-class woman dreams of a better future for herself and her daughter while enduring abuse at the hands of her husband. When a mysterious letter arrives, she discovers the courage to change the circumstances of her life.

name: Inside Out
title: 2015 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 35m
description: Eleven-year-old Riley has moved to San Francisco, leaving behind her life in Minnesota. She and her five core emotions, Fear, Anger, Joy, Disgust and Sadness, struggle to cope with her new life.

name: Inside Out 2
title: 2024 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 36m
description: Joy, Sadness, Anger, Fear and Disgust have been running a successful operation by all accounts. However, when Anxiety shows up, they aren't sure how to feel.

name: Frida
title: 2002 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 3m
description: A renowned and talented artist with a revolutionary personality has an unstable relationship with her husband and an extramarital affair at the same time.

name: Love Actually
title: 2003 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 2h 15m
