description: The film narrates the story of eight couples, of mix-bag ages and walks of life, who encounter love in their own special ways; all this in the beautiful days leading up to Christmas in London.

name: The Lost City
title: 2005 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 24m
description: Castro's Communist Revolution sweeps through Cuba, catching an apolitical Havana club owner in the middle and dividing his family.

name: Time Bandits
title: 1981 ‧ Fantasy/Adventure ‧ 1h 56m
description: Kevin, an 11-year-old boy, gets the chance to time-travel with a group of dwarves. He tags along with them as they jump from era to era in search of treasure to steal.

name: The Brave
title: 1997 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 2h 3m
description: A mysterious stranger makes an intriguing offer to a man recently released from prison, providing him with an opportunity to help his family who have been struggling to make ends meet.

name: Finding Vivian Maier
title: 2013 ‧ Documentary/Thriller ‧ 1h 23m
description: A look at the life and career of nanny Vivian Maier and her unbelievable collections of 100,000 photographs.

name: Jeanne du Barry
title: 2023 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 56m
description: Jeanne uses her charms and intelligence to climb the social ladder step by step. She becomes one of the favourites of King Louis XV and falls madly in love. Against all convention, Jeanne moves to Versailles.

name: Dark Waters
title: 2019 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2h 6m
description: Robert, a defence lawyer, goes up against a corporation to stop it from polluting a water source and endangering the lives of the people. However, he is forced to jeopardise his life to expose them.

name: McCullin
title: 2012 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1h 35m
description: The life and work of British war photographer Don McCullin, who discusses his career documenting conflicts and humanitarian disasters over three decades.

name: War Photographer
title: 2001 ‧ Documentary/War ‧ 1h 36m
description: For over 20 years, photojournalist James Nachtwey has been visiting war-torn countries such as Kosovo and Rwanda, capturing the destruction on film. While merely an observer, he still feels the immediate effects of the ravaged lands. The stark images are contrasted by Nachtwey's calm reserve as he fends off accusations of exploiting tragedy. Director Christian Frei attaches a small video camera to Nachtwey's still camera for a bird's-eye view of destruction, pain, and ultimately, hope.

name: Kodachrome
title: 2017 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 45m
description: Matt and his father, who is terminally ill, embark on a road trip to Kansas to process a Kodachrome film before Kodak's last laboratory shuts down permanently.

name: Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl
title: 2003 ‧ Adventure/Fantasy ‧ 2h 23m
description: Will, a blacksmith, joins forces with Captain Jack Sparrow, a pirate, to rescue the love of his life from Jack's associates, who have kidnapped her suspecting she has his medallion.

name: Chocolat
title: 2000 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 2h 1m
description: A woman and her daughter open a chocolate shop in a conservative village in France, much to the villagers' disapproval. Over time, they win the people's hearts and also help them with their troubles.

name: Before Night Falls
title: 2000 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 15m
description: Arenas manages to break free from the norms of the society by openly declaring about his sexual orientation. This lands him in trouble and Arenas gets arrested on the charge of assaulting minors.

name: Callas Forever
title: 2002 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 55m
description: Maria, an opera singer, tasted success early in her singing career. However, at the end of her long career, she struggled to maintain the pitch of her voice, and decides to give her career a push.

name: Dead Man
title: 1995 ‧ Western/Fantasy ‧ 2h 1m
description: Having murdered a man, William Blake, an accountant, is on the run. Later, he meets a man who calls himself Nobody who eventually leads him on the path of spirituality.

name: Geronimo: An American Legend
title: 1993 ‧ Western/Action ‧ 1h 55m
description: After Apache Indians reluctantly agree to settle on a US government reservation, they face problems as life is nothing as they were promised. One man forms a team and fights against the government.

name: Last Night of Amore
title: 2023 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 11m
description: Franco Amore, who has been an exemplary policeman throughout his career, is about to retire. However, just before he hangs up his badge, he agrees to do a favour for a Chinese mafioso in exchange for €5,000.

name: Pride & Prejudice
title: 2005 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 2h 7m
description: Elizabeth Bennett is a strong-willed yet sensible young woman. At a local ball, she encounters a wealthy young man, Mr Fitzwilliam Darcy, who is arrogant, and they develop an unusual relationship.

name: Basquiat
title: 1996 ‧ Drama/Indie film ‧ 1h 50m
description: The story of Jean-Michel Basquiat, a struggling street artist, whose meteoric rise to fame could not prevent his personal demons and heroin addiction from taking his life.

name: All of Us Strangers
title: 2023 ‧ Fantasy/Romance ‧ 1h 45m
description: One night in his near-empty London tower block, screenwriter Adam has a chance encounter with mysterious neighbor Harry, puncturing the rhythm of his everyday life. As a relationship develops between them, Adam finds himself drawn back to his childhood home, where his parents appear to be living just as they were on the day they died 30 years ago.

name: Origin
title: 2023 ‧ Drama/History ‧ 2h 21m
description: Author Isabel Wilkerson writes her seminal book "Caste: The Origins of Our Discontents" while coping with personal tragedy.

name: Sing Sing
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 47m
description: Based on the true story of a man imprisoned at Sing Sing for a crime he didn't commit. When joined by a wary outsider, he finds purpose staging an original comedy with a theater group of other incarcerated men.

name: Shadow of the Vampire
title: 2000 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 32m
description: F. W. Murnau (John Malkovich) is struggling to create his silent classic "Nosferatu" on location in Eastern Europe. The director is obsessed with making this the most authentic vampire movie ever. To that end, Murnau has employed a real vampire, Max Schreck (Willem Dafoe), explaining to the crew that he is the ultimate of that new breed, the "method actor" -- trained by Stanislavsky himself. Schreck will appear only in character and only at night.

name: Living in Oblivion
title: 1995 ‧ Comedy/Indie film ‧ 1h 32m
description: Nick, an indie filmmaker, tries to make a low-budget movie. However, he faces numerous difficulties on the set due to his cast and crew members.

name: In the Mouth of Madness
title: 1994 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 35m
description: When horror novelist Sutter Cane (Jürgen Prochnow) goes missing, insurance investigator John Trent (Sam Neill) scrutinizes the claim made by his publisher, Jackson Harglow (Charlton Heston), and endeavors to retrieve a yet-to-be-released manuscript and ascertain the writer's whereabouts. Accompanied by the novelist's editor, Linda Styles (Julie Carmen), and disturbed by nightmares from reading Cane's other novels, Trent makes an eerie nighttime trek to a supernatural town in New Hampshire.

name: Girl, Interrupted
title: 1999 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 2h 7m
description: A directionless teenager, Susanna, is rushed to Claymoore, a mental institution, after a supposed suicide attempt. There, she befriends a group of troubled women who deeply influence her life.

name: Corpse Bride
title: 2005 ‧ Family/Fantasy ‧ 1h 17m
description: A shy young man inadvertently brings a deceased woman to life when he practises his wedding vows near her grave. Trouble ensues when she thinks he is married to her.

name: Bless the Child
title: 2000 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 47m
description: When Maggie's sister Jenna saddles her with an autistic newborn named Cody she touches Maggie's heart and becomes the daughter she has always longed for. But six years later Jenna suddenly re-enters her life and, with her mysterious new husband, Eric Stark, abducts Cody. Despite the fact that Maggie has no legal rights to Cody, FBI agent John Travis, takes up her cause when he realizes that Cody shares the same birth date as several other recently missing children.

name: Ligabue
title: 1977 ‧ Drama ‧ 3h 20m
description: Ligabue is a 1978 Italian biographical drama film directed by Salvatore Nocita. It depicts real life events of painter Antonio Ligabue. It is based on a book by Cesare Zavattini. For this film Nocita was awarded Nastro d'Argento for Best New Director, while Flavio Bucci won the Nastro d'Argento for Best Actor.

name: National Treasure (Skarb narodów)
title: 2004 ‧ Adventure/Action ‧ 2h 25m
description: Action movie a bout a treasure hunter who is in hot pursuit of a mythical treasure that has been passed down for centuries, while his employer turned enemy is onto the same path that he is on.

name: Night at the Museum: Battle of the Smithsonian
title: 2009 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 45m
description: Larry, the security guard of the Smithsonian Institution Museum, must gain access to the museum in order to rescue Jedediah and Octavius, who have been shipped to the museum by mistake.

name: Live Free or Die Hard
title: 2007 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 9m
description: The Director of FBI's Cyber Crime Division assigns John McClane the task of tracking down a hacker. John ends up working with Thomas, an ethical hacker who helps him deal with the cyber criminals.

name: The Charlemagne Code
title: 2008 ‧ Adventure/Action ‧ 2 hours
description: Adventurers race around Germany to find a legendary treasure.

name: The Da Vinci Code
title: 2006 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2h 29m
description: Symbologist Robert Langdon travels from Paris to London to unravel a bizarre murder. Accompanied by a cryptographer, he soon comes across a religious enigma protected by an age-old secret society.

name: Sherlock Holmes
title: 2009 ‧ Action/Mystery ‧ 2h 8m
description: Detective Sherlock Holmes and his partner, Dr Watson, send Blackwood, a serial killer, to the gallows. However, they are shocked to learn that he is back from the dead and must pursue him again.

name: Murder on the Orient Express
title: 2017 ‧ Mystery/Crime ‧ 1h 54m
description: After the Orient Express gets derailed by an avalanche, Edward Ratchett is found dead with multiple stab wounds. Detective Hercule Poirot must solve the case before the killer strikes again.

name: The Two Popes
title: 2019 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 5m
description: Behind Vatican walls, Pope Benedict and the future Pope Francis must face their pasts and find common ground in order to forge a new path for the Catholic Church.

name: Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom
title: 1984 ‧ Adventure/Action ‧ 1h 58m
description: Upon his arrival in India, Indiana Jones, an American adventurer, is asked by the villagers of a remote hamlet to retrieve a mystical stone and rescue young boys kidnapped from the village.

name: Solo: A Star Wars Story
title: 2018 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 15m
description: In a galaxy where hyperfuel is in high demand, Han Solo gets involved in a large-scale heist within the criminal underworld and meets individuals who change his life.

name: Rogue One: A Star Wars Story
title: 2016 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 13m
description: Jyn's father is forcibly taken by the Galactic Empire to help them complete the Death Star. When she grows up, she joins a group of resistance fighters who aim to steal the Empire's blueprints.

name: What If...?
title: 2021 ‧ Action ‧ 2 seasons
description: Reimagining noteworthy events in the Marvel Cinematic Universe and creating a multiverse of infinite possibilities.

name: The Legend of Vox Machina
title: 2022 ‧ Action ‧ 3 seasons
description: Vox Machina, a band of eight unlikely heroes, find themselves on a quest to save the realm of Exandria from dark magical forces.

name: Scott Pilgrim Takes Off
title: 2023 ‧ Action ‧ 1 season
description: After meeting the woman of his dreams, a charming musician finds himself contending with an army of her ex-boyfriends.

name: Love Death + Robots
title: 2019 ‧ Horror ‧ 4 seasons
description: This collection of animated short stories spans several genres, including science fiction, fantasy, horror and comedy. World-class animation creators bring captivating stories to life in the form of a unique and visceral viewing experience. The animated anthology series includes tales that explore alternate histories, life for robots in a post-apocalyptic city and a plot for world domination by super-intelligent yogurt. Among the show's executive producers is Oscar-nominated director David Fincher.

name: Freedom Fighters: The Ray
title: 2017 ‧ Action ‧ 2 seasons
description: Reporter Raymond Terrill is attacked with a genetic light bomb that gives him super powers.

name: Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.: Slingshot
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Following the character of Elena Yo-Yo Rodriguez, an Inhuman with the ability to move with super-speed, as she struggles to balance the restrictions of the recently instituted Sokovia Accords.

name: Banshee
title: 2013 ‧ Action ‧ 4 seasons
description: Lucas Hood, an enigmatic former swindler, assumes the identity of a murdered sheriff. But haunted by his past, he finds it difficult to carry on with his devious criminal activities.

name: Banshee: Origins
title: 2013 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Banshee: Origins is a series of webisodes based on the American drama television series produced by Cinemax called Banshee. The series offers flashbacks in-between the time where Lucas Hood was arrested and when Sheriff Lucas Hood first arrived in Banshee.

name: Reacher
title: 2022 ‧ Action ‧ 2 seasons
description: When retired Military Police Officer Jack Reacher is arrested for a murder he did not commit, he finds himself in the middle of a deadly conspiracy full of dirty cops, shady businessmen, and scheming politicians.

name: Lost: Missing Pieces
title: 2007 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Lost: Missing Pieces is a series of thirteen video clips ranging in length from one to four minutes that aired during the hiatus between the 3rd and 4th seasons of the television show Lost, from which this series is a spin off.

name: Westworld
title: 2016 ‧ Sci-fi ‧ 3 seasons
description: In a futuristic Western-themed amusement park, Westworld, the visitors interact with automatons. However, all hell breaks loose when the robots begin malfunctioning.

name: S.W.A.T.
title: 2017 ‧ Action ‧ 8 seasons
description: Sergeant Daniel and his team from the LAPD fight dangerous criminals and strive to protect the public from the threat they impose.

name: Whiskey Cavalier
title: 2019 ‧ Action ‧ 1 season
description: FBI agent Will Chase is teamed with a CIA operative, Francesca, to lead a team of spies. They must deal with office politics and other distractions as they try to save the world.

name: Chicago P.D.
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 12 seasons
description: Two units of the Chicago Police Department, the Intelligence Unit and a team of uniformed cops, whose strategies distinctly vary, fight against various crimes while battling their personal problems.

name: Animal Kingdom
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: After the death of his mother, Joshua decides to live with his grandmother, who heads a criminal clan. His life takes a turn as he gets involved with his cousins and their criminal activities.

name: Waco: The Aftermath
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Exploring the uneven scales of justice faced by surviving Branch Davidians; tracing the horrific events that fuelled the emerging "Patriot" movement which led to a terrorism act in Oklahoma City.

name: Waco
title: 2018 ‧ History ‧ 1 season
description: The FBI and the ATF raided the Branch Davidian religious compound in Waco, Texas, in 1993. In the ensuing gun-battle, many are killed and numerous others wounded.

name: History's Greatest Escapes with Morgan Freeman
title: 2021 ‧ Crime ‧ 2 seasons
description: The host, Morgan Freeman, a renowned actor, walks through some of the most ingenious and daring breakouts in history from the world's inescapable prisons.

name: Peaky Blinders
title: 2013 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: Tommy Shelby, a dangerous man, leads the Peaky Blinders, a gang based in Birmingham. Soon, Chester Campbell, an inspector, decides to nab him and put an end to the criminal activities.

name: How to Sell Drugs Online (Fast)
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: To impress his former girlfriend, a nerdy teen starts selling drugs online out of his bedroom, and soon becomes one of Europe's biggest dealers.

name: Chernobyl
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: In April 1986, the city of Chernobyl in the Soviet Union suffers one of the worst nuclear disasters in the history of mankind. Consequently, many heroes put their lives on the line to save Europe.

name: Mr. Robot
title: 2015 ‧ Thriller ‧ 4 seasons
description: Elliot, a cyber-security engineer suffering from anxiety, works for a corporation and hacks felons by night. Panic strikes him after Mr Robot, a cryptic anarchist, recruits him to ruin his company.

name: BoJack Horseman
title: 2014 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 6 seasons
description: A humanoid horse, BoJack Horseman -- lost in a sea of self-loathing and booze -- decides it's time for a comeback. Once the star of a '90s sitcom, in which he was the adoptive father of three orphaned kids (two girls and a boy). The show was the hottest thing around, then suddenly, was canceled. Now 18 years later, BoJack wants to regain his dignity. With the aid of a human sidekick and a feline ex-girlfriend who is his agent, he sets out to make it happen. But Hollywood is vastly different from those days, and getting used to stuff like Twitter may take some time. This first animated series from Netflix -- with plenty of references to sex, drugs and alcohol -- is not for the little ones.

name: Alias
title: 2001 ‧ Action ‧ 5 seasons
description: After learning that the agency she works for is a counter-government unit, Sydney Bristow, determines to bring it down and begins to work as a double agent for the CIA.

name: The Night Agent
title: 2023 ‧ Thriller ‧ 2 seasons
description: While monitoring an emergency line, an FBI agent answers a call that plunges him into a deadly conspiracy involving a mole at the White House.

name: Beyond Scared Straight
title: 2011 ‧ Reality ‧ 9 seasons
description: Take a look as at-risk teenagers are placed in a reform programme to veer them away from a life of crime and witness juvenile offenders experience the horrors of life behind bars.

name: Brain Games
title: 2011 ‧ Documentary ‧ 8 seasons
description: Experts in cognitive science, neuroscience and psychology perform experiments and explore various components of the human brain.

name: Better Call Saul Employee Training
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Better Call Saul's Emmy-Award winning Employee Training digital series.

name: Better Call Saul: Madrigal Electromotive Security Training
title: 2018 ‧ Short
description: A series of short training videos done by Mike Ehrmantraut for Madrigal Electromotive employees.

name: Bluff City Law
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Sydney Strait, a brilliant young lawyer, returns to her family's elite law firm in Memphis and works with Elijah, her estranged father, on landmark civil rights cases.

name: In Contempt
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Working for a legal aid office in New York City, Gwen Sullivan fights for clients who can't afford to choose their own attorney. The passion she has for her job and for those she represents has cemented the rebellious and wildly outspoken Sullivan as arguably the most talented public defender in her district. Along with the complicated cases she tackles in a hurried environment, Gwen must also manage various distractions at the office, including working with her ex, newly appointed supervisor Charlie Riggs, whose extraordinary talent in the courtroom is only matched by his outsized ego, and Earl, her stern, hard-to-please father, a former judge.

name: Top Dog
title: 2020 ‧ Thriller ‧ 2 seasons
description: A mysterious disappearance causes an ambitious lawyer to enter into an unorthodox collaboration with a recently released convict; she wants to secure her future, and he wants to leave his old life behind.

name: Dahmer – Monster: The Jeffrey Dahmer Story
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: With access to hundreds of pages of police and FBI transcripts and personal testimony from family, friends, and survivors, the haunting story of how Jeffrey Dahmer went from shy adolescent to a notorious serial killer and cannibal is revealed.

name: Bates Motel
title: 2013 ‧ Horror ‧ 5 seasons
description: Norman Bates's life spins out of control when his mental health deteriorates. Meanwhile, his mother, Norma, tries to get him the help he needs and protects him from the people around them.

name: Crisis on Infinite Earths
title: Arrowverse
description: When the Anti-Monitor unleashes his wrath on the multiverse and begins to destroy various Earths, the world's greatest heroes must find a way to stop him.

name: Elseworlds
title: Arrowverse
description: "Elseworlds" is the fifth Arrowverse crossover event that features episodes of The Flash, Arrow, and Supergirl on The CW. The crossover event began on December 9, 2018, with The Flash, continued on Arrow on December 10, and concluded on Supergirl on December 11.

name: Homicide: Life on the Street
title: 1993 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: Detectives investigate different homicide cases in inner-city Baltimore. Working for the police department, these detectives are committed to bringing justice to the streets of Baltimore.

name: Crime & Punishment
title: 2002 ‧ Reality ‧ 3 seasons
description: An unscripted look at actual cases brought to trial by the San Diego District Attorney's office. Although it is edited to have the look and feel of a prime-time drama series, it gives viewers a real behind-the-scenes view into the criminal justice system.

name: High Incident
title: 1996 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: High Incident was a police drama television series produced by DreamWorks Television for the ABC network. The show was created by Steven Spielberg, Michael Pavone, Eric Bogosian, and Dave Alan Johnson. It aired from March 4, 1996, to May 8, 1997, running a total of 32 episodes.

name: Hill Street Blues
title: 1981 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: A gritty, realistic look at the life of cops in a large (and unnamed) metropolitan city. Led by Capt. Frank Furillo, the cops of the Hill Street Station kept the peace - though there were plenty of casualties along the way. Focusing more on those within the precinct than on the cases they were trying to solve, "Hill Street Blues" cast of characters featured public defender Joyce Davenport (who later married Furillo), gruff Sgt. Phil Esterhaus (who always cautioned his charges to "be careful out there"), eccentric Lt. Howard Hunter, Officer Lucy Bates and Sgt. Mick Belker (who sometimes resorted to injuring the felons he apprehended).

name: New York Undercover
title: 1994 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: New York police Detectives J.C. Williams, a recently divorced cop trying to be a good father to his son, and Eddie Torres, a young Puerto Rican who struggles with his heritage, try to balance their stressful work duties with their own personal demands. Their boss, Lt. Virginia Cooper, is tough but fair in her assignments.

name: Stax: Soulsville U.S.A.
title: 2024 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: In 1960s, Memphis, Tenn., a set of interracial collaborators make music on their own terms, forming Stax Records, one of America's most influential creators of Black music.

name: The Black Hamptons
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: A feud between two families in the quaint town of Sag Harbor on Long Island, N.Y., starkly illustrates the difference between old and new money; based on the novel of the same name.

name: The Family Business
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: By day, the Duncan's are an upstanding family who run a car dealership. By night, they live a dangerous secret life. When they come under siege the Duncan's will have to stick together, or die.

name: David Makes Man
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: David, a child prodigy, looks for a way to escape his poverty-stricken life in Florida while struggling to move on from the death of his closest friend.

name: Queen Sugar
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: Two estranged sisters, Nova Bordelon and Charley Bordelon, along with Charley's son, Micah, set out to inherit their deceased father's sugarcane farm.

name: The BMF Documentary: Blowing Money Fast
title: 2022 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: "BMF: Blowing Money Fast" tracks the rise and fall of the most notorious drug syndicate in American history, Black Mafia Family, as chronicled through firsthand accounts of BMF members, insiders, associates, and celebrity figures close to the Flenory family. The series focuses on Meech's time in Atlanta, where he set up East Coast BMF headquarters and launched an entertainment company to promote rap artists in the early 2000s. He and his crew spent gobs of money on strippers and champagne at dance clubs and lounges while rubbing shoulders with P. Diddy and Lil Jon.

name: McGraw Ave
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Two men with different intentions navigate the streets of one of Detroit's most notorious neighbourhoods seeking dominance.

name: For Your Love
title: 1998 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: The romantic comedy features three couples who try to counsel one another on how to deal with the opposite sex.

name: One on One
title: 2001 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: A single father suddenly becomes a full-time dad when his ex-wife accepts a job out of the country and his teenage daughter, Breanna, moves in with him. The former athlete-turned-sportscaster finds his bachelor lifestyle completely turned upside-down as he and his daughter settle into a real familial relationship.

name: The Parent 'Hood
title: 1995 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: Former New York college professor Robert Peterson and his wife, Jerri, share their Manhattan brownstone apartment with their four kids, ages 3 to 15.

name: A Different World
title: 1987 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 6 seasons
description: A group of young students who study at the reputed Hillman College face the ups and downs life throws at them and get involved in hilarious situations.

name: The Parkers
title: 1999 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: Spunky daughter Kim is mortified when her bigger-than-life mom, Nikki, decides to go back to school at the same junior college she attends.

name: Single Ladies
title: 2011 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Set in Atlanta's fashion, music and celebrity circles, "Single Ladies" strives to find out what women really want in a relationship. The comedy-drama follows three best friends who don't hold the same philosophies on sex and relationships: Keisha is a former video dancer who wants a rich man to support her high style; April is finding out that her fairy-tale marriage to her supposedly perfect man isn't what she thought it would be; and Raquel is trying to break free from her mother's influence and attempting to stand up for herself and make her own choices.

name: Half & Half
title: 2002 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 4 seasons
description: Half-sisters Dee Dee and Mona are poles apart in terms of their upbringing and mannerisms. However, they shift in different homes in the same apartment owned by their father and try to get along.

name: The Hughleys
title: 1998 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 4 seasons
description: Darryl Hughley is a successful black businessman who seems to have achieved the American dream. When his family moves into a predominantly white neighborhood in California's San Fernando Valley, he and his family must try to adjust to their new lifestyle while not forgetting who they are and from where they came.

name: In The House
title: 1995 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: After an injury ends his professional football career, Marion Hill agrees to take a job as a "manny" to help his tenant, divorcee Jackie Warren, with her two children, Tiffany and Austin.

name: Living Single
title: 1993 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: Six black 20-somethings -- four women and two men -- share their lives and loves in a Brooklyn brownstone. A trio of women share one of the apartments, receiving frequent visits from a fourth pal; meanwhile, two men who've been friends for years share an apartment one floor up.

name: The Best Man: The Final Chapters
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Longtime college friends Harper, Quentin, Lance, Murch, Jordan, Robyn, Candace and Shelby face the midlife challenges of marriage, parenting, health, romance, work and identity as they revisit and redefine their friendships. Harper gets the opportunity to turn his book "Unfinished Business" into a movie as he aspires to elevate his literary standing and lifestyle. Quentin gets married and struggles to take over the family business from his obstinate father. Lance discovers new passions as he faces difficult parenting challenges. Jordan struggles to find a work-life-love balance on her journey toward self-care. Candace and Murch reframe their relationship as she pursues higher education and he fights for respect. Robyn searches for peace and her true place in the world. Shelby struggles to be taken seriously as more than a Real Housewife.

name: Roc
title: 1991 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: A hard-working man supports his extended family.

name: The Game
title: 2006 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 9 seasons
description: Melina travels with her boyfriend Derwin, a professional football player against her parent's wishes. She must act as a responsible partner to avoid Derwin from falling prey to a gold digger.

name: Soul Food
title: 2000 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: When Yannis moves with his mother to her partner's apartment, he starts to develop a bond with Olga, a middle-aged woman, who resides in the basement of his building.

name: Mama Flora's Family
title: 1998 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A black matriarch instills values of God and family in three generations of 20th-century kin. Adapted from a book by Alex Haley and David Stevens.

name: In the Heat of the Night
title: 1988 ‧ Drama ‧ 8 seasons
description: Carroll O'Connor stars as a small-town police chief (and later a sheriff) in fictional Sparta, Miss. For a small town, Sparta has its share of murder, rape, corruption, racism and drunken driving, so O'Connor's Chief William Gillespie has his hands full. The TV series is based on the novel and film of the same name.

name: The Jamie Foxx Show
title: 1996 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: Texas native Jamie King is an aspiring actor who heads to Hollywood in hopes to find fame and fortune in the entertainment industry. To support himself, he works at his uncle's Los Angeles hotel, the King's Towers. On the job, he competes for the attention of gorgeous desk clerk Francesca "Fancy" Monroe, who has made it clear that she is not interested in an office romance. Nevertheless, Jamie is determined to hone his skills as an entertainer and move into the limelight.

name: Thea
title: 1993 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 1 season
description: A feisty widow with four kids approaches life with humour and patience.

name: The Oval
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 6 seasons
description: Written, directed and executive produced by Tyler Perry, "The Oval" is a political drama series. It tells the story of U.S President Hunter Franklin and first lady Victoria Franklin, a power-hungry interracial couple, who present a perfect facade to the world while indulging in wildly scandalous behavior behind closed doors. Not to be outdone, their children -- Gayle and Jason -- bring their own brands of volatility and excess to the Executive Residence. The soap opera-style series also tells the stories of White House staff members whose lives become intertwined with those of the first family. Head butler Richard Hallsen is an ex-serviceman who struggles to maintain his integrity in the face of greed and corruption. In "The Oval," Tyler Perry supercharges the political genre with off-the-charts levels of scandal, sex, depravity and betrayal.

title: 1985 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: Follows the lives of a group of middle-class people living in an apartment building.

name: Unsung
title: 2008 ‧ Documentary ‧ 17 seasons
description: This documentary series takes a look at some of the top R&B and soul artists of the last several decades, many of whom are not household names. Narrated by actor Gary Anthony Williams, the NAACP Image Award-winning program features interviews with people who know the musicians well enough to tell the ups and downs of their careers. Episodes usually start with the story of an artist's upbringing before moving into the trials and tribulations faced as the subject searched for the big break early in his or her music career. The pinnacle of the performer's career plays out next, before a turning point that led to each one's career beginning a downward trend.

name: The Ms. Pat Show
title: 2021 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 4 seasons
description: A street-wise woman finds herself living in middle America as an unlikely suburban mum.

name: The Last O.G.
title: 2018 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 4 seasons
description: After 15 years in prison, Tray Barker returns to Brooklyn for a fresh start in life. However, his neighbourhood has changed completely and his ex-girlfriend is raising their children with a new man.

name: South Side
title: 2019 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 3 seasons
description: Two mischievous friends, after completing their graduation from a community college, dream to establish and succeed in business while working at a rent-to-own shop.

name: You Take the Kids
title: 1990 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 1 season
description: Michael Kirkland is a bus driver in Pittsburgh living with his wife Nell and their four children, Raymond, Lorette, Peter and Nate. Nell's mother Helen is living in the basement.

name: Out All Night
title: 1992 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 1 season
description: A former singer opens an urban nightclub in Los Angeles.

name: Built to Last
title: 1997 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 1 season
description: Built to Last is an American sitcom television series that aired from September 24 until October 15, 1997, on NBC.

name: New Attitude
title: 1990 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 1 season
description: Two sisters open a beauty salon.

name: The Royal Family
title: 1991 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 1 season
description: A soon-to-be divorced woman moves back home with her three kids.

name: The Sinbad Show
title: 1993 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 1 season
description: A carefree bachelor becomes a single parent when he adopts two orphaned children.

name: Getting By
title: 1993 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 2 seasons
description: Two single mothers share an office and a home.

name: Getting Personal
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy ‧ 1 season
description: Sam and Milo are best friends who work at a Chicago commercial production agency. Sam fixes up Milo on a blind date with an acquaintance named Robyn, and it turns into a disaster. The disaster continues when the two suddenly discover that Robyn has been hired as their new boss.

name: Martin
title: 1992 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 5 seasons
description: When Martin Payne is not running his radio show, he is running his funny tongue. His love interest Gina and friends Pam, Tommy and Cole find themselves in hilarious situations due to Martin's antics.

name: Me and the Boys
title: 1994 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 1 season
description: A widower is raising his three sons in Dallas with the help of his mother-in-law.

name: Linc's
title: 1998 ‧ Sitcom ‧ 2 seasons
description: Russell A. Lincoln, aka Linc, is the owner of Linc's Bar & Grill. Set in Washington, D.C., Linc's attracts a wide range of clientele - from cabbies to politicians. Together, the staff and guests deal with issues.

name: Coroner
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Jenny Cooper, a widowed coroner, lives in Toronto and faces several obstacles as she tries to solve a series of suspicious deaths.

name: Blue Murder
title: 2003 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: A detective and single mother struggles to balance her professional and personal responsibilities. Luckily, colleague Richard Mayne is always around to offer support.

name: The Last Detective
title: 2003 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Detective Constable Davies proves himself time and time again by cracking some of the most baffling cases that nobody seems to want. His hard work and dedication earn him the loyal support of many.

name: Dark Heart
title: 2016 ‧ Crime ‧ 1 season
description: As a young man sets out to investigate the murder of his parents, it begins to take a toll on his personal and professional life.

name: Mayo
title: 2006 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A comedy detective drama television series starring Alistair McGowan, Jessica oyelow, Huw Rhys and Loo Brealey. It is based on a popular series of Gil Mayo mysteries books by Marjorie Eccles.

name: Scott & Bailey
title: 2011 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: This program follows the personal and professional lives of two detectives working for a Manchester police unit that specialises in murder cases.

name: Common Law
title: 2012 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Travis Marks and Wes Mitchell are two police detectives who cannot stand each other. As a result, their commanding officer decides to send them for counseling.

name: 100 Centre Street
title: 2001 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Set in Manhattan's night court, this drama tells the stories of the judges, lawyers and criminals who populate the judicial system. The show's name comes from the street address that is the location of the criminal division of New York's Supreme Court. Alan Arkin stars in the show created by Sidney Lumet ("Network").

name: Above the Rim
title: 1994 ‧ Sport/Crime ‧ 1h 37m
description: Kyle, a promising high school basketball player, has to choose which team he wants to be a part of for a local tournament, his school team or a team run by a local drug dealer.

name: Poetic Justice
title: 1993 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 49m
description: Stuck with the dilemma of her murdered boyfriend, Justice finds salvation in expressing her feelings through poetry. Soon, she encounters a like-minded postal worker, who helps her overcome isolation.

name: Fresh
title: 1994 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 55m
description: Fresh (Sean Nelson) is a 12-year-old drug dealer who finds himself trapped in a web of poverty, corruption and racial tension in Brooklyn, New York. When his drug-addict sister Nichole (N'Bushe Wright) starts sleeping with local drug lord Esteban (Giancarlo Esposito), Fresh calls upon the skills he learned playing chess with his alcoholic father and speed-chess champion Sam (Samuel L. Jackson) and devises a complex strategy that will free both himself and his sister.

name: New Jersey Drive
title: 1995 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 38m
description: Jason (Sharron Corley) is an impoverished youth growing up in the slums of New Jersey. He and his pal Midget (Gabriel Casseus) get their thrills by stealing cars and taking them for joyrides. Eventually, the boys grow more serious about auto theft when they realize they can earn cash by passing off the lifted cars to black-market dealers -- which proves to be a risky way to make a living. Soon Jason finds himself on the wrong side of the law, and makes a dangerous enemy in his neighborhood.

name: Bad Boys for Life
title: 2020 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 2h 4m
description: Detectives Mike Lowrey and Marcus Burnett join the Miami Police Department's special team AMMO to bring down the ruthless Armando, who is on a mission to kill Mike at his mother Isabel's orders.

name: Under the Same Moon
title: 2007 ‧ Adventure/Drama ‧ 1h 49m
description: In a desperate bid to reunite with his mother who works illegally in the US, a 9-year-old tries to cross the Mexican border after the unexpected demise of his grandmother.

name: Rosario Tijeras
title: 2005 ‧ Romance/Crime ‧ 2h 6m
description: Rosario Tijeras (Flora Martínez) has been abused by men all her life, initially by her stepfather. Years later, she works as a paid assassin, seducing men and killing them when they least expect it. She meets Emilio (Manolo Cardona), a wealthy womanizer, and his best friend, Antonio (Unax Ugalde), at a nightclub, and starts an affair with Emilio despite Antonio's growing feelings for her. But circumstances bring her closer to Antonio, until her past catches up with her in a devastating way.

name: Bad Boys: Ride or Die
title: 2024 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 1h 55m
description: When their late police captain gets linked to drug cartels, wisecracking Miami cops Mike Lowrey and Marcus Burnett embark on a dangerous mission to clear his name.

name: El Chema
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: El Chema is an American crime television series premiered on Telemundo on December 6, 2016, and concluded on April 3, 2017. The series is produced by Argos Comunicación and Telemundo Studios for Telemundo. Starred and produced by Mauricio Ochmann. It is a spin-off of the series El Señor de los Cielos.

name: Pablo Escobar, The Drug Lord
title: 2012 ‧ History ‧ 1 season
description: An internationally recognised dramatisation of the life of the most feared drug dealer in the history of Colombia, Pablo Escobar Gaviria, who spread terror and violence throughout the country.

name: El Dragón: Return of a Warrior
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: A Tokyo-based financier must return to Mexico to replace his grandfather as head of a cartel. Two rivals are already causing trouble and he finds himself having to battle them for control.

name: Narco Circus
title: 2023 ‧ 1 season
description: Four-part documentary series in which investigative journalist Romain Bolzinger infiltrates the Sinaloa drug cartel, the most dangerous in Mexico, for three years. Looking for the answer to the question: Is the 'War on drugs' fake?

name: The One Who Couldn't Love
title: 2011 ‧ Romance ‧ 1 season
description: Ana Paula, a kind nurse, gets a job in a huge mansion where she has to take care of Rogelio, who is recuperating from an accident. She learns about his tragic past and slowly starts falling for him.

name: Eva la Trailera
title: 2016 ‧ Romance ‧ 1 season
description: A successful woman is tired of her husband's nature as he is an unfaithful person. She decides to leave him. Later, she meets another man who changes her life.

name: Imperio de mentiras
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Imperio de mentiras is a Mexican telenovela that aired on Las Estrellas from 14 September 2020 to 17 January 2021. The series is produced by Giselle González for Televisa. It is an adaptation of the Turkish series Kara Para Aşk, and it stars Angelique Boyer alongside Andrés Palacios.

name: Diablo Guardián
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Violetta, a frustrated teenager, decides to steal money from her parents and start her life anew in New York City to live the life she has dreamed of.

name: Operación Pacífico
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Operación Pacífico is an American drama television series produced by Telemundo Global Studios and Fox Telecolombia for Telemundo. The series it premiered on 10 February 2020 and ended on 17 April of the same year.

name: America's War on Drugs
title: 2017 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1 season
description: America has been fighting an ongoing war on drugs that has cost the country more than $1 trillion. This series steps through the history of the battle, from its origins to the unexpected effects it has had on American culture and politics.The timeline begins with President Nixon initially declaring a war on drugs following secret CIA LSD experiments, leading into the era of the famous "Just Say No" advertising campaign championed by former first lady Nancy Reagan. It goes on to explain how the Sept. 11 attacks intertwined the war on drugs with the war on terror and why Americans' demand for heroin and other illegal drugs is on the rise.

name: Savage Beauty
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Seeking revenge for her tragic past, a mysterious woman embeds herself in a powerful family who possess a global beauty empire, as well as dark secrets.

name: The Longest Night
title: 2022 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: The doctors and officials at a psychiatric prison begin to question their morals when a group of armed men attempt to capture Simon Lago, an inmate who they suspect is a serial killer.

name: Bad Blood
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Montreal Mafia boss Vito Rizzuto is released from prison after serving 31 years for murder and seeks revenge on those who killed his family and friends.

name: Hijack
title: 2023 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: When Flight KA29 is hijacked during its seven-hour journey from Dubai to London, corporate negotiator Sam Nelson tries to use his professional skills to save everyone on board.

name: When Heroes Fly
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: When Heroes Fly is an Israeli drama television series that was first broadcast in Israel on Keshet 12 in May 2018. The series was created by Omri Givon and loosely based on the novel of the same name by Amir Gutfreund. It uses flashbacks to account for the differing time periods.

name: Kingdom
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 3 seasons
description: Alvey Kulina, a retired MMA fighter, runs his own mixed martial arts gym. However, he must also keep his family together in the midst of various problems going on in his life.

name: Wentworth
title: 2013 ‧ Drama ‧ 8 seasons
description: Found guilty of attempting to kill her husband, Bea Smith is arrested and sent to Wentworth prison. While awaiting trial, she must learn how to survive in jail.

name: Clickbait
title: 2021 ‧ Thriller ‧ 1 season
description: When family man Nick Brewer is abducted in a crime with a sinister online twist, those closest to him race to uncover who is behind it and why.

name: True Story
title: 2021 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: A tour stop becomes a matter of life and death for a famous comic when the fallout from a night with his brother threatens to destroy everything he's built.

name: Celblok H
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: Celblok H is the Dutch adaptation of Wentworth, the Australian drama series about a women's prison divided in two camps. The series, produced by Willem Zijlstra, was broadcast at SBS 6 between March 3, 2014, and March 27, 2017. The last twenty episodes are original scripts.

name: Bad Girls
title: 1999 ‧ Drama ‧ 8 seasons
description: Portrayal of life in a women's prison, focusing on the inmates and staff's friendships and relationships, and the issues surrounding them.

name: Love Child
title: 2014 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: A modern, spirited midwife, returns from London in the 1960s and turns life on its head for everyone at Kings Cross General Hospital and Stanton House - a home for young unwed pregnant women.

name: Cocaine Cowboys
title: 2006 ‧ Documentary/Crime ‧ 1h 58m
description: Colombian drug lords and Cuban and American gangsters realised that America had developed a taste for cocaine in the 1970s/80s, the drug but the authorities were slow on reacting to the threat. There was profit for all with, initially, very little risk attached. The story is told through three key characters.

name: The True Story of Killing Pablo
title: 2002 ‧ Documentary/Crime
description: An exploration of the life of drug lord Pablo Escobar that culminated in the largest manhunt in history and the controversial 1993 killing of Escobar on a rooftop in Medellin, Colombia. Features interviews with key officials in Colombia and the U.S.

name: Alien: Romulus
title: 2024 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 59m
description: Space colonizers come face to face with the most terrifying life-form in the universe while scavenging the deep ends of a derelict space station.

name: Furiosa: A Mad Max Saga
title: 2024 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 28m
description: Snatched from the Green Place of Many Mothers, young Furiosa gets caught in the crossfire of two tyrannical warlords. As the tyrants fight for dominance, Furiosa soon finds herself in a nonstop battle to make her way home.

name: Alien 3
title: 1992 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 54m
description: Ellen Ripley's escape pod crash-lands on Fiorina 161, a penal colony planet terrorised by an alien. She rallies the inmates into killing it but realises that she is carrying an alien embryo herself.

name: Highlander
title: 1986 ‧ Action/Fantasy ‧ 1h 56m
description: Russell Nash, a mysterious Scottish swordsman, realises that he is immortal. Soon he finds himself in a ferocious battle against the powerful and wicked immortals who want to destroy the Earth.

name: Real Steel
title: 2011 ‧ Sci-fi/Action ‧ 2h 7m
description: Charlie, a prize fighter, loses his chance to win the title when humans are replaced by heavy, towering robots in the boxing ring. After failing badly, he teams up with his estranged son Max to win.

name: Superman II
title: 1980 ‧ Family/Action ‧ 2h 7m
description: Superman decides to give up his superpowers for the sake of his true love, Lois Lane. At the same time, three criminals from his home planet of Krypton land on Earth and try to conquer the world.

name: F.I.S.T.
title: 1978 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 25m
description: Johnny Kovak, a trade-union worker, makes his way up the hierarchy in the organisation. But things take a turn as Madison starts a campaign against him due to his ruthless management methods.

name: Million Dollar Baby
title: 2004 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 2h 12m
description: Frankie, an ill-tempered old coach, reluctantly agrees to train aspiring boxer Maggie. Impressed with her determination and talent, he helps her become the best and the two soon form a close bond.

name: XO, Kitty
title: 2023 ‧ Romance ‧ 2 seasons
description: Kitty, the youngest of the Covey sisters, embarks on a quest to find true love.

name: Feel Good
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Mae Martin, a comedian and recovering addict, tries to get a hold of her life but things complicate further when she starts dating George.

name: Gilmore Girls
title: 2000 ‧ Drama ‧ 7 seasons
description: The mother-daughter duo of Lorelai and Rory bond over everything they do and are essentially inseparable. Their lives depend on each other for the most part and to some extent on their close friends.

name: Ashley Garcia: Genius in Love
title: 2020 ‧ 2 seasons
description: Teenage robotics engineer and rocket scientist Ashley Garcia moves across the country to work for NASA and live with her uncle, a high school football coach.

name: Outer Banks
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 4 seasons
description: A teenager enlists his three best friends to hunt for a legendary treasure linked to his father's disappearance.

name: Gossip Girl Indonesia
title: 2020 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: Gossip Girl Indonesia is an Indonesian teen drama streaming television series developed by Nia Dinata for GoPlay. It is adapted from the American television series Gossip Girl, which is based on a series of books of the same name by Cecily von Ziegesar.

name: Dynasty
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 5 seasons
description: When billionaire Blake Caringlton gets married to a rival employee, his daughter and heiress to his fortune is unhappy. She forms new allies and tries to stand up to her father.

name: DI4RIES
title: 2022 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: At the Galileo Galilei middle school, days pass amidst a thousand surprises and events, first crushes, first kisses, beautiful friendships and even fights between rivals.

name: Puberty Blues
title: 2012 ‧ Comedy drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: `Puberty Blues' is based on the book written by Kathy Lette and Gabrielle Carey. This coming of age drama series is set during the late 1970s and focuses on the lives of best friends Debbie and Sue. The two inseparable teenage girls are seen growing up together in the beachside suburb of Cronulla. As the years go on the two friends become torn apart over a love affair and their lives are threatened by the oncoming bush fires destroying their homeland.

name: The Heavenly Idol
title: 2023 ‧ Romance ‧ 1 season
description: Lembrary, a deity, finds himself waking up in the body of singer Woo Yeon Woo. He has to lead a life as a K-Pop idol after an incident during a broadcast catapults Woo Yeon Woo's group to stardom.

name: Swarm
title: 2023 ‧ Horror ‧ 1 season
description: An obsessed, Houston-based fan goes to increasingly violent lengths for her favourite R&B singer.

name: Daisy Jones & The Six
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1 season
description: In 1977, Daisy Jones & The Six were on top of the world; the band had risen from obscurity to fame, and then, after a sold-out show at Chicago's Soldier Field, they called it quits; now, decades later, the band members agree to reveal the truth.

name: Snowdrop
title: 2021 ‧ Romance ‧ 1 season
description: An enduring love story in 1987 Seoul; Youngro, a female university student, treats the bleeding Suho, a student attending a prestigious university, who one day jumps into a women's university dormitory despite the dangerous situation.

name: Apartment 404
title: 2024 ‧ Reality ‧ 1 season
description: Six residents trace the truth behind extraordinary events that occur in their residences.

name: Special
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 seasons
description: Actor-writer Ryan O'Connell stars in this semi-autobiographical series based on his memoir. He plays Ryan, a gay man with cerebral palsy who decides to do away with his identity as an accident victim and go after the life that he wants. After years of dead-end internships, blogging in his pajamas and mainly communicating through text, Ryan figures out how to take his life from bleak to chic as he gets ready to start limping toward adulthood. O'Connell serves as an executive producer on the comedy series, along with "The Big Bang Theory" star Jim Parsons.

name: wtFOCK
title: 2018 ‧ Drama ‧ 8 seasons
description: WtFOCK is a Flemish teen drama web series broadcast by Play4 that follows the lives of teenagers in Antwerp. Broadcast was then taken over by Belgian streaming services Play More, Streamz, and GoPlay in preceding years. It is an adaptation of the popular Norwegian series SKAM.

name: Memories of Murder
title: 2003 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 12m
description: While South Korea is still under the military's reign, two local, unreliable detectives are joined by an experienced one from Seoul to investigate a series of mysterious murder cases.

name: Sympathy for Mr. Vengeance
title: 2002 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 9m
description: An expelled worker kidnaps his boss' daughter and asks for a ransom to be able to afford his sick brother's treatment.

name: I Saw the Devil
title: 2010 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 2h 22m
description: When his pregnant fiancee is murdered, secret service agent Soo-hyun sets out to seek revenge. He identifies the killer and forces him to swallow a GPS-tracking capsule.

name: Parasite
title: 2019 ‧ Thriller/Comedy ‧ 2h 12m
description: The struggling Kim family sees an opportunity when the son starts working for the wealthy Park family. Soon, all of them find a way to work within the same household and start living a parasitic life.

name: The Handmaiden
title: 2016 ‧ Thriller/Romance ‧ 2h 31m
description: A Korean con-man conjures up an elaborate plan to seduce a woman and swindle her of all her wealth. Along the way, he seeks the help of an orphan to ensure that he succeeds.

name: Mother
title: 2009 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 8m
description: When a mother learns that her mentally challenged son is accused of the brutal murder of a young girl, she conducts an independent investigation to prove his innocence.

name: A Bittersweet Life
title: 2005 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2 hours
description: The relationship between Sun-woo, a high-ranking gangster, and his leader, Kang, turns sour when the former decides to disobey his senior's command.

name: Kill Bill: Vol. 1
title: 2003 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 51m
description: A pregnant assassin, code-named The Bride, goes into a coma for four years after her ex-boss Bill brutally attacks her. When she wakes up, she sets out to seek revenge on him and his associates.

name: Drive My Car
title: 2021 ‧ Drama/Romance ‧ 2h 59m
description: An ageing, widowed actor takes a directing job in Hiroshima where he's required to get a chauffeur for insurance reasons. He hires a 20-year-old girl and, despite their initial misgivings, a very special relationship develops between the two.

name: American Fiction
title: 2023 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 57m
description: Monk is a frustrated novelist who's fed up with the establishment that profits from Black entertainment that relies on tired and offensive tropes. To prove his point, he uses a pen name to write an outlandish Black book of his own, a book that propels him to the heart of hypocrisy and the madness he claims to disdain.

name: The Father
title: 2020 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 37m
description: Anthony suffers from dementia and is cared for by his daughter, Anne. But when Anne decides to move to Paris and Anthony must deal with this change, he finds himself losing his grip on reality.

name: Marriage Story
title: 2019 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 2h 16m
description: A stage director and his actor wife struggle through a gruelling, coast-to-coast divorce that pushes them to their personal and creative extremes.

name: Poetry
title: 2010 ‧ Drama/Comedy ‧ 2h 19m
description: Mija, an old woman, is diagnosed with Alzheimer's disease and she later learns about a crime committed by a family member. In order to deal with her stress, she decides to join a poetry class.

name: Oldboy
title: 2003 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 2 hours
description: A man attempts to find the identity of the person who keeps him captive for several years for no rhyme or reason. Later, he receives money and is released, unaware of the fate that awaits him.

name: Shoplifters
title: 2018 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 1m
description: A family that survives by shoplifting brings an abused child into the fold. A death, however, sets into motion a series of events that causes them to take a deeper look at some aspects of their lives.

name: Broker
title: 2022 ‧ Crime/Drama ‧ 2h 9m
description: Two men who make a living by finding new parents for babies who are left anonymously in boxes meet a young woman who left her child behind, but now wants it back; two investigators are hot on the heels of the baby dealers.

name: Brokeback Mountain
title: 2005 ‧ Romance/Western film ‧ 2h 14m
description: Ennis and Jack are two shepherds who develop a sexual and emotional relationship. However, their relationship becomes complicated when both of them get married to their respective girlfriends.

name: Joint Security Area
title: 2000 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 50m
description: When two North Korean troopers die at the Korean Demilitarized Zone, a group of neutral investigators from the Neutral Nations Supervisory Commission examine the incident to find the perpetrators.

name: Beasts Clawing at Straws
title: 2020 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 48m
description: Beasts Clawing at Straws is a 2020 South Korean neo-noir black comedy crime thriller film written and directed by Kim Yong-hoon as his debut feature film. Based on the 2011 Japanese novel of the same name by Keisuke Sone, it features an ensemble cast led by Jeon Do-yeon and Jung Woo-sung.

name: The Grand Budapest Hotel
title: 2014 ‧ Comedy/Adventure ‧ 1h 39m
description: Gustave H, a concierge who works at a famous European hotel, must prove his innocence when he is framed for a murder. In the process of doing so, he strikes up a great friendship with a lobby boy.

name: Okja
title: 2017 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 2 hours
description: For 10 idyllic years, young Mija has been caretaker and constant companion to Okja - a massive animal and an even bigger friend - at her home in the mountains of South Korea. But that changes when family-owned, multinational conglomerate Mirando Corporation takes Okja for themselves and transports her to New York, where an image-obsessed and self-promoting CEO has big plans for Mija's dearest friend. With no particular plan but single-minded in intent, Mija sets out on a rescue mission.

name: Barking Dogs Never Bite
title: 2000 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 50m
description: Frustrated with loud barking, an academic (Lee Sung-jae) wages war against dogs in his apartment building.

name: Three... Extremes
title: 2004 ‧ Horror ‧ 1h 58m
description: Features an anthology centred on the experiences of a witch doctor, a film-maker and a disgruntled extra determined to take revenge on him, and a novelist as well as her twin sister.

name: Project Silence
title: 2023 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 41m
description: Trapped on a collapsing bridge, survivors of a massive car pile-up find themselves in a fight for their lives against a mysterious creature.

name: CODA
title: 2021 ‧ Musical/Comedy ‧ 1h 51m
description: Ruby is the only hearing member of a deaf family from Gloucester, Massachusetts. At 17, she works mornings before school to help her parents and brother keep their fishing business afloat. But in joining her high school's choir club, Ruby finds herself drawn to both her duet partner and her latent passion for singing.

name: The Artist
title: 2011 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 40m
description: When George, a silent movie superstar, meets Peppy Miller, a dancer, sparks fly between the two. However, after the introduction of talking pictures, their fortunes change, affecting their dynamic.

name: Beasts of the Southern Wild
title: 2012 ‧ Fantasy/Adventure ‧ 1h 33m
description: In the wake of her father's ill health and the flooding of her home, Hushpuppy, a six-year-old girl, must brave prehistoric creatures called aurochs and seek out her lost mother.

name: Central Station
title: 1998 ‧ Drama/Road ‧ 1h 55m
description: Dora, a school teacher, helps illiterate people pen letters they wish to send loved ones. When one of her clients dies, she helps her son find his father.

name: The Illusionist
title: 2006 ‧ Romance/Thriller ‧ 1h 49m
description: When two lovers are separated owing to their class differences, the boy decides to become a magician. He must use his powers to free his lady from the royal residence.

name: Donnie Darko (Director's Cut)
title: 2004 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 2h 14m
description: Donnie Darko: The Director's Cut is a 2004 re-cut version of Richard Kelly's directorial debut, Donnie Darko. A critical success but a commercial failure when first released in 2001, Donnie Darko grew in popularity through word-of-mouth due to strong DVD sales and regular midnight screenings across the United States.
